\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Could I have your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh my name is Anne. Anne, oh Anne Mainwaring now you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And your present Address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Number 60 Tanygores Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And you are married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, I'm married of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And the year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well there that was - that was - 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Year of my birth was 1880.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I was born in Grugwallt Farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In Margam. In Margam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well we didn't because it - my mother died on my
 birth you see, my sister took me to Penny-y-Cae. My sister was married to Rhys Nicholas, Betsa's daughter - son you know. Well - they took me then you see, they had no children of their own then and they took me up to Pen-y-Cae, and there I was brought u
p until I was ten. And then I went back to Margam to my father to the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long were you there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well there I was there then all the time you see, all the years, all my life then until - 1911.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And where did you move in 1911?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 To Tanygroes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 To 60 Tanygroes Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And that's where I am now. Been there 60 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you know why you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well we had a house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 First of all you moved because your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - oh yes, that was while they were to take care of me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When you were ten you went back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I went back then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why did you move back then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well, we went back of course we had a - my sister had a big family, had seven children by now. Then I went back to my 
father to Margam. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And then you moved from Margam to Tanygroes on marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. That - and that's all the - and that's all the - oh we were there for a while after you see and we were there for a while - went up to grandma to Port - to - we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 were in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  Margam until then, we moved to Port Talbot on 19 - in 1911, buy we had been - of course I had been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I had four sisters. I had four sisters and four brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was Margaret born in 1859, Mary 1863, Catherine 1868, Lizzie 1877, John.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, John was be - the first - John was next to Margaret. Yes, I see now. William 1865. Daniel 1872. Rhys 1875 and yourself 1880.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - I should think because my mother was forty-two - I have an idea that my father was - two years older than her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 About forty-four?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 From Carmarthen. Carmarthenshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he have another job before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, he always was, he was born and brought up on a farm. Yes, always farmed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he do any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he do any jobs before he died, any other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, nothing, no, he was a farmer all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 My mother was born in that house, and here forefathers from - from what I could gather, that the old famil
y had lived there nine hundred years. It was one of the granges of Margam, the old house. Very very old. The old - the - front wall - I think was - they said was nine hundred years. And then - no the back wall - my father was said nine hundred years, had 
b
een there nine hundred years, and then the front wall was three hundred years. It was a very strange old house. A long old place, with - seats, window seats would be - the wall was thick you see, thick enough to put a seat, there you are, we had seats in 
the window like that, but it was all part of the wall. The walls were over a yard wide. Thickness. It was very old place, thatched, thatched and thatched and thatched. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your mother have any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, she always lived at home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Only - no, only at home that's all. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I think it's Pen-y-Cae we ought to talk about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember how many rooms were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Now then. There was one - it
 was a house of one big room. When we went there. My brother-in-law was a carpenter you see. And - it was - on the Margam estate of course they used to pay a shilling a week for it, for the houses there then. And there was a kind of a slope in the back. B
ut there was only one room. And then he had made a partition upstairs, to make it into two bedrooms. Then there was a big stone step here, and then a flight of stone steps going up. Up the stairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where was it in Pen-y-Cae?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Now - no, no. Now you 
know where you turn around - you know where - where the - where the transport comes - and goes down the hill, Pen-u-Cae Hill, well you know you come around, that - then bend there, just where Mrs Track and - where their house is now. Well it would be from
 that - it would be about the fifth house, right in there. Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What was the name of the road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh just Pen-y-Cae Road. That's all. Yes. Peny-Cae Road. And it looked straight down you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did anyone else besides yourself live in the house, there was your sister and her husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. And her husband. And then there came Rhys, Maggie - and the little girl that died, Lizzie. Nellie Maud, know Nellie Maud of course. Bethy, well he died. And Dorrie. And John Morgan. Yes, she had seven children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When you were a little girl how many were living there now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well it was Rhys and Maggie and Nellie Maud and - Rhys and Maggie and Nellie Maud. And the kittle girl that died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Rhys was your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Rhys was their eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was only you from your family was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I was the only one of our family, they took me - a baby ten days old you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You went to live with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And her husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. And then after that - they didn't have one then you see. No, they didn't have one for three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They didn't have any children when they took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. They didn't have one. Then they had - in - there was fifteen months, in fifteen months she had Rhys. And then there was Ma
ggie, Lizzie, Nellie Maud, and Bethuel, and Bessie, and John Morgan. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was your sister who looked after you, not your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was my sister you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your sister pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did she made or mend the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well she would mend them I expect, but my - other sister was a dressmaker you see. Cathy was a dressmaker. And - she used to make the clothes for us. And of course we - things were sent to me from home you see, that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Your sister at home would really make your clothes would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well they - she was learning to be a dressmaker you see, yes, that sister that - she used to sew for my sister, would 
make all the things of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have new clothes or second hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh new ones, I don't remember ever having - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were they bought at all or all made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 All made at home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When would you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 We usually used to have them - Whitsun, new set of clothes Whitsun then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 We had to wear boots, we used to wear then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have new ones or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Oh new ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When would you have new boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I'd have new - new boots, with new clothes. Yes. But I used to have mine - my new clothes about - I usually - in the spring, the gymanfa Bwnc and I was always reciting a chapter somewhere, and I was usually have a new suit, a new hat for that you see. I r
emember having a hat to go and recite a chapter - a white one with blue - streamers hanging down the back. Oh dear, dear I can remember the fro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 cks I had. Black velvet.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they nake the hats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was a shop in town - Mrs Owen made them. My s
ister used to go there to have our hats made. I don't remember the name but I know her father was called - Evans the druggist, he was the only - chemist in - Aberafon then, and his daughter had a millinery shop, and she used to make hats, and I can rememb
er my sister taking me there for her to measure me to - make a hat up. Yes, I remember that very well. Yes. I forget her name now, she had a - she didn't have a - a Welsh name. No. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your brother-in-law help your sister with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, yes, used to do everything. Yes, and he was wonderful, he did - and he transformed that house you know. He made it bigger, he made - he made a new - a new little kitchen, and he - as I told you, he - he made a partition in the - an
d he made new doors and new windows, but we still had the - stone stairs. Yes. Oh yes, he was very musical, very musical. The first thing that I can remember, and another thing he did, now this house was open, just one room, but he made a partition to com
e
 in beside the door, so as to - it used to cut the path to the - especially where the fireplace was you see, it used to make it - quite cosy then. And this partition, the first thing I can remember, on this partition was a modulator, the tonic solfa came 
o
ut then, John Curwin, and it was a big voice I suppose and he was very musical, and he used to teach children in Pen-y-Cae then. He had a big Band of Hope. Tonic solfa they used to call it. Tonic they used to call it. And - my first recollection now is - 
of that modulator hanging on the wall, and - yr wyddor gymraeg, the Welsh alphabet, I used to learn it you see. The Welsh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 alphabet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 . And - when I was about three years old I was saying anything in solfa, no matter what I heard. And whatever I'd hear anywhere
 I'd - I - sing it in solfa. I've always had solfa, it's stuck into me, and I could read when I was four. I was moved up from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
hevestry when I was six into the girls chalss. But you had to be able to read before you should go in Pen-y-Cae then you know. An
d - but that was the way I was brought up. Sitting on the little step, I can see it now, little stone step and singing from the - and learning the manual signs from the hands, I would sing anything from - or do anything, and I do it now. Quite natural now
.
 But - I remember one - yes, it was - it was at the singing school, and of course everybody was learning solfa now, so - I remember me being put to sing, I was three to four years old, three years old I think, they said I was, of course I'm going from wha
t
 they were saying you see, put to sit on the table in the vestry, the old vestry now, the other side of the road, and - put to sit there and - then - this - the - singing school would sing the hymn from my hand, doe me fah soh, on French, the tune French.
 
And they were singing hymns and me doing - the manual signs with my hands, sitting on the table, and very strange, oh years - years after that, not so many years ago, do you remember Mrs Enoch? Now then - you see, she was - she was ninety something when s
h
e died. And I remember telling me, I was up in Pen-y-Cae to some big meeting or other and she said to me, do you know what is the first memory I have of you? No I don't. Sitting on the table in Penycae and us singing a tune from your hand. And I'd forgott
en all about that but - dear, she brought it back vivid to my mind you know Yes. Well that's the way - we were brought up you see. Then. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So your brother-in-law was very helpful around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he do any cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Everything, he used to do - there was no - used to do the papering, painting, everything about it to be done you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he ever do any cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't know whether he - whether there was any time for him to cook, if - well i
f it was necessary, my sister was laid up or something like that of course he used to - look after the children like a woman. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he wash up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh dear yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he make the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, and the - used to light the fire every morning. Before he went out, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he ever undress you or dress you or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, and oh - yes, he used to - take the children you see, to help her oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, he taught u
s to read. Taught - taught us to read, I would read anything when I was four years old, he was very - he was very keen on - in that way. And I was probably quick to learn to you know, I don't know, I - whether I had that gift to - or not, but - I remember
 
I was very very young and I don't know, I'd had something wrong that day - I don't know whether I'd - said an untruth and I was - terrified of saying an untruth you know, and we wouldn't dare - say an untruth, I had done something that day. I think I said
 
an untruth that I had - not done something that I had done, or I - hadn't done something. But however I was going to bed that night, after having undressed and said our prayers by the fire you know, and I was going on to the step and he came to me, wait, 
h
e said to me, and he opened the hymn book. Read this, he said to me, the children who serve Christ will ever escape sad or sorry hell. Myriad of young people in heaven are pearls in his crown. And I only looked at him - and up I went to bed. Better than a
ny sermon. Yes. Always in Penycae, and they all said the same. Everybody. Oh he was, he was as wonderful as - granny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Of course he was her son?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He was her son you see. And old granny, oh dear, you go down to Twell yny Sare, she used to put me to 
stand, there was a partition made there too, now which is the best chapter you have learned? And I had to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 recite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
 the last thing I'd learned you see. But I'll always remember the children who serve Christ, and I only looked you know, and off I went to bed and there - oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, well we knew all the Bible you see that way, yes. He was wonderful. He was wonderful. Yes indeed. Wonderful man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he take you out without your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't remember s
o much about that because - there wasn't much going out then you see. Of course when every - when one went everyone went then you see, they - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he look after you when she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. YES? YES. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any little jobs you had to carry out regularly at home to help your sister and her husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I - well after I came - oh look after the baby. I used to look after the baby always if only for them to go to chapel or - I always used to mind the baby for them to go 
to chapel. Or to go to - to - shopping or something like that you know. Yes, oh yes, and wash the dishes, I did that very early. But mind the baby was my - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have to look after the baby in any way, did you help to dress or to feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. Oh no, only look after it, and rock the cradle. Used to rock the cradle of course. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 We went to bed at six o'clock every night. And he had the singing school you see as they 
called the - and they used to come down there to practice. And there were one or two cracks in the - in the ceiling, and we used to hear - oh, lots of them did their courting in - in - my sister's house. Mary Banford or John Jenkins and - oh dear, a lot o
f
 them, John Davis and - I can remember them very well you know. And they used to sing, and lovely voices there then, oh - he had a wonderful choir, and we were going to - we were going to sleep like that, and I was peeping through. Dear, yes. Yes, they us
ed to come there to learn. And practice if there was any eistedfodds or anything on. There they come to practice you see, there they come to learn. Dave Rhys Pickton and all those, you know, maybe your mother would be able to say all this tune.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And you children would be put to bed upstairs?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\tx7106\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid13252668 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And we'd be put to bed the others would go to sleep but I was so fond of that sort of thing you know that I wanted to hear you see.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid13252668 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
You were musical you see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. I was full of it, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh my sister and he would you know, take us all up, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I don't know, I don't - well probably when I went up back home you see. My sister used to - take us all up to bed you see. Yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh we had to because there was only two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was only one bedroom really wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, divided you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you share the bed with one of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, with the children and - the little - the younger ones would be with me for me to take care of them you see. Yes. I used to look after the younger ones. Nellie Maud was my baby you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would be the sleeping arrangements then, would your sister and her husband be one side of the partition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. On one side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they have one of the children in with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, there'd be one or two with them you see, yes. And probably the baby would be there. With my sister, oh y
es, the baby would be - with my sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were only ten when you left there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Only ten. And then there were more children then you see, the - another one or two were coming then you see. Yes. Although mind - when John Morgan, of course after Jo
hn Morgan came - but that was after - after my time of course, my brother-in-law as I told you - had made another part, well now - John Morgan of course he was - he was so marked, John Morgan Nicholas and Miss Talbot took an interest in him you see, and s
he wanted to know now - of course when he was - she put him in Eton College. Yes, she sent him to Eton, well now - she wanted -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did she get interested in him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I'll tell you love, Je - John - do you remember John, he loves his choir, you'
ve heard of it but perhaps you don't remember John Graves' male voice choir, and John Morgan - was a - very small, he was very - he own the National when he was twelve you see, and he became a marked boy, he was a prodigy that - he was called that you see
. Well now then - of course he went - they went up to the Castle to give a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 concert}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
 in the Castle every year, same as we used to in Gores of course. And - and they'd - and he would play - John Phillips would play. And - he was a pianist, and then they took h
im - and of course she went to ask about him and where he'd come from and his - family tree and all the rest of it, and of course she found it was of the old family from - from Lligart. And she took a great interest in. Well of course after that she asked
 my father twice to let me go to her. She wanted to educate me you see. For my mother's sake she said. Yes, I could have gone. But my father didn't feel inclined to you know. No, to let me go to London.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I didn't
 know you see, I was - didn't tell me then. No. No, he didn't like the idea because - the Castle life was very different from ours. But she came up twice they said to ask him. Yes. Yes, she said, well - I could do more for her, she said, than either you c
a
n do, can't expect you to - educate her but I suppose - I was marked when I was in Groes school you see because everybody - all the chief parts. And helped the schoolmaster to teach the children - to sing. Well I was only twelve then you see. And he was -
 very keen for me to go in - for teaching, I could have gone in for teaching then. But there you are. Other things came, my sister wanted me to come to her - to - the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Rhondda{\*\xmlclose}
, she went to keep a shop there, and she wanted me to come to her and I went up there and - I've had a varied life. Very. Varied life, different. Until I was - seventeen or eighteen and - my sister got married and then I - I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 stayed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  at home and then - put all my work into Groes chapel. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What room did you bath in in Pen-u-Cae?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well we bathed all of us in front of the fire in the kitchen. Yes. All, one after the other. And in the farmhouse too. Yes. Yes, big - a gig - pan you know, big brown pan. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How often would you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well of course there was a - oh a good wash every night of course. But every Friday night. YES. Every Friday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When would, you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well then - we used to bath on Friday night, no, no. No, no, Saturday night, Saturday, then had clean clothes for Sun
day. They were all in a row. Hanging by the fire. Yes. And it's very strange you know that will stick to you. I was the same with the children you see. All their clothes ready on Saturday night and - and all their - and doing their hair and - used to take
 me about - the three girls, it used to take me an hour and a half to do their hair. Oh dear, dear. Oh I remember it. Dear, dear, dear, dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - in - oh - well of course it was all - one of course you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did your sister cook?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh there was a - there was a big oven you see in size, she used to put - do all the cooking there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 A coal range was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was an old - oh a coal - coal oven you see, there was an oven on the side. Beside the fire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh about eight - about eight o'clock. Oh yes, about eight, because we had to go to school - well we went to school by half past nine then. Eight to half past you see, or - of course there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would he having breakfast then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well now my brother-in-law used to come home to have breakfast from the sawmills. Yes. Used to come home at half past eight always. Used to go down -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What time would he go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh go down by six in the morning. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was he working in the sawmills?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In the sawmills.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Quite near wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well it was down the road you see, down by the - down the steep hill there. You know where Pistyll Tydraw is. Well now then - their house was on
 the top then. And he would run down. And from there I used to carry water. Carry every drop of water from there. There was no tap or anything anywhere near. Carry water for everything. Except for washing and then they had - everybody had a cask outside t
heir back. Big cask in the back you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Tell me about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. Now then outside - the back there was a big black cask. Everybody had - I think they're finished with them, I think they were there. With the houses. Everybody had a big cask, and th
ere you had water for washing, and for doing - household then you had to carry water, from Pistyll Tydraw then. Well there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You had it just straight from the mountain stream?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Carry two - two pitchers of - it's a wonder to me that I've go
t hands or a back. The - all the nursing and all the carrying water I did. And even after going home to Margam, we had to carry water for - a mile, more than a mile, every drop of water the - except water - well - you know, we couldn't wash in the water w
e
 had, a big old well - in the garden, there was a big pond on the side of the road, but of course that would do all right for - washing anything. We could wash the potatoes or taking them down from the field or - something like that, but - you couldn't us
e
 it for anything but the animals could drink it. It was clean. Otherwise we had to take them down the Roman Bath to get clean water. And we had to carry water for more than a mile. Over the fields. I - I'm sure I carried tons and tons. Hundreds of tons I'
m sure. So it's a wonder I'm very very economical. And the same now from when I was in Pen-y-Cae, from Tydraw, you had to - carry all the water. But - as I say, you know I can see the old - the old cask now, at the back door.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd have enough from that from the rainwater?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh the rainwater you see, but we had to be very sparing, with that. When - when the dry weather came you see it was very awkward. But Pistyll Tydraw never failed. Used to go a little less sometimes. And then when - when the wor
st came to the worst - of course they had to go to the river. The river was coming down you see at the side of the road. The river was beside us when we were going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Your brother-in-law would have gone out early in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And then he'd come back for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Come back at half past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you all have your breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he have anything to eat or drink before he went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember whether he would, well
 I wouldn't know I don't suppose you see, whether probably he would drink a cup of tea, we'd be do - he'd be lighting the fire. And my sister was going down you see. I expect he would be getting a cup of tea for going out. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would you usually have to drink and eat for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh, a cup of tea. Toast, bread and butter and egg or some - whatever would be easy. Eggs used to come from home of course, from Margam, and the butter and my sister used to make the butter. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have anything different on certain days for breakfast, would you have different on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well, not on - I don't remember, if we didn't have - eggs in the week we'd - we'd say get one on a Sunday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the midday meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh a dinner, they used to have a dinner. Broth and soup and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would be there for the dinner midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh all the children of course, we'd all be there for the - midday -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When would you have the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh twelve to one you see, one o'clock would be the dinnertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would your brother-in-law be there then as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, he was coming home - he used to come home to dinner. But if he had a - something special to do now, such as making coffins or anything like that, as 
he was - he was looking after that sort of thing, I used to take dinner down to him then, in a little basin. Yes. I carried many a little dinner in a basin. Tied up with a handkerchief. Yes, and a little - a little tin then with tea in it you see. Took th
at many times down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the other meal, would you have different midday now on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well we'd have a - dinner on Sunday of course but - Sunday dinner was a big dinner you see. Big dinner than the week. My sister used to - cook in the
 meat on Saturday night. Yes. Chapel Sunday morning. Only the vegetables had to be done. Yes, Sunday morning. Ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What sort of meals would you have midday in the rest of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - there you are, soup or broth or whatever would be - pea soup or - plain food, wholesome food, plenty of it. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What other meal would you have in the day, would have an evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, well we'd have breakfast and dinner and tea. And then perhaps a cup of something before you went to bed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would you have for tea?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh there'd be cake for tea you see or fruit or - anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Had tea. Cup of tea, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your sister bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes, she made everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, everything, she used to make everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would she bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well there wasn't so much bottling fruit then you see. But she used to make jam. Used to get fruit from home, from - from Margam, plenty of fruit there you see. Any amount of fruit. Growing in the garden there. Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 lots}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  of stuff used to be sent, of course father used to see that - she had them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would she make wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. No, I don't remember anything about wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, well - no, not - only the - well what do it - vinegar and honey and - some things like to you know for colds, lemon. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. We had nothing to do with beer at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about small beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh diodfaen she used to make. She used to make diodfaen sometimes, yes. Oh yes. She used to do that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. He had an allotment. Up in - Caerhendy now. H
e had an allotment there. And he used to try for Margam flower show sometimes. Yes, tried there, potatoes and - onions and all that sort of thing you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they have to buy any, or would they grow all their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh we used to grow all our o
wn because, you see then there was from home again, plenty of Swedes and everything that was - plenty from a big garden there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have any tinned vegetables or tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I don't remember anything tinned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Or dried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I never remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Dried fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes - in Pen-y-Cae? Oh no. Oh no, nothing. No, nothing, only a bird. We had a bird in the house. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Easit a canary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 A little canary. I remember the bird very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh I don't know. There'd be something made, some sort of meat, bacon there - we'd have plenty of - that from home you see. Bacon and ham and things like that, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I never remember seeing tinned meat. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever have any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not from coaching. But they used to catch them at home you see, the dogs used to. Oh no. Not allowed to do that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But you'd have rabbit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh because - of the - because of the farm you see. Plenty of that. And chickens. Things like that you see from the farm. We were as - we had an advantage that way. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember seeing your sister having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh no, I don't remember that. She might have mind. She might have but - I don't remember. Much about that. Well I wouldn't have been - perhaps I wouldn't have been old enough to - take notice of things like that do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You would notice if your brother-in-law had more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, we were not allowed to talk, no. No, we were not supposed to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked, or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - oh well, we had to take what was given.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What was your sister and brother-in-law's attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I don't - I don't remember - sometimes we'd say we'd enough for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 
ourself}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 . It was very seldom though. No, they knew exactly what we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you hav
e to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - I don't know, if you wanted it you had to ask for it I suppose. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Probably if you wanted any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I don't remember about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have to sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, I don't - I don't remember about that, oh probably we did - have to sit straight.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Could you bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No, not then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well after you'd - after you said your grace and after you were allowed - when you were allowed to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they always have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Probably they did, yes. Yes, as far as I can remember I always had the same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You don't remember how you sat round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I don't. No. I know that my sister sat there and my brother-in-law sat there, and we
 were around, it was a round table we had. Remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they sit next to one another, your brother-in-law and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. I don't - no, they - one at each end of the table and then the children would be - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where would be the babies, the young ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh the baby would be either in a cradle or on the little high chair or - there was a little high chair then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would feed the baby then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh my sister, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How was the meal served, who would serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I don't know, it was put out on the plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was put on the plate ready?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 YES. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What order were you served would you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mm. No, I don't remember. Because there was just about the same put on every pla
te and - whoever would carry them in to the table put them down. Yes. YES. No, there was not any - any marked preference in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was your sister an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. She was very strict. Oh yes. Quite strict. Yes, quite - 
strict for behaviour and - and speech and - strict, she was strict to the end. And they knew it and in the Band of Hope too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did she show affection to you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, well of course I was her sister and there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I didn't know any difference you see. Until one day in school. In the fore school and I was on then between nine and ten. Was it, no. I was younger than that. And one of the girls, of course I used to go to the Band of Hope you see and - and Su
nday school, and one of the girls, I think }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 she\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
 alive now, I haven't heard of her death, and she said to me, your mother is dead, she said to me. Somebody had told her you see that Mrs Nicholas was my sister. Your mother is dead. And - we'd just come out 
from school. I began to scream. And I ran all the way home, up the hill, screaming. And when I got in my sister was there. I said to her - By the door, she could hear me. She couldn't understand what was the matter. And I said, Mary Griffiths said you wer
e dead. And then it dawned on her. That if she didn't tell me others would you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did she tell you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So there I think I was told after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Well then it was mixed. Then the mixing began you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So you called her mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh mam always. Mam to the end. Mam to the end. I couldn't call her anything else. Speaking about her it would be Margaret you see. But - when I did speak to her, but - of course Margaret she was after. After I went home she was Margaret.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When you went back to the farm?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. When I went back home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But mam she was to you before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mam when I was small. Yes. With the other children you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You didn't know really until then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And I didn't know you see. 
And then I - I was on between eight and nine, and I ran home, and I thought - and it was then I realized - then I knew. And yet always - there had always been - I - I'm sure any child that had - been through it, I'd always felt somehow - at the back of my
 mind - that there was somebody there. Always had a feeling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about your father, what did you call your father in the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh my father of course, yes. They were both fathers. Oh yes, they were both you see, yes. But he too of course - he wa
s supposed - to be - a - like the grandfather was it. But still I knew he was my father you see, and then I - and I knew that Rhys Nicholas was - so I had two fathers you see. See, you get used to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You don't think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, you don't reason things out. No child does.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you think when it came to you you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I used - when - when I went home and told her. Well then of course she realized you see, of course I don't remember what - what passed between but then - father an
d mother they were each other. Well they were father and mother to me. They were good to me, I called them - I couldn't do anything else and I called them father and mother to the end. And I called him father because oh he was wonderful. He was a wonderfu
l man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You didn't feel any different from their children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You felt they were your brothers and sisters did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, no. But I was the eldest of the children you see. Yes, but oh my - but there was - and now when my fathe
r - when my father from - Margam used to come up to Pen-y-Cae now there was a - there was always something about him, it's strange isn't it. You couldn't say what it was you see. It's - I often think of - any little girl - to a girl I think it's worse tha
n a boy. Yes, to lose a mother. I think. But she was - she was a good mother, and she taught me and they both taught me, and brought me up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 If you had any worries could you share them with her not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't remember now, whether I would - oh
 but I was very - I was - I don't know if you can say and I think it has been a fault with me. I was very sensitive. I've always been sensitive, and I never can stand cross words. Never. Even now I don't like the cross word. No. But then I used to be terr
ified of cross words. Yes. Any cross word anywhere now. YES. Oh yes, I was very sensitive, probably - it was my nature but there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about your father, was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 If you had any worries could you share them with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I could tell him you see and he would - he was very - oh he was a wonderful man wonderful. Wonderful, if I wanted to know anything about the Bible ask him. He read it thre
e times through. And he knew everything. And they say that my mother was wonderful in the Bible. Wonderful. And she was determined that the boys should be ministers. And they both came. Yes. Yes, it was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - we wouldn't think of behaving any other way than - what was right. Yes. Oh - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, of course we had to look after - I had to look 
- I was a mother - I was a second mother when my sister would be laid up you know or something like that. I had to look after them then of course. Oh and nurse them, oh I nursed my share.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh no. No. No, they never believed that. They never said that, nor I have never said it. No. Although I may be wrong, but I never told the children. Somebody would do something to them, do - give it back, I - I don't know how it is but - I tell t
hem never mind, they'll be hurt more than you in some other way. You see the first time - that I - recited a chapter - in the gymanfa bwnc, of course the gymanfa bwnc used to be a great thing then, it was more, I think people thought more of it than the g
ymanfa garni then, which was of more importance, and I remember the gymanfa bwnc was in Carmel. And I was being taught, my brother-in-law taught me - to recite - the fifth chapter of Romans.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Three years old. I would have been f
our in June, and this was on Good Friday. And - I hadn't been well. And I can remember him carrying me on his back, down - we had to go down the field you know, down to got to Carmel down to the road, and I couldn't walk all down that field of course, and
 
I had a black velvet frock, and had two streamers, remember that very well, and - and my brother-in-law carrying me on his back down until we were on the road, and then taking me down to Carmel. And I remember going in the seat and into the big seat, and 
the old minister in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Carmel{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 then was Rhys Phillips, and it was he had buried my mother I suppose. When she died. He was a minister there and - so I remember - the priest taking me in to the big seat and putting me to sit there. And there was a - I think they
've got one in - Duffryn now, as tell to put the Bible on, in the big seat, have they got it in there? They had it in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Carmel{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 then. And I was so small - that of course I had to be put up to stand up there, he put me up there. But however when - I can rememb
er John Nicholas was standing on the gallery, the front of the gallery meeting the people you know, with his back towards - me, and I was afraid he was going to come down on his back towards - me, and I was afraid he was going to come down on his back all
 
the time, I was terribly frightened I can remember very well, and I was telling Rhys you know, of course he was Rhys' brother Uncle John is going to fall. No, no, he's all right. And he was leading the singing. But however - they started after this, all s
a
t down, I was quiet then. And now Rhys Phillips said, well now, he said Annie Jones is going to recite the chapter. And I turned round, I didn't know my name was Annie Jones you see. And I turned round to Rhys, I said, I am saying the chapter. And everybo
dy heard me I suppose. So that - they had quite a bit of fun over it, oh I heard that story many times. So now I was too small to stand on the big seat you see, so Rhys had to put me to stand on a - on a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 ostrum. But anyway - Bible, and there he held me up 
- to recite the chapter. And then of course Rhys Phillips I suppose was - explaining to them about me, why did I say that I was going to - because I thought I was Annie Nicholas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel about that, when did you realize that you were Annie Jones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - it was - oh yes, then you see, I had to - yes. Oh dear, dear, dear, well I remember that very well but - then - I - I did }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 recite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  the chapter when I was four in some gamanfa, but when I was five - there were big meetings in Penycae, in Saron
, and it was - he was preaching. And I had learnt the first chapter of John, it's a big one you know. Of course I was - I've heard of this since then because I wouldn't remember that you know. At that time, but I remember it distinctly. I remember granny 
t
well yn y Ware calling, granny that used to call Betsan, was granny twell yn y Ware, calling in my sister's, and she come on - on the Monday to the two o'clock - service, Monday afternoon. And my sister had a cloak and a little bonnet - then. And she was 
q
uite young. And granny had her shawl, touching the ground at the back you see, a three cornered, and I - and she was catching my hand going up to chapel, to Penycae and - and - and you know - I can feel the fringes on the fringe of the shawl now on my han
d
, she was holding my hand, and into the chapel and there by the door Rhys was meeting us, and took me upstairs. And I'd never been up the steps, the stairs up to the gallery, never been there. I didn't know where I was going. So up to this gallery I went.
 
And there put to sit by the clock. And there's a - a little shelf by the clock, you know the clock doesn't come up one with the gallery, there's a little shelf behind it, where the clock is. I was put to sit there. Had to look round, saw this big man - in
 
the pulpit, the big eyes you know. Well - I was terrified. And I said to Rhys, I am afraid of that old man. And - he is a nice man. Say the chapter now loudly, everyone wants to hear you. But however my name was called to say - to recite the chapter. And 
R
hys putting me to stand - on this little ledge behind the clock you see. And I started. And off I went of course, I knew - well - when I learnt a chapter I learnt it and I knew every word. Went through. And he put - and as - as I finished you see the old 
m
an shouted - wonderful. And I didn't know what ardderchog was. I'd no idea of course. I thought I'd done it all wrong. I began to cry. I suppose I screamed. They had to take me home. They had to. And when I was going out and the old man was saying it I su
p
pose, it went to - and when I was going out granny was beginning to shout you know, she used to be noticed for - she used to get up then you see and come on, and I could hear granny's voice shouting, when Rhys was taking me down to the - he had to take me
 home. I was terrified.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How much do you know off by heart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh I could say - yes, I could say many many chapters. Many. And the fifth chapter of Matthew, the first one, Always, well I could recite that now, every word. And most of well - of cours
e after - after that you see I learnt the old - new testament through, recited it through, in Sunday school there, recited many - I recited that chapter many times, first chapter of John and - and - oh many of them, dear, yes I - Psalms, I learnt them - b
y
 heart. Yes. I remember that very well. But oh that was when I was going to Groes. But then that's in Groes, that's not in Penycae. I remember going there. We used to go down if there was a - anything important on. I don't know who was preaching there, bu
t I was - I was seven then. Yes, I was seven. And in Penycae then the - Sun - the singing school used to learn - a book like they used to do in dyffryn to learn a book in Dyffryn didn't they. And Joshua and all those, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}
}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}St Paul{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and all those - so however, the
y had learnt the book of Johan, in Penycae. And - whenever they'd learn a book I always had to do the reciting, it was coming in between you know. Yes. Parts of chapters, and I'd learnt the book of John and there's three or four - four chapters I think. I
 
think there are four. Three or four, I'm not quite sure now. And I'd learnt the book of Jonah of course ready for the concert. And then this was on the Sunday morning. I don't remember who the preacher was, I was told about it many times after that. And -
 
he said that - a little girl is going to start the meeting by reciting a chapter. The bennod he said you see, I didn't know it was one bennod, I thought - I didn't know there were many, I thought it was only one of course. Down I went, Rhys taking me down
,
 putting me to stand in - Groes in the front seat there. And I started. And I went through the book of Jonah. I went through, and - and some how I felt after I had said the first chapter - I felt - I wonder if something is wrong, but off I went, I gather 
a
fter and off I went. And I said it through. And then I was taken down, taken back to the seat. The seats were up there then in Groes, do you remember the seats up there, going up steps in Groes? No. Flat you see, it is. They used to go up to the window si
l
l. Yes, and they - and I remember one of the - and that's what he said, I don't remember who he was, I was told then, you think that child is taking the service. Plenty of welcome for me, he said. I heard that story many times. Well - well I didn't know y
ou see. I thought it was all one, and off I went.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You must have had a prodigious memory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, yes, yes, I was given a - memory, well there we are. And - Morgan has been very good in that way. Very good memory, yes. Oh well, well, well, I said that Jonah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I tell you - going to chapel and Sunday school and - and speaking the truth, oh that was of course, you were frightened to say anything - it was put into us you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. You wouldn't dare. Oh well, great burning fire if you swore. Yes, you went to the big burning fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they tell you that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh they came in - you will go to the great fire. Oh yes yo
u will go to the great fire if you say - no, no, no swearing, oh no. I never heard a swear word then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. Sit in the corner and be quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 If you did something that they disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - you would be scolded. And if it - the worst came to the worst you'd have a smack on your hand.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would smack you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - the mother or the father. No, my - the - mother. My sister, she would give a 
smack, but I don't remember my brother-in-law ever giving me a smack. No. But that's the way he used to do it was to bring a hymn or a - you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That upset you more probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes - it did, it went deeper you see, yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel about being punished? Do you remember any occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well it - oh well it used to be - it used to hurt me of course. It used to hurt me then - it used to - I don't know how it - how it would feel because - now by - w
hen - by the time I came to understand - that there was - there was a second somewhere, you see, you couldn't under - you couldn't explain it but there was a - a feeling you know that - you felt - doubly hurt somehow. It was a funny - it's a strange view,
 you can't be - you can't explain it at all. I was willing to take it. But if I - if I wasn't guilty well I wasn't willing. Yes. Oh yes indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both of them or did one play a more important part than the other?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Excuse me, I didn't catch you now. No. They were both very - very strict, oh yes. On - on behaviour. Oh yes. Yes, they'd both been brought up in that way you see. My - my mother - was very strict they said about behaving.
 And then - and granny twell yn y Ware after she was very strict, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, we'd have a birthday. Yes, my birthday was in the summer, I used to know naturally. I'd have some li
ttle thing on my birthday. Yes, you were - oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have a present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I'd have a little present of some sort you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Perhaps it'd be a little - different wee cake o
r something like that now. But there would be a difference. Yes, they would observe it, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would, you have any visitors to tea or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well - Christmas Day in Penycae was spent in chapel all day. Was a service in the morning. There was a service in the afternoon and there was a big concert in the night. And every - I think everyone in the chapel used to take part. It
 was a - of course we had a Christmas dinner, is true. And we would have our stocking, everyone of us would have our stocking filled. Oh yes. I remember having a little one little thing. A little - scissors, a little - sweet - made of sweets, a small scis
s
ors made of sweets, and it was a pretty little thing, I did like it very much, and an apple and an orange of course, but this little scissors - and - although I was only very small mind, it seemed to tell me that I was going to be a dressmaker. Now wasn't
 
that funny. Remember that little - thought coming to me now, that' little scissor, was I going to be a dressmaker, and a dressmaker I was. But I can see it now, little pink and white rose on it, oh - I was very young I know. Yes, oh yes, Christmas Day. Oh
 dear, it was a busy busy day. I was out there reciting and singing and I don't know what I was doing besides. And everybody else. Oh yes, used to - we had a way of bringing out all the children, he was wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well now a piano came there. When I was - seven - a piano came there. But before that - we had been down to my brother, my brother had gone to Bwlgh, he had gone from college - and he'd gone to Bwlgh, Breconshire. To - as a minister, and
 we went down there, I went down there for a month, and he had a little harmonium, and this harmonium was - oh I was - I aimed the ahrmonium very much, so after hearing my sister-in-law playing and she - she had a school there, she had a little private sc
hool, my sister-in-law, she was a schoolmistress in Taibach before she married my brother, John, Miss Jenkins she was, your mother would have remembered hoer of course And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You fancied this harmonium?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And this little harmonium I fancied so - I w
ent and put my hand there of course and to try and - and see if I could play on it you see, and upon my word I began to see - and do you know the first tune I played on it? Sandown - Lead Kindly Light. With one finger. On that little harmonium, oh I thoug
h
t it was wonderful. Then I wanted to play another one, and another one and - anything I could do with the one finger you know, get the - once I had the note I was right. So then - after we went home we had a piano. And of course - I was at the piano. I - 
well I don't know, it seemed to be in me somehow, I couldn't - I just couldn't help it you see. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who else played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And little Rhys - Rhys the next to me of course, Rhys was next to me and he - Rhys was a - made a brilliant musician too. 
He would. But however -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your sister or brother-in-law play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No, they didn't play because they had never - but - of course they knew whether we were right or wrong or whether we made a mistake, oh yes, quick to - so - began to play and then -
 there was a - a lady living in Pentyla, Miss Brew she was, so - we went there to her lessons to her. We went quarter - so much a quarter it was then you know and - and I remember we went, little Rhys and I went. And the first time we went down - 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Paws Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, they were building the first house next to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Bethany
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, where that shop is now. They were cutting the - because all the way down there to - to the Porth school you see, it was - fields, they hadn't started building anything - where we are now, it was all fie
lds. Wheat fields. And the boys used to go up on top of the - hedges and collect the wheat you see and - and the old farmer would see them and they had to go quick. But - there was - they were - cut down the hedge, and they were building. And that's where
 they were starting, and they had a big old lamp and I remember them starting that. And when we were coming home from Pentyla, used to go - wandering in and out these houses as they were building you know. Can remember that very well. Yes. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was there any of the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh they were all - we all could sing you see, yes. Yes, so I be - it was six months I had - little one like that, but - I got into the piano quick. Of course when 
I went back home there was no - no piano there. But I had learnt to play then you see, I could play - I could play what I wanted to. And the little pieces that - you learn you know and - but six months isn't much you see, twelve lessons - isn't much, but 
i
t was in me, I - I just - I missed it, I missed the piano more than anything. So there was - so - but I - I knew I could play, and then - on Sunday I used to go to chapel in Gores after that, that's how I began, so I became an organist once, by thinking I
 
had to go to Groes to tea, with Thomas Savon, Mrs George Llewellyn, instead of going all the way up home to the farm to tea, used to go there to tea every Sunday, and they had an harmonium, and I taught myself there, and they - I had to go in - I used to 
g
o in and shut the door, and sit down at the little harmonium, and it was there I learnt to play, and I started to play in chapel without any lessons. Yes. But I was very fond of - when I was in Penycae and of course little Rhys would play very well, and t
hen John came after you see. Yes. Oh well of course John - and John was the same, he took it in like I did you see, just drank it in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh In Penycae, oh we were always singing. Yes, we were always singing. Yes. Oh yes. It was always - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they ever play games with you, your father and mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember - I don't remember any games. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, they had books you see, the -
 yes, used to have Trysorfa Plant and all those - little books that come, the children you know. And the books we used to have for - prizes always, having books - prizes you know for something or other you see, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was there a newspaper in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I don't remember a newspaper. I don't think there was time for a newspaper. No. It was mostly music books that were there. My brother-in-law used to be - he was always learning some - oh he was always teaching us something you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was a busy life wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh very. Very. Very between the chapel and the household, yes. And the modulator on there, we had. We were and - and I was always learning chapters. \lquote Til I came to learn myself, and then I had to learn myself then. But oh 
I didn't mind. Learning a chapter wasn't - I used to enjoy it. I enjoy it now. Yes. Yes. Oh yes, I used to - when I was five and six - and seven I'd learn the chapters myself an I had to. It was nothing for me to hear him coming home and saying - well if 
the gamanfa was coming or - Cwrdd Mawr was coming, he'd come and tell me, you must learn this chapter now. Watch now. And I'd learn it, yes. I used to love learning. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not many children can read at that age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Oh well to learn them then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It would be all Welsh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 All Welsh you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Or would you be reading English as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I was reading - I was very good in reading English you know - in school. I remember the old Fore school. You came in here and then you went up - flights y
ou know, sitting down on those flights of steps. It's a funny old place. Sitting there. And - oh and - and I had a good memory then you see, I used to learn the - poetry and things like that, and I was always brought out to - to recite of course. And I re
m
ember - oh funny now, talking about - that, I remember the first - when the modulators came out, a modulator came to Groes to - Port school, and Miss Gwenny Jenkins, she was - she was in Saron Benicar, she was in this Sunday - in the - in the of course, a
n
d they brought a modulator to the school. And these charts they used to have you know. And I remember one day they had a - teaching them children to sing, and - Miss Jenkins, I think it was Miss Jenkins, not Miss Winter, Miss Jenkins or Miss Winter, remem
b
er Miss Winter from Taibach? Remember the Winters? She was there. And I had to come down - down those steps and point the modulator - for the children to sing. I was only about that size. It was a part of me you see. I didn't mind it a bit. No. But I can 
remember it now, I can see it now, those old steps. Sitting on them all day. Things are very very different now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There were no desks or chairs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was a big desk down there you see, and - and a - there was a - I don't know what fo
r - whether this was the first - from or no. It was one of the little forms at ever - I don't remember where the others were over there, but I can see this now. Those steps going up as if you were going up the steps of the - House of Commons. Long steps. 
First there would be about twenty children sitting on each one. Yes. And their - feet are behind you. Remember that very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Reading{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
? Oh yes, they - reading was - a part of the - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh no - I don't think they would. No, not unless it was something very - or perhaps if she'd be dewing and he'd be reading and - something to her you know. Yes. Otherwise they would -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. One. One funeral. The - there was Rhys, there was Rhys and Maggie, and then this little girl Lizzie. 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Elizabeth{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. She died when she was - two and a half. She was a very beautiful child, very beautiful, and that was the - t
he big - well a big cloud, knocked them down, oh I can remember that very well. And that was the first time I saw Doctor Davis, old Doctor Davis, Taibach, I remember him coming into the house. And that was - that was only about - six weeks I think - befor
e
 Nellie Maud was born. Yes. And my sister was very poorly in health I remember. But I can remember the day of that funeral. And it was then I think I had had this black velvet frock. I've seen a picture of myself in that, since then. With one of the girls
,
 I'd like to get hold of her again but she's very old, she's older than me I think, don't know whether she's alive, but in years after I saw the picture, and lace here you know and lace there, and a cloak across here. Sitting on these steps, of that schoo
l. They took the photograph.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You had mourning clothes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And everybody - oh yes, everybody was in deep black for a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 For the baby, after a baby died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, everybody in black. Yes. Yes, I remember her very well. I remember Do
ctor Davis coming. And an aunt of my - my mother's only sister, my mother now, that's her only sister - from the farm, and then - and - I don't know, you may know the - son of the family, Elizabeth Ellen has gone out to America, the Ress's, they used to l
ive in Club Row, now to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What was it like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well all I can remember is you see about them - because of course it was all in this one room, it was full of people of course. Full of people. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did they keep the coffin then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well it was in the kitchen. In the same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In this one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
In that one room. Coffin was there - covered over with a shawl. Yes. And then - and the flowers I can remember them - putting flowers, I remember that very well. And - muslin 
over her face. Oh she was - oh she was very pretty, and she had long ringlets you know. That's what I remember about her. She was a beauty I suppose. And especially children. If a child had died all the children of the place would come. Oh yes. Oh yes. Ye
s
. And I remember the afternoon the funeral and me sitting down - on that stone step, that was my perch always, I was sitting there, Rhys and I - very well and little Lizzie we called her - going out, I can remember that very well. Very well. That was the 
-
 and that was the funeral. Oh when we were children, if there'd be any child that we knew, you know. Yes, yes. Oh it was the thing you see, it was the thing then. Yes. And it was the thing to go and see - as people go and see them now, to - sympathise wit
h
 them don't they. Well we do now, but - they used to go then. Well just to say well - have a last look you see. See her for the last time, they used to say then you see. And one old lady told me - that - I - I've forgot - well I've heard it from several t
o
o, that - of course if there was a new baby the baby would be - would be christened - on its mother's coffin. They used to put the christening basin on the mother's coffin. And they told me - but not one of the family, not one of our - one of our family. 
A
nd yet I have an idea - that one of my sister's told me too. My eldest sister did and I don't know whether the other one did or no, but I remember an old lady telling me - what a sight it was. To see me - christened - on my mother's coffin. That the - the
 
basin on the coffin and they christened me on the coffin, and of course they had long gowns, and I had black tie ups. I can remember that old lady telling me that. Oh until - old Aunt Eliza Groes. Old Aunt Eliza Llewellyn. It was the custom. Of course I r
emember babies, I always had tie ups on the babies - baby's gown a - a bow of ribbon or - each side there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That was the custom to christen the baby if the mother had died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And they used to christen the baby - if the mother had died then, when th
e baby was small, to - to christen the baby on the - it was done you see. So probably they did the same to me you see. Yes. So I don't know - but - I was told that, yes, and that they said - that everybody felt it - so much and to see me, says - so tiny, 
I suppose I was a very tiny baby they were afraid to handle me. I was very very small I heard my father saying that. But - so that was - it was the custom you see and they - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 probability}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  is that they - they did the same to me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you taken out visiting neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh no. No. No. I don't remember - my - my sister - she - anybody in trouble she'd go. Or anybody - anybody had a baby or anybody in trouble wanted a - little bit of something, oh she would go. Yes, but never any other time. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Sometimes. But I used to do the shopping when I was very young. Very - young. I knew exactly - I was told what to do and what to g
et and - of course she couldn't go and leave the children you see, I had to go. Shopping many time - there wasn't many shops in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose}
 then. There was only a - there was only shop Nicholas and - and the tailors, and Weoods. Only three or four shops in - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose} then you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Out with my father? No, I don't think so. No, we used to go out - all together. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember any outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I remem - the
 only outings we had was Sunday school outings you see. And the outings as I used to have would go from - Penycae up to Margam. Those were my outings. Up to the old home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How often would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh we'd go - two or three times a year. And -
 the baby would be in the - we used to have a - she used to have a pram you know, carriage, whicker carriages then, maybe one walking and one or two on the pram, in this carriage, and we used to go up from - walk all the way of course, and go up from Port
 
Talbot, calling Twell yn y Ware with granny first. And then we'd go - after having bread and butter or whatever would be there, bread and jam or - a biscuit or something, and then we'd go up to - up past Brombil. Brombil Farm. And I was afraid in my heart
 of the dogs at Brombil Farm. Or any - or the turkeys, I was terrified of the turkeys. And then we'd go to the - little - that little house at the bottom of the wood. You know, the first house there, and - she used to leave the pram there. \lquote 
Cos - and then up through the woods up home. Walk up through the wood. She'd carry the baby. And then get to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You couldn't take the pram right up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Not further. And then leave the pram there. That was our outing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you go back the same day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 O
h yes. Yes. I remember the day - remember when my father died, we went up on a Saturday afternoon. And I had - Gwynn, Gwynn was a small baby then, I had him in this - little pram. That's how I used to take the children up. From 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose} all the way. And
 - I remember going up - and my father had been taken ill and I didn't know. And I met one of my cousins by Brombill gate, from the house, and he said, did you know your father was ill. I said, no I didn't. Well he is - very ill. Oh dear. I couldn't get u
p
 quick enough, dragging the children up through the wood, and - of course he was in bed. He'd been taken ill the day before. He'd fallen outside in the yard. And he was in bed. In the four poster. Four poster we had you see, with curtains all round. Littl
e
 white ones inside, I had made them. I'd made little lace curtains inside, and then the old - the out - the old brown ones outside, they were brown, sort of alpaca stuff. It was very - it was two - they were two hundred years old whatever, and they were e
d
ged with reds. Have a think now. But I didn't care for them - to sleep under, so I had put - lace curtains for my father right around the bed. And he was like a king there of course then. But however he was ill. He was very ill. Oh dear dear dear. Well I 
t
hought I - and I couldn't stay because the baby was only - May, June, July, August, he was only four months old. I had to go take the baby back that night, and - well I was asking him, oh you're going to get better. You are going to get better. Well, my d
e
ar, you have kept your father a long time. And here he was eighty six you see. You have kept your father a long time my dear. You must be willing Annie. Those were the words he said to me. You must be willing. Oh dear dear, I was breaking - broken hearted
.
 Well I went home. I took the baby home and - took the - and the others, and then daddy came home from work. Because he had to work on that night and I was on my own. So he took the children and looked after them, I put everything, put the baby right, and
 
I - my brother Dan's little girl Margaret came back with me. I can remember, I can see the cornfields now. We put everything right for the night. And I started to walk back. Because I knew he wasn't going to be long. And - she was - this little girl was w
i
th me, she was - about eleven I think, Margaret was about eleven I think, back we went, and it was moonlight. We were starting from our house at half past twelve. And I got home between half past one and two. And I can see the corn now - and the - and the
 moon shining on it you know, and both of us going through the corn. And - but I didn't - he didn't talk to me after, he died next day. Yes. Oh I shall never forget.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 People had to walk then everywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Walk, all those miles. And that - through that place now. Right through that wood, the Margam wood, \lquote 
cos every tree was there then. Only of course I knew every stump of a tree. Of old, and going up through the - through the fields, I can see them now. And he died that night, yes. Wonderful man. Won
derful, and he never married. Brought up the nine without - and people are telling him that - why didn't he marry again because we had a good housekeeper, a lady from Margam. Oh no, no, no, no. He couldn't put my mother's memory off like that. He was wond
erful, yes. But I remember him saying, you must be willing Annie fach he said. Yes. Yes, he was - wonderful. Yes, that was Margam then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember what you would do on a Bank Holiday in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When I - when we were in Penycae? Well now 
then a Bank Holiday - there wasn't so much - done on Bank Holidays then. Whit Monday was our day and the day of the trip. But the Whit Monday, oh the Sunday school would turn out and the banner and - and another - turn out we used to have - was a temperan
c
e turn out, which we don't hear of now. The temperance. We used to go - we would turn out, which we don't hear of now. The temperance. We used to go - we would turn out, march out, yes, and Band of Hope we marched, and all the bands of Hopes - would be to
gether in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose}, and a big blue banner, and sing temperance boys and girls are we, I've taught it to hundreds of children since then. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd march from the town would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 March through the town. Yes. Yes. Because in temperance was very - bad in - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot
{\*\xmlclose} then. And they - yes, and then it came after a - a kind of a wave - good - great people came down you know and they had a big - they had meetings in the in the hall, in the - what did they used to call that old hall now by - by the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Vints?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. No, not - no, that hadn't come then. No. It was the old Town Hall down near {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Water Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, you know, those steps - wonderful people been speaking there. And {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Bethany{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} vestry they used to come to. And then they used to - and all the Bands of Hope, it was for the best then, blue ribbon, wear blue ribbon. Blue ribbon badges, oh - wonderful. And indeed it caught hold and - temperance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was a lot of intemperance was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was, before that, because people were 
- there you are, there was nothing to drink but beer all the time see. But - then we - oh it came different then. Churches took it up and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Let me see now. I remember going - yes - yes, down to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Carmarthen{\*\xmlclose}
, to my father's old home. I remember going down there. And the holiday that when I went to Bwlch to my brother you know when he went to - but I remember going down to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long would you go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Carmarthen{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh about a week you see, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was it only once that you went or did you go regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Ah no, we didn't go regular, oh no, couldn't afford it you see. No, she couldn't afford it but we went I remember us going then, and going around to the - to the different -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh my sister and - and - brother-in-law taking us down, and fetching us back you see. But we had to go - by train then you see. Costing money of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you do when you were down there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well there you are, wander around the farms and go - and see the different - relatives you see. But - I didn't go - very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And when you went to Bwlch, who went with you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh the - we - they all went then probably you see, yes. Yes, and Nellie Maud was a baby. She wa
s very very very delicate. And not much wonder because - you see - yes, yes, yes, yes. And she wasn't well you see. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go for a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh about a week we went, and went to my - went to a cousin or a - oh to Bwlch, to my brother there ye
s. And - Mary had a - she had a little private school there you see. Yes, he was the minister and - she had a private school. Yes. At the top of the houses I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You liked going there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I did, I enjoyed that. I enjoyed that very much. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you spend Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well - Saturday was a cleaning day. Oh yes. It was a big day for cleaning for Sunday. Everything had to be done for Sunday. And I must say I can't help it now. I don't be - live in any work on S
unday now. I get my vegetables all ready on Saturday night, exactly as I used to. Exactly the same, everything had to be ready for Sunday. And not a sound, oh I can remember now - when we went over - and I was at home and I was quite grown up, my father w
ouldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 allowed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
 the boys to - whistle to the dogs or shout - out on the farm, no. He wouldn't. Wouldn't allow any noise. That's the sort of farmer he was. Mmm. No, Sunday was Sunday then. It was a holy day then. And Penycae was - it was quiet. I can remembe
r now - Sunday morning in Penycae. Going out to the house now. And not a sound - but the church - Aberafon church bell would be going, and the river. The {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Avon{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}River{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. You could hear that every Sunday morning, the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Avon{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
PlaceType}}River{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, going down you know, a lovely sound of it. And then - the - church bell would go. That's the one thing that remains in my mind on Sunday. Quite fresh. Yes. Dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How would you spend Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well of course we used to go to chapel. And Sunday school. When we were too small to go
 to chapel of course we all went to Sunday school, everybody went to Sunday school. Depended on how the babies were if - after the baby was old enough to be left - my sister used to go then and leave the baby with me. Children would be with me and we'd be
 
playing school and playing chapel and goodness knows what in the house. That's how I was with our children, playing chapels and anything. Margaret was playing the piano on the chair and Morgan was standing up on top of the chair preaching. Oh dear dear. O
h indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have different clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes. Oh yes, Oh yes, Sunday - Sunday clothes, Sunday shoes, Sunday stockings. Everything. They were only worn on Sunday. Yes, there was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well - they thought it was wrong to work on Sunday. The only work that was bound to be done I remember now - my - my brother-in-law sometimes he'd ha
ve to make a coffin you know, or it would have to be finished on Sunday, or someone would have died, that was the only work. And I - I remember my father - on the farm - the farmers around now - he - when the weather would go bad and they'd be afraid the 
r
ain was coming, and all the crops waiting to go in you know, and I can remember us coming home from chapel, Sunday night, and supper. Off you go to bed. And when the clock would strike twelve he'd call us. And down we had to come, and breakfast and out to
 
the fields. And I've seen it half past six on a Monday morning, and the last load coming in and the rain coming. And he would have it in. But he wouldn't touch it on Sunday. The other farmers would do - work on Sunday, but father wouldn't. And the the old
 clock would strike twelve down at the foot of the stairs. Down they'd come. And the the old clock would striking. Dear, dear, dear, dear. YES? THAT type of men. Finished now. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Welsh Presbyterian wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, Welsh Presbyterian.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How often would they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh they'd go - all day Sunday you see. Yes. They would go to - morning and night meetings and the 
children go to - oh but my father was a Sunday school teacher for years. Yes. Used to go - three times. Yes. And Monday night and Wednesday night. In the weeknights. Yes. Of course it was a rule of life then you see. Religion played a vital part in our li
fe then. An important part. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, I've been a Sunday school teacher for seventy-two years. Yes. And I'm still a superintendant in the vestry there. Oh dear, but I must - shall have to give it in now, it's getting a bit - much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go on any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. Oh yes, we used to go to Porthcawl you see. Oh yes, they used to go to Porthcawl - in the - in the - wagons you see, the same as we used to go in Groes in wagons. Yes. And down to th
e beach. And to Mumbles, Mumbles was a - favourite place then too. Yes. Yes, I can remember going - when I was small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What other social activities were organised by the chapel that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well there was nothing else except the concert
s you see, the different concerts, especially Christmas, Christmas Day all day, and - and then there were the - there was the choir, the concern of course, a big concert they used to have - used to have important people to sing. But - those were the thing
s you used to look - forward to you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You belonged to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Oh yes. And with the children of course. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And you said earlier that they ran a temperance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh the temperance. The temperance band was a - oh yes, that was a - that was a wonderful, and - grown ups and children in that. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You used to go did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did they used to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well, they used to have temperance meetings you see and - and sign the pledge, everybody signed
 the pledge. And then they used to have turn out - and maruch through the streets. Yes. Singing temperance songs and - used to have big people to speak you see in the hall. Yes. Oh they did a lot toward bringing temperance back then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you belong to any other club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, there was nothing else you see, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, oh the children, we've always said grace. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And family pra
yers after. Family prayers, well we still keep that up - even thought daddy are only - together, we still keep the family prayers. Yes, and when the children - Morgan comes over - Morgan - and I well love he says to come here, and she loves to have family
 prayers when they're here, and we are there. Yes. Oh yes always we've kept that going. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would say grace in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh the children would all say grace together you see, yes. Say grace for every meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh no. Well only what was - going on you know, because - specially when - if there'd be an election now and - and the Liberals were very strong. Of course all chapel people and church people are Liberals. And old Mr Talbot was a - h
e was a - a father in the House of Commons, he was a great Liberal. Oh yes. That - my first - the first thing I ever heard about politics was Liberal. Yes. It's gone from my mind }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 one thing}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  now. As you say now there was an election - something big coming on
, and there were delegates sent from each church. To this big meeting to the Park Hall Cardiff. And we both were selected, we weren't married then. We both were selected. And oh wait a minute, there was somebody else too that came, one of the deacons. Cam
e
 to this meeting, to Park Hall to hear Lloyd George. Was it - was it - no, it was in Swansea, that's right, because Lord Glantower, Lord Glantower was - welcoming us when we went in, I remember it very well and some man too, but - we went up on a - a gall
e
ry, all these delegates, and Lloyd George was speaking down there. And somebody shouted to him, you're speaking in Welsh, and somebody shouted to him to give - more English, and he said that - that sick didn't want it - it was the sick people wanted a doc
t
or, not people that didn't want any - the people didn't want a physician, they - they didn't need the doctor he said. Some - something after that kind but - he soon put a stop to that. But however this is what I was going to say. We came down then when we
 
were going there was - refreshments and all, and when we were going we went - we were going to the anti room now to get our clothes, and - who was standing in the doors - shaking hands with us but Lloyd George himself. That was the only time - that I ever
 met him, face to face. And he shook hands with both of us. Yes, and he said, I'm glad to see young people here. But - the - one thing we did here there was the - the suffragettes had tied themselves to seats behind us, we were awfully }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 frightened}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 . They tied
 themselves. Tied themselves to the seats and shouted. They wouldn't let him go on you see. Yes. And - the suffragettes - we didn't know what they were then. Dear, there was an awful row there, and the policeman had to go and carry them and carried one wo
man bodily out and she was kicking and - I remember very well. Yes she was - boots she had on, kicking away, and he was carrying her out and they were shouting. Oh, screaming, oh dear, yes, I remember that's the only time I saw suffragettes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They were fighting for the vote then weren't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
They were fighting for the vote then you see. And the only time I saw - Lloyd George was he shook hands with me. But after that I little thought - that I would be helping his daughter to undress in the Gorsed
d. The last time I saw her, Megan, she was coming, she was late, her car had broken down, and she was late coming, and we had - and we were starting, and for some reason or other - I was one of the last going out, I was dressed. And she came in with her c
ase and - she asked me if I'd help her to dress. And I helped her to dress. Yes. Megan Lloyd George. And that's the last time I saw - the only time I spoke to her. She was very very nice, and she was so grateful, \lquote 
cos I helped her because the - the - procession had started you see. Yes. So that's how I met Lloyd George and Megan. Yes, so it was a - I was very glad of that. Yes, it was rather an un - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Very popular character in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} then wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, he was, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So your father was a Liberal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why do you think he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't know - it was the general view I think of all - of all workmen, of all farmers then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about your mother, what would she be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh w
ell - of course I don't know, there wasn't much politics then, not at that time. No. But as the - I think the first - I think they always were Liberals ever since there was a - I'm sure no one in Margan had ever been anything else. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember your father or mother voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Of course you yourselves would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, yes, yes. We'd be voting then probably. I don't remember much about -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You don't remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No I don't. No. Don't
 remember much about - we hadn't taken - any interest in - politics, and - and I've never been keen on one of the children taking interest. No. You can't do everything you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 mm. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you think your father felt any pressure like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No. No. No, that wasn't done there, it was done in some places I know. Some people had to suffer because they -
 because they - voted according to their convictions but - no, there was nothing of that in Margam. No. Nor in Penycae. No. I don't remember much about - about anything like that - yes. Yes, and I don't remember - much talking about voting. In Penycae at 
all. Well there you are it's - between - eighty and ninety years ago, it's going back a long time you see. Mm. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Before 1919 you'd have been married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - yes. Yes, and there was no votes for - young people then at all you see. You had to b
e married before you could - vote then you see. See since then this - votes under }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 twenty one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
 came. Whether they're wise or no I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was your father a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  working for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, never, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I don't know - what time they had beside doing their daily work they did in the church. It was all church work every night. Yes. They had no other activities, nothing else. Only the church - well their - the home - was around it or the church was a
round the home. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Your sister it was really wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did she have any interest outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, it was all in the - the home and the church. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. No more than I did. There was never time. Oh dear, dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I tell you it all depended - oh dear, well - oh - now my brother-in-law you mean. Well he used to - well he'd finish at six yo
u see. Finish at six and - unless there was - something special such as a coffin or something like that to be done. Then he'd have to work on. Otherwise six o'clock. From six in the morning \lquote til six in the night. Those were the hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well he'd spend them all except when he was in - doing the chapel work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did - our mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh dear me no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he bet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh dear no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 A boot club, or a sick, club or a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, no. No. I don't think - oh I'm sure they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Very well. Very well with them all. Oh the little ones, oh well, all right with the little ones of course and with my other - brother and sister, they've always got on well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No, I don't think - I don't think so. No. I had more to do with her and - then there was my brother Margam one of the ministers, he was a poet and we had a lot 
in common, we both, we'd a lot in common there. Oh and my sisters went to America. Of course were home for years together, in the old home. No, there was - oh I don't know, they were all - all the same, yes. No, we never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well I - didn't do much - didn't go outside, we - never went out to play because there was enough children in the house to play with. No, and you couldn't go out on the road in Penycae to play you know. It wasn't safe. No, I don't remember g
oing out much to play. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What a games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I know the only games we had in school was skipping and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You said earlier that you used to play school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh and play school - play school and a chapel oh yes. Oh I wou
ld of course with the children, there you are, play the - with the - well with my children now, of course that's a different thing. That's a different thing of course. Because then the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 organ}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  and the violin and all came into practice then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well, there was nothing there, only - oh well I had to - we had toys you know. Yes. As many of the three children that were there with me. Yes. And we were never left long alone. Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you go out to play at all there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - no, we were not - it wasn't very safe to go and get dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, there was nobody - I don't think there was anybody about there that was - would be any - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I don't think - we didn't think - we didn't - play with any children, only the children in the school and the chapel you kno
w they were - they were the children we met every day and every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you spend your free time when you are at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Your free time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh, free time, oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you keep any pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Or do gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You did mention earlier that you were minding the baby?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I was - that was my pet - that was what I had to do in mind the baby, look after the little ones. Yes. Oh mind the baby was my - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You must have spent a lot of time learning the verses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And of course I had - I always had a chapter of something to learn. Or a recitation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That was your hobby really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Those were my hobbies you see, oh yes. Learning. I was always learning something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Didn't you say you learnt all the psalms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, well I learnt most of the psalms, but I learnt - I - I learnt nearly all the New Testament
. And it - recited them off by heart. Mostly. There is one little book, I was taken ill - and I left Philemon out. And when I had the gold medal, the Gee Medal you know - the - the secretary of the eistedfodd asked me well what - why didn't you learn - wh
y
 didn't you learnt - why didn't you learn that book then he said, what had that poor man done. Well I don't know I said. I think I - I slipped him by. Well perhaps he'd come back again he said. Oh dear, dear. And nearly all - nearly finished the - Revelat
ion. I'd gone into the Revelation, I'd learnt some of it. But the others, Matthew, Mark, Luke and John, Acts, Hebrews, Romans, Thessolonains, Colussions, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Galatia
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, all of them. I learnt them all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That was your hobby really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, learning w
as my - learning was my hobby and - if I'd had a piano when I was home you see I'd have - I think I'd have spent all my time, I was very fond of singing, music. Music has been my ruling - has been my ruling power when I was young, and - and reciting, and 
even then - when I was very young I used to compose verses. Yes. When I was very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So that was a hobby with you really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, I used to compose verses then. Yes. And I was very fond of reading about the the Foreign Mission. The Foreign Missio
n, oh I used to love to read about the - and we had a very good teacher but that of course that belongs to Groes you see because - that was the time when they began with the Foreign Mission. Yes. Oh yes. But I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you still in school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I 
was in Groes school you see. Yes. Well my - those are my hobbies. Yes. And I was a country girl, I was fond of - I was fond of climbing trees and - and looking for birds and - and - wild flowers and things like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you collect wild flowers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh dear, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 A lot of girls used to press them didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. Yes, I used to - oh I - I had first prize in Margam flower show for - wild - wild flowers. I gathered them on my father's fields, on the moors you see. Oh, they were lovely c
hoice flowers down there you know. Yes, I used to know all the flowers. And the birds, oh I used to spend hours and hours in the woods. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So you would do a lot of walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Spend hours in the woods.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. I didn't go fishing. No I didn't bother with fishing at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would you go out with now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 On my own and the dog. When I was home you see, yes. Had Prince with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You wouldn't go with anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you go bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No, I didn't have a bicycle, I only went on the pony. I was a good bit older when I started going on the pony, I - suppose my father was very - he was very careful about me going on the pony you know. Oh no, on my own, no, it wouldn't do. I wa
s fond of the old pony, very fond of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How old would you be when you'd start going on the pony?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I was on about sixteen, seventeen, eighteen, that way you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That's after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember that I ever went to the theatre. And oh I was on -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well we had our concerts you see and we had our - school concerts and we used to have - have them up in 
the Castle and - yes, oh used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 A lot of concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, and I was always - taking chief part in the concerts. Dressed, and they used to send away to London for the clothes. Oh I used to enjoy that. And to the - and to the - church concert 
of course. I wasn't supposed to go then - the church choir, but I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Though you were chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Although I was chapel. And in - and in fear of being broken out of the chapel too. I remember my brother telling us go you. I'm going to the - to the
 - to the dance, the annual ball you know. I was singing with the choir you see. Going, my sister and going. And my brother telling us, Margan, the minister you know, go you, you will be broken out of the Seit. He didn't though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was he serious do you think or was he joking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't know. He didn't do it whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they though in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh they would. Oh yes. Oh - they were - there was that antagonistic feeling between the church and the chapel. So - I don't know. But they wer
e. The chapel people if anything mind I don't say - they had their good points, but they could be too narrow, and then that would too - that would do more harm than good, and it did more harm than good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why would they break people out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well of c
ourse you were not supposed to go to a dance. No. Not supposed to go to a dance. No, I used to love them. Used to go - and say I was singing in the choir of course and I was singing. Used to enjoy going of course. And go home after and in fear and trembli
ng next Sunday of being -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did they do if they did break people out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh my dear of course if you're a member you see you're broken out, your - your name was - yes. Your name was deleted from the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Can you remember anybody being broken out like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Let me see now. I don't remember anybody in Groes. No. I don't. I have been told of people you know and - but it was a - a fear and trembling for everyone to think of that you see. Yes, no I don't remember anybody. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go to music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 Cinema}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 , there were no cinemas then were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
'Cos you - if you went - I remember my sister - my elder sister, they went to a circus, she and - one of the - and one of the - the head, he was the head deacon I think. The
y were two - both of them, they went to see a circus. And they were put before the Seit. Ah they were. But they had to promise they'd never go again. Shouldn't go to the circus, shouldn't go to the Eisteddfodd. It was a sin to go to the Eisteddfod then. Y
es. Sin to go to Eisteddfod. Or to the circus. Or to the show. To any show, except a flower show.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The people went in fear more than anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well they were - they were - you see you - it was - too puritanical you see. Too - it was going too far.
 But it went I remember that. And if you were - going with a young man and a - and you walked with that young man on Sunday night - goodbye. And there was an old - and we had an old - deacon with us you see, and - him and his wife are going together. She 
w
as a - she - was - really did have some people from Tiabach. And he was one of the - one of the Margam, and they used to meet on Sunday nights, and they used to walk on each side of the road. One each side of the road. Now then. Yes, quite true. I can rem
ember an old lady from our - from Groes telling me - that she had met them. Ann was one side and Philip at the other side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they shout across or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't know what they were saying to one another. I remember that, oh we used to have a bit of fun about that. Dear, dear, dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well what pocket money I had was given by them you see. But I didn't have - I wouldn't have anything. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How much would they give you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - ther
e wasn't much - pocket money then. Children didn't go out to buy then. No I don't remember anything like that. Only when we'd go away somewhere and - we'd have a sixpence or something like that you see. But I don't remember much. No, it wasn't a - no, it 
wasn't the rule then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No, the only time I would see somebody come in there would be a midwife. Yes. I wouldn't see anybody coming there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did she manage if she was ill, or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes, well there you are. Oh well of course my brother-in-law was there then. Yes. And my sister used to come, my other sister used to come, from Margam then. Yes. Yes, she used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember when one of the younger ones was born? Do you remember what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well my sister's younger ones, well I don't remember much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You can't remember Nellie Maud being born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Nellie Maud, I can remember the time she was born, I know she w
as very ill, my sister came up then, my sister Catherine. And - but I know she was very ill. She was very very delicate. That's all I remember about her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You don't really remember one of the children being born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, no. Oh no, I was too young then, I only knew one - the only thing I would know if there was a new baby there. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Your sister came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mm. Oh - I knew she had come and that was all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your sister-and-brother-in-law have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No - no
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They didn't have any in Penycae did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Margam was the nearest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Margam was the nearest, yes. Both of them. Oh no, there was nobody -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 That}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  was about two miles away wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, three. Mm. From {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose}. Oh, three miles from 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose}, something like that, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How much did they see of the relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, we used to go up home most every - yes, and we used to go to Twell yn y Wale to see granny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How often would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well perhaps two or three times a year. Yes. It was a long way to walk, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they ever come up to see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, if there was something the matter they'd - but my father used to come from the farm very often, 'cos he used to bring things you see, yes, and - meat and eggs and butter and milk and all that sort of thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So you'd see him fairly often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, he used to come up or one of the girls. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Everybody was friendly up there. Dear me yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where would they see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well, when the - mostly - in the church work you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well they were friend - who was friendly with him were friendly with her. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would your sister have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. Not outside, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about your brother-in-law, would he have his own friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Not apart from her, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well if they happened to come, everybody would be welcome. Anybody that would come would be welcome you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - there was always a cup of tea, oh that was the - that went without saying. Yes. Always a cup of tea for everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they come on any particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I don't remember - there was anything like that then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you say that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or your father's friends or friends of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, I don't remember - there wasn't much of that done then you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would people call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Unless there was something the matter. If there was sickness or something like that it would be - it was different. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would neighbours call in often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. The only friends that - the only people that used to call was the - children shouting Happy New Year. On the New Year's morning. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, not unless they had - unless they had business, there was somebody ill or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 People often tell us that in those days they made their own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 amusement}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 , what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well yes. Oh I don't know. The only time they used to get together was to sing. Yes. That was the only time they got together. Nothing else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups
, in the time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh I don't know, I don't - didn't have much to do with that way. 1918, no. No, I don't - this class - affair never came into my life. All - everybody's been the same to me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What class would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I don't know my dear. What class would I belong to? What they say is the upper class and a lower class or - or a medium class or what? I don't see that I belong to any particular class myself. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What sort of people belonged to the same group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well they all - educated people, they're all educated people of course. Everybody is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What sort of people belonged to the other groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well 
- well I don't know, well - we don't - go to - we don't go to dances and - and games and things like that, we don't - because we've got no time for that. No, and never done anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. No, never - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you ever told to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh I used to curtsey always when I was a child. Used to curtsey to the Minister and to the Doctor, to the - schoolmistress. Yes, always. And 
- then - the first woman I saw curtseying - was - excuse me talking about the little one's funeral, little baby's funeral, and my aunt was there, mother's sister, Auntie Nell, I was telling you about her, and she was the first - and when - and Doctor Davi
s
 came in and she was the first woman I saw curtseying, this - old lady, curtseying to the Doctor. Of course I always - we were always taught to you see. Curtsey to the Doctor and to the - and our Minister. The Minister and Elder to me were - well - and th
e school - schoolmistress, always curtseying. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was there anyone you called sir or madam or master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Sir - to the Doctor always. I don't remember - and sir to the schoolmaster or - of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember anyone showing re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 spect to your parents in these s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 ort of ways? Like touching their cap to them or curtseying or anything like that, or calling them sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well they used to then you see. Well - especially now if we've had a - if there was any servant men coming to work on t
he farm or something, they'd say sir to my father now and again, mat - matter of courtesy that was know and - men working on the farms, they'd say yes sir or - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In the district then who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well now then in - in - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose}
 you mean now. Well now Mr Byers - was the big man then of course, Mr Byers. And the Doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why was Mr Byers considered a big man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh Mr Byers was the big man in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose}
. I remember the night Mr Byers - got married
. He was bringing his bride home. And it was in - I know it was in the winter, 'cos it was dark. And of course there was a long row of houses in Penycae then, there was no street lights or anything. And every house in Penycae - could see them from the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Forge Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, you look up to Penycae from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Forge Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} you know, you would know what I mean. Every house had a candle - in the - in the upstairs window and in the bottom window, and every house in Penycae was a - a row of lights, candles, welcoming Mr - Byers and 
his wife. Remember that now. And everyone watching when they were coming up, and they had a carriage of course and - and a big one. I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why was he considered a big noise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well he had the works, he owned them. You see.. Mr Byers owned the works, yes. Yes, of course they had to - welcome them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The doctor you thought as well did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, yes, the doctor, Doctor Davis, Doctor Jones. Doctor Arnold Jones. Tall man, with a black silk hat. Wonderful man. We were afraid of all those people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I don't know, and - not afraid, but we had that - respect. The respect you see. The respectful fear. Not that we were afraid of them. That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Anyone else did you think was important then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't reme
mber that there was anybody else in Port Talbot at that time. Of course in Margam there was a - the Castle people you see and - and the - and the vicar and - all the rest of it. But in Port Talbot I don't think there was anybody else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you come into contact with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Noto with Mr Byers. Oh no. With Doctor Davis and Doctor Jones of course they used to come to my sister's you see. But - not to Mr Byers. Nor anyone else like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - there we
re so many shopkeepers you see. Charles Jones, Woods, Nicholas, the grocer. Evans the chemist. We knew them all. Thomas Jones the Book as we used to call him, Thomas Jones the bookbinder, everyone knew - 'cos they were related to my mother. They were - re
lated to the old family you see. And we - we shouldn't buy a book anywhere. Except at Thomas Jones. We shouldn't buy furniture except at Johnnie Jenkins, the furniture. Because they were related. All the relations had to be considered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would the shopkeepers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well I don't know, they were - I can't say who they were - there wasn't many of them you see and they used to go to the - I don't know whether any of them went to - went to chapel, most of them went to church I think. If 
they went anywhere. Yes. Of course the - people at the works were the big people then you know. We didn't have - Mr Bray and - and Mr Gray after - Mr Bray of course was a big man with the Nesley. Yes. And Edward Davis after a little bit, in Taibach. And y
ou knew Edward Davis of course. Yes, yes. That family and Miss Davis of course played the organ in - she was the first organist - in Dyfrryn, remember the organ. Yes, yes, yes. he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 Who did the cl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 ergy associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well the - oh - I don't think they - who was there, who was the clergyman, of course I remember building St Theodores.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There wasn't St Agnes then was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No St Agnes. I don't remember about the vicars in here. But I remember them building - St Theodores, because I too
k many a meal to my father there. My father and two brothers, they used to bring the stones from the quarry, from Margam. That's what it's built St Theodore. I was telling Eric Roberts one day - I've got more to do with that - place than you have I said '
Cos I helped to build it. I used to take their - lunch to them every day, over to St Theodore when they were building it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were living in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Tany Groes Street{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I was living home in Margam. All the way, walk all the way from Margam 
with my basket - with their - their lunch every day. For weeks I did it. When the weather would be - it all depended where they were - what they was having to do that day, but if it was the day when they were taking - the stones from the quarry - or fetch
i
ng something from - the other side, from the - station or something like that, and they wouldn't be coming home with the horses, I'd have to bring - bring their - their lunch for them in a basket, yes, I - I brought many - yes. I've got a - I've got a cou
ple of hands in that St Theodores. I like old St Theodores, I saw it going up. Yes. Yes. I saw it going up. But I don't remember anything about St Agnes. Because St Agnes was built after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about teachers then? Who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I - 
don't know, they - oh each one well - most of the teachers then - were locals you see and they went to the - churches where they'd been brought up, most of them. Of course - my sister-in-law, my brother's - wife, she was headmistress in the infants there,
 for a few years, Miss Jenkins. She was from Dowlas. But - I do -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the teachers in the Fore school where you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well now then - there was Miss Gwennie Jenkins from Penycae, Miss Minter. Miss - Amanson, the son - she had a son Mansell
 - and there was somebody else, a - Miss - oh wait a bit now. What was the name of the one man that used to - Bendall. Miss Bendall. And who else? Miss Morris.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember Miss - the Morris's. Morris the gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well they went to their different churches you see, yes, yes. Morris the gardeners of course they were - they went to - I think they were Wesleyans too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about farmers then, who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well 
they - went to their different - I don't know of any farmers went to church. Most of them went to chapel. As many as I knew of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the employers then, like Mr Byers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well they were church people. Yes. Yes, they went to - they went to St Mary's I think - church. Byers, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, well there you are. They would go. Yes, and - St Michaels Cwmavon after -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was a works in Cwmavon wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, a big works in Cwmavon. Of course I didn't know Cwmavon so well. I knew some people there but - John Armery and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would you say went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Now then. In - in our - in - well they were mostly working people you see. Yes, mostly. Mostly working people. As far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Would you say where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say that there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - they were not all the same. Although I should say the 
majority of them went to chapel, church, whatever they were, but quite a lot of Roman Catholics down at the bottom of the town. It was very Catholic down there. Yes. Oh yes, they were - pretty well attended their own Catholic churches, yes. Yes. Oh yes. B
aglan church after of course there - I think - some farmers and - and some - business people went there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
What about the different sorts of groups in the working class, different standards of living? Would you say that some were thought of as rough and some were thought of as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well - I don't know, perhaps - it all depended. If you were very poor - you know, they didn't have the same respect, you wouldn't expect it you see. But those that were - a bit better off now - and dressed be
tter and - you know, the others couldn't - associate with them, there was a - a kind of a feeling, you can't say what it is but it's there you see. It was there. That would be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you think one group felt superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No I don't. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Oh yes, that used to be. That used to be. The labourer was a labourer. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was a big difference was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, there was a - mo
re of that in Margam really. Mm. Was a good bit of it in Margam. I don't remember - I don't remember much about it in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose} you see because - I wasn't old enough to distinguish you see. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You felt it in Margam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But you'd feel it in Marg
am. Yes, oh yes. Yes. Dear. Some trying to be - better than the others you see. Oh yes, of course, I was getting older, I was get - and I was very sensitive to anything you see then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In school, and I was a little Welsh girl of course. And - I us
ed to help Mr - the schoolmaster, I used to help him to teach the children to sing and - and teach them for - when he'd be - preparing for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 concerts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 , he always used to get me out with the children to help - the children to sing. And some of these upper flat
s as we used to call them - these officers and - on the Estate now their daughters weren't willing for it you see. And - I remember one day going home from school, and - the organist's daughter, she was - a lovely girl, Frank Seaton's sister, she was a lo
v
ely girl, and she - we were always very friendly you know, and I remember one girl telling - don't go - don't go with that girl, she said, she's an old Welshie. I remember that. Oh and it did hurt me. Oh dear, dear. And it - but I knew she had it in for m
e because she was never willing, that the schoolmaster was making a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you feel a distinction was there between the Welsh and the English?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was a little. With the children. With the children you see, yes. There would be yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 argam community then, Groes community, it wasn't all Welsh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh - no. They were going into the English, although - Welsh in chapel. Welsh every word in chapel. Then. But it came English and I'm afraid I was one of the - I was a culprit there, th
at I - I was - there were about - I had forty children. In the Band of Hope there. They didn't understand Welsh you see. I had to teach them in English. So then I had to introduce English you see. So - used to have a lot of English in the concerts, and - 
especially now the time of the Revival, if I wanted the children to know what they were doing well I had to tell them in English. Had to you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There were English families were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They were English families. Even the poorer classes - were E
nglish families you see, and I wanted them as much as I wanted the others. Although some of the church children used to come to me. In the Band of Hope. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The church was English then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, but in Groes you shouldn't spe
ak English. In Groes chapel then. They changed after that thought. Some - knew - authorities came there, and they were English people, some people from Scotland came there, and they came to Groes chapel because they didn't like the church, you know, all t
h
e Scotch are - they are rather chapel minded aren't they. And they are Presbyterians and these people - and it was, and now these people came there, and they were Presbyterians and that opened the door - to great distance. Yes. And now - they have - Engli
sh every Sunday night. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Oh yes, we didn't - we didn't make any distinction or any - everybody. No. I remember my father used to say a man is a man, bec
ause we used to - people used to come from the roads now, to ask for a day's work on the farm you know and you didn't know how they were you see, used to to ask for a day's work, and then my father would take them in, give them good meal, and then - you k
n
ow, we - he'd come down to the fields with them and - he'd have - they'd have a share of what was there, and that was father always said, a man is a man. Dyn yw dyn he used to say. That was the sort of man he was you know. And a share for him, yes. And th
e
n he'd find room for them to sleep, because you couldn't put them to sleep in the house, well - nobody did because you didn't know - but then they had a comfortable place to sleep, and they had meals, a good breakfast, and dinner. I remember - I used to m
ake round cakes on bakestone you know, piles and piles of them, and they would disappear. Poor old chaps, yes, father used to - I remember one day father giving me the organ and I had it - when - oh but that's in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Groes Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. That's at Groes too. And - I -
 I had had the organ, now I'd been - appointed organist in Groes, when I was twenty. And I never learnt you see. But I used to play you know. I had been given the children when I was eighteen, I started with the children when I was eighteen. Oh, and it wa
s
 a great honour. Because it was only elders that were supposed to teach children in Sunday school then you see. And then I had the the Band - started the Band of Hope. They'd never had the Band of Hope before. And the children used to come from everywhere
. And - and - any old how, a sack over them or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They didn't have coats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. They didn't have enough coats you see to cover themselves. And I remember very well - about these children coming to the - to the Sunday school you know and - the chi
ldren didn't go anywhere you see, they came - but I used to make the same - same of them all. Yes. Used to no difference - they made no difference to me. No, and I remember one of the old Elders, he was a funny old man, oh he - he had no thought for a chi
l
d at all, I remember a Mrs Lewis telling him, yes, yes, she said, the childrens have never been born, they're always perfect. Yes, but - oh we used to come - at five o'clock on Sunday night, perhaps they you know, perhaps it had been very wet in the after
n
oon the poor little things - were never able to come but they'd all manage to come. They knew the little Band of Hope at five. Didn't think what kind of a Sunday I used to have I tell you. And - and I remember one Sunday night he came in he stood and he s
aid, well, where were you all this afternoon. Oh but please Mr David, we like Band of Hope best. Oh, but - oh they wouldn't miss it. And they used to come - do you know that children used to come - I don't know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 whether}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  you know - now you go all the way thro
ugh Cwrt y Defaid, and there's a road coming up to the pub - on the left - oh just before you come to Kenfig farm, up to - what's the name of that little farm the children used to come - I'm sure they used to come four miles. And they would come. I've got
 their picture in our house. Yes, Mr Miles was - oh he was delighted to see that picture, when he came, Mr Miles, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Margam Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 you know. Delighted to see that picture, he came to our house one - one day to see me. Brought me a bunch of flowers because I'd had the Medal Gee. Lovely of him wasn't it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 To have the medal Gee you've got to be a Sunday school member for how many years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, you've got to have done - oh yes, many many - well - well I had been a Sunday school teacher seventy-two years y
ou see. But I've been a teacher for that you see. Well I'd always been in the Sunday school you see, member of the Sunday school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It's a long record isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you think your sister saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No, not for a minute. We never did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you think it was possible to move from one class to another in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't know, perhaps it was, I don't know. Perhaps it was, I - I don't know what - I never c
onsidered anyone - perhaps they had a little bit more to put on or - bought - for dressing, I don't know, no, I think people - well judged them by what they could do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh 
a real gentleman and a real lady was always a real Christian. Could be sure of that. Yes, oh yes. Yes, it - meet an occasional man now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Could you remember anyone in the district then who was called a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That you could call a real ge
ntleman. Well I don't know. I would have called old Doctor Davis a real gentleman. And sit down. And look at his paper and put it in his hat and put his hat on the table. And perhaps dad used to speak Welsh to him you see. Why do you speak Welsh to me? An
d
 there he'd go and talk about the old - the old families. And he knew - he was with my mother you see. When she died. And she was one of his first patients. Yes. Was one of his first patients. And coming up all that way. You don't know the way up to Crugw
a
llt Farm. And now then you turn up - yes, you go up past the pond, you know where the pond is. Well you go up right to - up through the woods, right up to the top. A mile up. And coming up there in the night - at half past twelve in the morning. He was - 
h
e was a real - Christian gentleman. Yes. Yes, I remember it. And I'll never forget him when our children went to the - went to the hospital. The four of them went together. And he was coming every day to see if I was, and that was only - a month - before 
- I think it was a month - yes, a month before Ifan was born. Yes, and the four went. They all had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 diphtheria}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
 and scarlet. And Gwyn was - he was three - he was three days and unconscious, and they never thought that he was - never thought. I remember the ni
ght they came home, they were sitting with the children on each knee. Morgan saying, mummy - I'm sure God has something to do for our Gwyn. Because they all thought he was dead. And Gwyn said, yes, he was saying the other day, I was reminding them the oth
er day when I was there, yes, he must have had something for him to do. Gwyn is the comic of the family you know. Yes, he's good old boy though. Yes indeed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I don't remembe
r. I don't remember a policeman there. And if I saw a policeman I think he'd - he'd put the fear of death into me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why would you think like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I shouldn't know why, I had a fear of policeman. Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was it because somebody had frightened you perhaps with I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well may be something. I used to - wait a bit now, what did I see once? I think I saw a policeman - shaking a boy once, catching a boy. Oh I had a terror - or I had a terror of policemen. Yes. Then - 
not many policemen. But there were none up in Penycae, they would be down in the town you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How do you think the policemen treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I don't know how they treated them then. They had to - fight for themselves I expect then you see because - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, a shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, well it was done through the - through Margam you see, Margam }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 Estate}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 , yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well of course that was evident because they had to look after every penny. Oh yes. Oh yes, you could - of course you knew there was nothing to - nothing to throw away. Nothing. Because I remember - and t
here used to be - a lot of beggars then. Oh tremendous. Lots of people And lots of people - singing on the roads, singing for singing for food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I remember that, I remember a Saturday afternoon - I - let me see now, it was rain
ing. And I forget what had happened, but however my brother-in-law was there, and we were going to have tea. And three little children out on the road, I can see them now, and they were singing you know - las la, Spanish Chant. You know that little tune? 
A
nd these three little children were singing that tune, out on the road - singing properly or so - she had a lovely little voice, little girl and I think it was two little boys. And they were singing out on the road. And I remember - about that little girl
,
 she'd a lovely voice. And they were singing in the rain. And my brother in-law coming in, and he was crying. Oh dear, dear, dear. And there was a plate of bread and butter on the table, not a lot you see. And indeed he - what did he do but fetch the thre
e
 little children in, you know, there wasn't a lot to spare, fetched them in and put them to sit by the fire and he put all the bread and butter and cup of tea each of them. I can always remember that. Yes. Yes, very well. And I can hear that, and that was
 when I learnt that little tune. I've heard it many times since then. But I can always remember that you know. Yes, he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you think then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They - well - we thought - we thought he was giving them our tea. See we didn't know, we didn't 
understand you see. And he was crying. Oh and wasn't willing to see him cry, we didn't mind my sister crying. A woman can cry. But we weren't willing to see him crying. And he - yes, and he was giving them - put the bread and butter in front of them. And 
w
e thought well the bread and butter was gone now, we didn't know. There wasn't a lot then, but we - it was, but people used to come around and sing you know. And beg, oh always beggars. Always. And she would never turn them from the door, without giving s
o
mething. Either a penny or something, well a penny was a penny then. And many a time I - saw - and going to get a piece of bread or a piece of bread and butter, a piece of bread and cheese, whichever it would be. It was awful to hear people begging for br
ead. She couldn't stand that you see. No. But it was like that then. And the poor people didn't have much to - no, I remember that very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well we were all crying then of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you think about all these people begging?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well - we were used to it. We were used to it you see. And then these bands used to come round. The German bands, oh and I was terrified of them. I used to - and the bagpipes, I was terrified of the bagpipes, I - I used to think
 they were full of beetles, those big pipes. Oh I was terrified of them. I never liked bagpipes since then. But they used to think - make me think that they were full of black - and the most awful thing I could think of was a black beetle, and I'm afraid 
of a black beetle to this day. Yes indeed. But the singing around the road, oh singing on the road was - and bands and things like that you know, or a violin or - or a tin whistle whatever he had. Yes. Oh yes, it was not easy then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What difference did it make to the family where your brother-in-law was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well it made a big difference. Yes, yes. I remember him having his finger - cut off in the machine, in the sawmills, had his finger cut off. And it was buried in the chapel of
 ease. The finger has been buried in the chapel of ease, I don't know - whether it has been buried - with Betsan or beside the grave. Yes. It was buried just about there somewhere, beside - just about his mother's grave somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who buried it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I don't know, he buried it I expect. It was put in a little box. In the little box of wadding. Yes. And buried. Yes, his finger will be there. He conducted enough with it. Conducted. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was it more of a struggle when he was off ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - well
 yes, yes, although I don't know how did they manage then, they had a club you see. Yes, they - I remember he had - what was it called now - this - this temperance club, what was it called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 Recc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 obites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Reccobiets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So when he was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes, they had - they had that you see, yes, and people - and there was an old lady - when they were ill - there was an old lady living - up the top of the - road there, she used to make bread, and she used to tell my sister, Margaret, don't be without bre
a
d. And the boys used to bring her a loaf of bread every day, while Rhys was - not at work. Remember old Mrs Jones very well. And I'll tell you who she was now. You knew Mrs Jones - Mrs Jones that used to keep a shop by us? Daniel Jones? His Mother. And sh
e
 used to tell my - Margaret, don't be without. Yes, she used to send - I can see the boys coming down now, with a basket of groceries for her, and she'd be crying like a child, because Mrs Jones wouldn't take anything for it. No. No. And she was a widow w
ith boys. But no, she wouldn't take anything from Margaret. I can remember that very well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was your brother-in-law often off from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, not often. No. Not often. Very seldom. But - I remember that. And I remember once he had something in 
his back as well, he was ill for some time then. But no, she never - she never saw - the want of a - and of course, my father used to bring - from the - from the farm, plenty of - there was butter and eggs and bacon. And everything like that you see so sh
e - she never saw any want. But I remember old Mrs Jones, sending the big loaves of bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they ever get help from the Guardians or the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Never. No, she never, no, no, never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where ther
e was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it? Did they make people leave the district at all you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I don't - I don't remember anything of that. No. No, not in that
 - place because they were - mostly was people living up there were - well you know, working people and chapel people and - we didn't know of anybody do you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you given lessons by one of your parents, a tutor or a governess? You did mentio
n you were given lessons by your brother-in-law didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, the dodel, yes, yes. He used to teach us the - solfa. And the solfa and the reader you see, and to read - and to learn. And to learn. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How old were you then when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Four. Yes, I went to school when I was four. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You went to school about half past nine in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go for the whole day, or just morning school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I used to go a whole day, but I - 
I only went in the summer, I didn't go in the winter. No. Very seldom I went in the winter. Unless the - the weather was good. There was long summers then you see. Long summers. But - I used to stay home a lot in the winter. Yes. I don't know why, whether
 it was because - perhaps I wasn't strong or something I don't know - for what reason, but - I remember I was not - always there in the winter. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What time would you come back from school when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh half past four you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go home dinner hour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes, oh yes. Went home to dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What kind of a school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - oh dear, slates - and pencils.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was it a board school or a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Just a board - a works school. It was kept by the 
works. Owned by the works you see. Yes, it was owned by the works, Margam Tin Plate Works. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. Yes. Mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't know how did I get there? I don't know whether it was supposed
 to be for - anybody beside the children of the - workers of the Margam Tinplate, I don't know - but - we went there, all of us, oh all of the children - around there, whether it was for the children of the district, I can't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have to walk to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well it - I don't know. About twenty minutes perhaps down. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who went with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I used to go with the other - with children bigger than myself you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You had your midday meal at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I - went home then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you think of the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I - I used to like it all right. Oh I was all right because I was - it didn't matter what I learnt, I learnt you see quickly, and then I was on - I wa
s on top, I never had to fear anything in that way, because I was a good reader and everything. Well then as far as the music and that sort of thing, but I was not a good - sum worker. I never was very good at arithmetic. No. Although I - I can count I kn
ow exactly in my head, but - I wasn't very good at that well you can't be good at everything can you. But as for reading and - writing and - all that sort of thing I didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I used to get on very well with the teachers. Very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they emphasise certain things as important in life? Manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh they were very keen on manners in that school. Yes they were. I have seen that - I have seen a lack of that since then in schools, but 
they were very keen on manners. Oh yes. That's what I was telling you, they were teaching you to - you had to curtsey to - and you had to speak properly and - oh yes. Yes miss to your teacher. Yes. Oh they were very keen on manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh I expect we'd have the cane. And only once in my life I ever had a cane. And I never forgave that girl, I hope I shall have forgiveness., I think she's dead now. But - she said a lie about me. And 
it was a lie. And I was so hurt about it, it hurt me and I had the cane. The cane hurt me, but the - the thought that the girl had said a lie about me, and she knew, she said a lie. And I - she was so much old - she was older than me, and they took her wo
r
d you see. And they used to have - lavatories outside then and they were not too clean - years ago you know, not like they are now. There's a lot of difference. And - I don't know how it happened but she said that - I had done something in one of those - 
l
avatories and - and of course I knew I hadn't you see. And I had the cane. Do you know what - I had the cane across this hand. There you see, was it, yes, there. Do you know what - I had the cane across this hand. There you see, was it, yes, there. Do you
 
know that little thing smarted for months. Because it was - it was wrong you see, I felt - I felt the wrong you know. Oh I couldn't forgive her. I couldn't forgive after I'd grown up. And I hope I have forgiven her now. She was a very good woman after tha
t
 supposed to be. But - she got me - the only - what hurt me was that - it was the only time I've had the cane you see. And they couldn't - I remember miss Gwennie Jenkins looking at me and wondering why I'd done such a thing you see. Yes, I remember that 
very well, I can see it now. And going home I was. Well well well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They punished the girls the same as the boys did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. You had the cane on your hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The girls and the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would you have to do to have the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well there you are, well I don't know, somebody had done something and the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What sort of offences would they have the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I don't know, what did they - what else because I never did - for anything. But - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh I saw many a woman coming down, and getting the - the teacher out. Oh they didn't mind a bit. You had an occasional one you know, goodness. You had it, yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about your sister and brother-in-law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they take an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well of course they did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, of course I - I was ready with my work every day you know yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they meet the teachers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They knew most of the teachers you see, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh because we lived - we lived out, we lived up on top of the mountain. Were children coming near, no. Not when I was in school. No.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were they similar sort of homes, background to your yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well most of the farmers children you see. Yes, but th
ere were not many round us though. I don't know there - there wasn't many - the farms were - a bit apart you see. So we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mostly just the village children then was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The village children were down in Groes and - and in Brombil Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about when you were in the other school in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Forge Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well all the children were - together there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they come from similar sort of homes to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh just the same. Yes. All working people. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you think the teachers singled out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I don't know whether they used to know - single them out but - I happened to be a bit forward with - in music and they used to - make me if they wanted to - to learn to sing som
ething or - or - point on the modulator, I had to go and do it. But I was terrified when they got that organ there. I was terrified. They had to stop it. I was getting - quite hysterical. I was screaming. Had to take me out. They couldn't understand me at
 all. Me, I was terrified.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I don't know. I used to be terrified of these - these - hurdy gurdy as we called them. That come around, yes, the barrel organs, I used to be terrified of them, and the bagpipes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Y
es. I was afraid of them and then when this - the little organ came to the - to the school - oh well I thought it was one of them you see. Oh I was terrified. But of course - when I came on after - seven years, six and seven years old then - And when I we
n
t up to Bwlch to my brother and he had an American organ, and I heard him play a hymn on it and I wanted to do the same, and that - started me off. Yes, I loved it. And I've loved it ever since. Nothing I like better than going and sitting in the dark and
 
playing a couple of hymns. I love it, yes. Something soothing. Yes. Always been - full of music. Ever since I can remember, I just couldn't help it you know. Something that's in you, you can't help it you see. No. You can't say you're clever because - it 
- you didn't put it there yourself. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But you had opportunity in that even in the Forge school for expressing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, yes, for expressing that, yes, and reading. I was always very forward in reading. I think those were the two - things tha
t I was forward was learning and reading. Music, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were there any gangs or groups in the school? In the Forge school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember if there were any then at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were there any children left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember, I think we were all - all together there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You went on to another school after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Then when I was ten I went to Groes school. I went home then. To the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What kind of school was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That was the church school. Yes. That
 was - run by the church, Mrs Talbot's school you see and she used to - she used to give them prizes for - sewing at the end of a year and - used to have concerts and - and then the concerts were taken up to the Castle, and we used to have a - our annual 
t
ea every New Year's Day, things we used to look forward to you know. And then we'd have a big bun to go home, huge bun. And an orange, to go home. And the - Miss Fletcher would be - home at that time, the family would all be there then, because they all c
a
me home for Christmas. Oh the Castle was ablaze Christmas time. Because you could see it from our road. And - and they used to like to come and play with the children because they were not - I forget how many children there were in Groes school. Somewhere
 
about the seventy I should think. Yes. Families, you see, and the - and the fathers. All around you see used to come. Used to come from miles of course, there was no other school. There was no other school then though I don't know - whether there was one 
in Kenfig Hill. Otherwise there wouldn't be one - from Port Talbot to Bridgend. There wasn't one in Pyle. There was a little school in Kenfig Hill. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So they would come quite a long way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What time in the morning did you go when you first started in Groes school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh we went by half past nine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When did you go back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Used to go home about - about four, four to half past. In the winter it would be dark before you get home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You didn't come home in the midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 We used to take our - our - we - I took my lunch with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was too far for you to go back home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, it was a long way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long did it take you to get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well it would take me a good half hour. Yes. I had to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How would you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well either down - straight down through the woods or around the road, around the Castle way you know or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd have to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh dear, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I was on my own. For years
. Because the - they were two little girls in the next farm but they were too young - to come with me then. But - no I was on - I don't remember - because the other children - our children were so much older than me you see. Yes. Yes. And they had left sc
hool. I used to go on my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes, it was a mixed school. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you have to eat for your midday meal, you took your meal with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh we took a - a sandwich and - cake or whatever we'd - yes, apples or whatever would be growing there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you think of the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I always loved school. I really loved the school, the school was never a - a burden to me. I - I loved learning, I was al - I wanted always to learn. I' see a piece of
 paper - I would devour every word that was on it, didn't matter what it was. I was very fond - and there were not many books - of course the only books in our house - were the books that the boys had, the ministers you see. Because they were college book
s
 and - and those sort of books. But - I loved - any kind of book. Yes. And there were - there was an old. - cradle in my home, it was a very old cradle of the family, it was an oak one. And it was full of old books. And I used to look at that and wonder w
h
at it was and ask questions about it but of course - I was told that I wasn't to touch that - nothing that I could - knew anything about, and it was shaped like that you know. And it was pushed over - and - under the - under the - a corner - of the kitche
n
, the kitchen came up from the door and it was - it was a thatch you see, and it was pushed over in the corner there, in the thatch, I used to - I used to eye that, of course the upstairs - was limed, there was no painting or - or papering or anything lik
e that, it was limed every year, and there was nothing - the thatch was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You could see the thatch could you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. And do you know people used to come, I remember strangers coming and asking if they should go upstairs - to see the thatch. For 
there was nothing - the old beams were oak, and they hadn't prop - they hadn't been polished or anything like that, rough you know. And I used to push - books and all that sort of thing. And I remember one Sunday afternoon some people came, I'm not sure, 
I
 think it was from - from Swansea, I think it was Abertawe, the - it was all Welsh in our house you see, and I remember my father taking them up, they wanted to see the thatch, and - they went up these - we had three big steps there, and then you turned a
n
d then three big steps again, and then you were on this loft, and there was a place where we used to keep tea and sugar and things, to keep dry over there, it - was not to put them in the - in the - dairy, because that was for food, and - I remember that 
S
unday afternoon I came home from Sunday school, and - they were so delighted and then of course - father - whoever was there came to my sister and - make tea for them, and I remember - the lady giving me a pair of kid gloves, the first fair of kid gloves 
I
 ever saw I think. And she had a pair of kid gloves and she gave them to me because she had seen that. Strange isn't it? A strange thing to give a child. Kid gloves. I was small then. Oh well I was about - there you are, twelve, thirteen, that way. I can 
always remember that. But they were so intrigued with that thatch. They couldn't believe that they could - but mind -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The rain wouldn't come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - it had been there centuries. Been there nine centuries you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It would keep the place dry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. It was always cool in the summer. And always warm in the winter. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There'd be no heating upstairs would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, that's where all the beds were. Yes, we had two beds down, and we had two beds upstairs. But the other par
t of the house, after there was a - partition there and they used to - there used to be a bed there. But in my time there was no bed there. The old furniture that had been discarded, oh - old old pieces, old chairs and - chests and things that had - belon
ged to the past - they were up there then, and you had to go on a ladder to go up. Funny old place it was, very funny. But I remember that first pair of kid gloves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You don't forget things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, not - you don't forget the first t
hing, it was so strange. No. I forget where these people had come from. But however they wanted to see a - the thatch inside, they couldn't believe - and I remember one morning, my sister - and the little girls were there, and their bed - was - there was 
t
wo beds there, their bed was there, my bed was here. And they - we could hear a buzz. Oh - well a huge buzz. There was a nest of wasps. And they had worked their way in from the outside, right into the bedroom. This next of wasps. Well now how to get rid 
o
f those, because you couldn't light fires. Because would set all the - place ablaze you see. And I remember my father going up with a pipe, and boiling water. And squirting the boiling water and that's how he got rid of them. You had to have a - you had t
o
 have a brain now to think of that you know. Yes. But I can remember the wasps very well. Well you had to watch wasps and bees. Oh yes. Because they used to go right through, and then they'd hang you see, hang in balls like that. Oh I remember the - the o
ld thatched house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you feel about the teachers in the Groes school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh they were - now very strange this teachers were church girls. And Nancy John, Rosie Kinch. Yes, two teachers we had then. 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Nancy{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} was the - oh she was the boss, for she
 was a big woman in the church. She was a nice girl too, and Rosie Kinch, she was - her mother used to keep the Post Office in Margam after that. Those were the two, and the master himself. Schoolmaster of course, he took the - top classes you see, Mr Mil
ls. And {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Nancy{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Yes. And very strange - Nan - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Nancy{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} lived to a great age, she was - she was very old when she died. And I went to see her one day, we'd been to the flower show, and she lived in a house - close by the gardens, and she lived there to the end, 
wonderful house and a wonderful garden. Oh wonderful. And I remember going to see her and she had gone quite blind. And she said I know who's voice that is, she said, Annie Jones. And do you know she could go back over the times - when I started going to 
s
chool and she remembered all the things I used to recite. Well I was - I was surprised. She remembered things that I had forgotten. But she remembered the things I used to do in school. And she said I was a strange child in school. That's what she said, y
ou were a strange child, she said, and you knew such a lot. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You knew so much of the Bible off by heart didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. Yes. And anything - yes. And whichever Mr Mills would want to learn the school - any part in any play, anything - t
here you are. He knew he had no trouble. Yes, oh I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 All you'd learnt from a little child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. I - well I'd learnt since I was three years old on my own you see, yes. Yes, I was taught to read and - took an interest in - it was in me I supp
ose, oh I couldn't help it. And - you can train the mind and - oh yes. Yes. I remember when Morgan was a little one now I - used to sit by me when I'd be cleaning the grate or - I'd be teaching him psalms, he's got them now you see. He started very very y
oung learning. And he's got a good memory now. Yes. If you teach them when they are young - I think - but they don't all take the same interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You found that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I found that. Oh yes. Of course when I had more than one and two and three, well ther
e was a lot to be done. Yes. And at the same time. But I used to teach them when they were going to bed in the night, teach them their psalms and everything like that now, once they'd go to bed in the night I'd be up with them and - and they used to learn
 their - chapters and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Of course you still remember a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I think I remem - funny thing I was telling Morgan last night - do you know, I asked him, have you - have you preached much out of Hebrews I said. Do you know the eighth chapte
r of Hebrews? And then I began to tell Morgan how I used to recite, and once I'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 recite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
 the chapter - in my own way, they couldn't get me out of it whatever. I would say it may way you see. And I would put an emphasis on the words I wanted to you see. I su
ppose it was a treat - well I don't know it was a treat to but - it was a - a scram I think. I've heard them say - when I was - reciting prodigal son. I would say you know in my own way. Yes. The Prodigal Son, I was very fond of that. I would say hundred 
o
f sheep you know. Oh dear. Like children children are. Yes, oh yes. Yes, but now - it's a pity they don't teach so much - don't teach children to memorize now. They don't teach them to - they don't make their memories like they used to. Like you used to. 
Y
ou used to memorize in school now, great pieces of poetry. And in history. I know our children were in school and - well I know I was of course and - but now these last ten years, they don't memo - and I'm surprised at the children in Sunday school, but t
hey've got to in the Sunday school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You see a difference do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
My dear, I do. They know more than me now. They tell me now. Oh yes. Yes, the other day now one little girl, Nicola in the class, said, oh this, that and another and now who told y
ou that? Well teacher told me. All right I said. Now then, you turn to John such and such and so, and then you read that verse to me. Now then. And one little boy told me that - this story about Christ walking on the sea, it's a - it's all a fairy tale he
 
said. Is it I said. Who told you that? My teacher told me. Oh well you tell your teacher, I said, that I'd like to see - I'd like to have - the facts about that. Oh well, he said, it's about a - you see, he said, there are currents in the sea. Boy saying 
about the - the currents that were in the - and there were currents he said in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Sea of Galilee{\*\xmlclose}
. And - of course when he - one of those currents might have come along. And - and that's how he could walk on the sea. It's all a fairy tale he said. So I said
, now you be careful what you say. Who told you that? His teacher had told him. And now you go and ask your teacher, I said, who told him. But it isn't true. And he looked at me, well - oh yes, what do you think he said. Oh I know. It's there, I said, the
r
e you are, he walked on the sea, and who are we to say no. Or any teacher. If we were to believe the Bible well we must believe what's in the Bible. We can't - we can't change it. But - oh they're - another little girl there tool she - she will - oh dear 
m
e, but - a little Neil, Mary's little boy, oh I think there's something going to come of him, he's a lovely boy, but he's gone from - from me now unfortunately, he's gone to the English chapel. They - it was easier for them to go - down Sandgate. And I th
i
nk Mary's husband goes there as well So Mary - asked me - if I minded her - of course I don't like to lose the children I said, but if it's better for them and if their daddy goes with them, well I'm quite willing, I said, it isn't for me to stop them. Bu
t - he is a good - a good boy. I think something will come of him. I do really. And he's the top -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life in school, in Groes school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well of course you had to go to church. You were supposed to go to church. That element was very strong there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were chapel going weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I - went to chapel of course, well I went to chapel, but - there was nobody allowed not to go anywhere there, in Margam. They all - everybody - all
 - but most of the children went to church. Except - where the - the parents - were - went to the chapel of course and they were Welsh you see but - if they were not Welsh well there they - they went to -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was no one there who didn't go to a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. I don't think - I don't remember any, because you see - I used to gather the children. There were no children, and then there would be - perhaps there'd be a con - well there would be one big concert every year, and all the childre
n used to have new clothes for that. Not for Whitsun, but for the concert, which I used to have - either in May or beginning of June, because the children weren't able to come in the winter you see. And then they'd come out in all their white - white clot
h
es and new shoes and - and ribbons in their hair and all the rest of it you know. And - all the mothers - took an interest. And they would - they wouldn't - didn't mind the expense of getting - anything for the children. And the fathers and mothers used t
o
 come. And - gradually they would come to chapel you see, because I used to have a good bit of English then, the Band of - well I had to in the Band of Hope. They didn't understand - the Welsh and then I wanted to teach them anything I had to - and we did
 
a lot of missionary work, they learnt a lot about the mission, well of course when the Revival came, it was Revival choir after of course, they learnt the Revival books and - oh they'd oh - we'd wonderful concerts in Groes and used to come, I remember - j
o
hn Nicholas would never - never miss. And some of the - Dyffryn people used to come. Some of the - deacons from Dyffryn, they would always come. To the - and it would last about two hours. I can tell you. I worked hard. Oh yes, it was a - but it was worth
 
it you see, it was worthwhile. The children used to love it. And the church children came too. Oh yes. Yes, I had church children there. And if any one little child will - could play, he should play a little piece for somebody or - or - whatever they coul
d
 do they - they were doing it. It was nothing for me to have forty items on the programme. Didn't take long, but each child - was shown, and that brought the - the - parents you see. If you want to - and I remember an old preacher saying in Groes, if you 
w
ant to - what did he say - if you want - if you want to be loved by somebody, put your hand on that child - on that - child - on - wait a minute, how did he put it - put your hand on the child's head, and you've got the mother's heart straight away. And t
here was a lot in it. Yes. Oh yes, had wonderful times with the children, it was - it was hard work and was a long way to come through the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 storms}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  and - the wind and the rain but - I never regretted it. Never. And then the - the bigger boys would come - and 
take me up to the top of the wood after the - if it would be - it wouldn't be too bad you know, raining or something like that. And I had - put on my little lantern. Always had my lantern in the night. Go to chapel or - Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was a half hour walk to chapel? The chapel was right by the school wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh the chapel was right by the school you see, yes, yes. And they used to come up from - Hirwaun - did you know where Hirwaun Farm was? You know where Cwrt Y Defaid is? Well you go right
 over the road and then the road goes up back to the park, and there's a farm over there. The other side of where the gates were going into the park, the farthest gates, where Bakers live. Well there were little boys there and little girls, there were two
 
little boys and two little girls, and - it was a good - it was a good two miles if not more, and those little children used to come in the night. No lamp, nothing. They used to come in the night - to the Band of Hope, and to the Sunday school on Sunday. O
f course their - their father and mother came to chapel. They were people from - from Cwnafon, and they used to come all that way, they were very small. I've got their picture - when you come down to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot
{\*\xmlclose} - come to our house next I'll show you the picture - of Groes. Mr Miles saw it, he thought it - well - he couldn't get over it. 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When you were a little girl still in Groes school if you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't remember. I don't remember being - having -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they punish the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - if they did something very wrong. The master would punish, only the master.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would they have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - the biggest - punishment was stay in. After school. Becau
se you were a long way to go home and - and had to go home in the dark very often. That was the biggest punishment I remember them having, was staying in, or writing a lot of lines, oh didn't like that, but - especially the big farm boys, they didn't like
 it at all. No, but I don't remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 For what offence would they be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well - I don't know, the master was very much against them throwing stones at the birds. Or - or - and - smoking or anything like - anything - like that now, he wa
s very - oh yes. He was a very - very clean man, he was the band master, he was a - great musician, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would the girls be punished the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember the girls being punished at all. Only write lines. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents show an interest in your school work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well of course it was only my father was there you see and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he show an interest?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, of course, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I used to tell him - what I did you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well he knew them you see, knew them from children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well some - they mostly came from the - the people that worked on the Estate, or farmers. Those were the only two, classes there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, I don't remember that. No, I d
on't remember - master to teach the children you know. Singing. And I was only - well there you are, eleven. Elven and twelve. And when he'd be teaching them something new - Annie Jones, come down here with me. I think he was a Yorkshireman, I think he wa
s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I didn't - I took it - the others used to help me you see, and there were - there were bigger children than me, people that - and their - their fathers were somebody, and their mothers were somebody, in Marga
m but - used to - Annie Jones. But one thing I didn't like him to do, he'd be teaching them a new piece now for a concert, and the boys had all sorts of voices of course, they used to try and sing soprano, because you know what boys are, especially farm b
o
ys, and there'd be some horrible noises up at that. Annie Jones, go through those rows and see who's making that horrible noise, he said, horrible noise. Well I - you see, I did it once and I had to pay for it when I went out, they were all - they were al
l
 at me. Of course I had to point who was making - I had to stop - stand by the one that's making the noise, I had to do it you see. Horrible noise, and I never heard - horrible noise before, I couldn't understand what it - I was a Welsh girl you see. Who'
s making that horrible noise. Go through those rows, he said, and I had to go through the rows and find out, and then he would stop singing of course. And I was only that size, I was very small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did the boys do when you came out then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh th
en when I - I got a couple of thumps then of course. Yes. Oh I had to make myself scarce I can tell you. Yes, many a time he - oh he always used to do that. Oh I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So they singled you out for different treatment didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well they singled me
 out in that way because I happened to be - musical you see, it was nothing - I was not better than them, not for one minute but - but I knew when there was a sound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel, what about the other children, did they sort of take it out of you a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh no, not much, no, because - no, fair play, but one or two of the boys would give me a thump but - I didn't - they were afraid to do - oh they were afraid to do anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they single any other children out like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't r
emember. Ever anybody else being called out of the class to do - anything like that. Reading after now I had to - I was always a good reader. And memory, I used to memorize - I - Mr Mills used to say - that I was the best historian, because I'd remember e
verything. And he was very fond of history. And I knew all the history upside down you know. I was very fond of it you see. It was no - credit to me but I - I liked it and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was enjoyment then to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was enjoyment. All that I was doin
g I enjoyed. I enjoyed everything but sums. And I did not enjoy sums. And yet I can count in my head. Better than I could do the sums. Yes. I've even come into this decimal thing. Very quickly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about Mr Mainwaring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He's not so good. No, wel
l he - of course he doesn't go shopping like I do you see. And this - I say - around - the shops around us they know well - they say that - that I got into it - wonderfully quick. Perhaps if I go back to the old way you see, the two shilling piece is ten 
you see, it's ten you see, fives. Oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were there any gangs or groups in the school in Groes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh no, only the - only the farmers were always together you see. Yes, the farmers. You go to a farmers - anything with farmers, even a funeral, they
're all there. They're very clannish. Oh yes, yes, they're all very clannish, yes, and we were - they were farmer girls there too, farm girls there - and all those, dear, dear, dear. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember. Miners children again, coming from the Morfa. Yes, from the Morfa. Were children from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How were they treated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And they - well they were just the same you see. Depended - and it's very strange - some of them - were very good 
mathematicians. Strange isn't it. Some of those - boys especially. And they had good jobs in - under Mr Vyvyan and - the works now became - clerks in the different works after that you see. Yes, they were - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I didn't go to another school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 About - between thirteen and fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well, the schoolmaster begged of my father you k
now. To let me stay on because he would have put in for teaching. He said I would have made an excellent teacher. And he wanted me to, because I used to take the children, the little ones sometimes. The little - the little infants you know and the - and h
e
 said my father - sent him two letters I remember very well, saying that - I would make a good teacher and he could put me in for it. Well Miss Talbot asked my father twice you see, if she should educated me. So they saw me in me than I could see in mysel
f.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you feel about it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh of course I didn't know anything of this you see. But I knew that Mr Mills had asked father to let me stay on. That I would be - and now my sister got married at the time. And she - she went to live to the R
hondda, and her husband was - manager of the Cooperative - department, the boot department then. That was Kathryn. Mrs Rhys that was in Dyffryn. Remember her? Well now she wanted me to come there with her. And to go to a shop. And I went to a shop to lear
n to be a milliner. Mm. At that time - yes. But I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you have any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510 regret}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well of course I don't know - I did regret it when I got to understand. I didn't understand the - the picture of going - away from home up to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Rhondda{\*\xmlclose}
 with a lot of people well - it would draw any girl you know, and - but I - I wonder if I did ma a mistake then. But - I - and - then I remember - when they opened the - Country School - in Port Talbot - and - I remember my father was thinking then, he
 would like me to go to school. That was in a year or so after. But - of course - you see the farmers then - and I had no mother. And there was nobody to guide, you see. No one to arrange, no one to guide, no, and the money question with farmers then is v
e
ry very small. So - things outside the home and the farm - you couldn't very well. I don't know, I couldn't very well arrange my - the arrangements couldn't be made and - I know my father would like me to have been - I remember him telling you know an old
 
minister from North Wales, Gri-fith Ellis his name was, that - had my mother lived he - he couldn't believe that I was my - my father's daughter, see I was so young, because he knew my two elder brothers you see. There was such a big difference in our age
, and I remember my father telling him, if this child's mother had lived, he said, the boys would have been nowhere. She would have gone beyond them. Well you see, she - because she - had such a wonderful -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were so keen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh very, she was ver
y keen. And the boys had started, and she died. Yes. Yes, it was a - a great tragedy on my father never married after you see. And it isn't many men - like him would - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - from - oh yes
, oh yes, I - if I'd gone on I'd have - I'd have done well I think, I know I would, because I was nothing - I was full of learning, I was always learning you see. Learning was nothing to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Today you'd have had wonderful opportunities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - dea
r, I tell our children very often, I'd had their opportunity, but there you see now - the mother - especially the mother is anxious now, for the children to get on, and do something beside and - beside hand work isn't it. Yes. Oh yes. I know I would have 
got on very well. There you are. Of course I didn't know, I didn't understand then you see, and - there you are, that's how it was, that's how it has been, whatever and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. Oh no, nothing, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Your first full time job I'd like to ask you about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When you left school you mentioned that you went to the Rhondda?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mm. Yes. But - I forgot to put this in. I always
 wanted to be a missionary. That was my one - because in - of course went to Sunday school and learnt - I used to learn a new chapter for every Sunday, or - or a - psalm, I'd have something new - you shouldn't go to Groes school unless you had new verses 
o
n Sunday, oh no, you were marked - everybody had to have new verses on Sunday, and I used to very often have a chapter, when I got on to the twenties I used to have a chapter, always, but - Mrs John Lewis with us - and then - and Groes - was a very - was 
v
ery keen on mission work. Willie Jenkins Aberafon and those - and Sandy and all those people, they've gone our as missionaries, and of course we - it was we kept them you see there. And oh I always wanted to be a missionary. It had always been my - ambiti
o
n, to be a missionary. But then it wasn't the same as now. There's no chance of getting - no, and still but - still been here. And I remember one Sunday night - there was a - and I think the preacher was Moses Thomas Dyffryn, do you remember him? She woul
d
 know him. I remember him preaching in Groes. And - and I remember him saying a thing like that. Perhaps there's somebody here, he said, who would like to - to go and preach the gospel, or be a missionary, perhaps - that one won't - that wish won't be gra
n
ted, he said, but perhaps a child will come, to fulfill that wish. And do you know I've often thought of that with Morgan. Yes. Yes. Yes. He's always been that way minded. Missionary minded. Yes. Yes. And I've thought of it many times, and think that - bu
t oh I was looking at the man and I was thinking, oh dear dear, now then - now who could I ask, the - the boys in Groes of course. But there was nobody there. But they were good children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel about wanting to be a missionary, because you didn't have any means of becoming one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No means at all, no - of course they didn't want the education then they want now you see. I could have gone if I could have had somebody - to put me on the way you see yes. But I wanted to be a missionary, alway
s wanted to be a missionary. Yes, I remember - and remember the old gentleman saying, perhaps a child will come, he said, to fulfill that wish. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 My first full time job, now then, well now - of course I - I went to the shop in - in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Rhondda
{\*\xmlclose} in Tony Pandy. I was there for two years, learning millinery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I think it was through my sister. And her husband you see was - he was managing the - the boot department in the - and in
 the chapel, they met - people in the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What exactly did you have to do in the job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
In the - well - make hats. All hats were made then. And I was made a model - about twenty times a day, anybody wanted to try something on, I was the one of course for I was - small and slim then you see and - a girl of fourteen, fifteen, I - and I}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid534211\charrsid11040510  got into the chapel there. Tak}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
ing part in everything there. Concerts and all. I remember taking part in a - big concert there. Did you hear of Amy Evans the singer? Well there now Any and I got great friends. I was very friendly with her before she went to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And I remember - taking part in a gymanfa, in the Bwlch there, and Any was there and - she had won the - champion solo in National, and Amy was everythi
ng of course sna d she used to come to my sister's. And I remember I was singing, I am the one who nurses the baby, and I was dressed in a Welsh suit, had a big doll, on the stage, dressed as a baby singing, I am the one who nurses the baby. I remember th
at very well. Three nights of that you know. Yes. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Rhondda{\*\xmlclose} was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
In Tony Pandy. Mm. Oh Tony Pandy was a - a rough place then. Yes. Last night I was talking about Tony Pandy and about - Mr Ellis Trealaw, the old minister, and I 
used to take the things - after people had been buying in the week you know and they'd want their things, there was a dressmaker - in this shop as well, any hats to be made or - dresses, and I used to take them out on the Saturday, Saturday afternoon, and
 
Saturday night. And I remember taking hats for the Miss Ellis's and I was surprised to hear Morgan to say that they're alive now, one of them is ninety-five now. And - and going on a Saturday night with the hats and something else, to Mr Ellis Trealow's h
o
use, and Mr Ellis was getting ready to go - to his - calling on Sunday, to his preaching appointment on Sunday, and he was a handsome man, oh - and when I went in - he was dressed ready, with his bag in his hand, a silk hat on his head. And a three quarte
r
 coat, a double breasted coat you know, and I thought he was the thing. I didn't know him you see. I stood in awe of the man. Yes. Oh he was one of the handsomest men I ever saw. And the children, the girls, his wife and the girls were sitting round the t
able sewing. And then they gave me some biscuits and something - but I'll - I can see him now, tall. Silk hat. And I stood in awe, he was the first minister - I remember. Oh dear, dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What hours would you have to work in that shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I tell 
you they didn't have - they used to work very late then. They didn't oh yes, I remember they used to work eleven o'clock. Ten and eleven o'clock in the shops. The shops didn't shut until ten and eleven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And you were fourteen, what time did you start in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Nine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And you'd work all that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. Nobody thought of anything. And going back and fore and - and sewing, learning to do the millinery, oh I loved millinery. I loved trimming hats. I used to make the child
rens bonnets and all after that you see. Yes. Oh yes. Lovely. Oh I used to like millinery very much. And they had - there were two brothers. Two brothers-in-law, Jones and Byans, that was the name of the shop, and this Mr Jones was Mr Gelert Jones, he was
 
a Reverend Gelert Jones, he was a - they were Congregationalists, and he used to go every Saturday night to preach. Yes. That was - very interesting, I used to watch him going, but I never saw a silk hat on him. And I was disappointed because I'd seen one
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Nr Ellis was a Presbyterian I expect was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. Mr Ellis Trealaw of course I remember him. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have to work on Sunday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No, they'd no shops on Sunday. No shops on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Saturday, oh dear me, well - you'd never be out \lquote 
til eleven and twelve, my sister kept a shop, paper shop - you know, in Tony Pandy, Mrs Rhys, stationers hall it was called. It would see all a bit of everything of course but papers mostly, and books and so on. Well
 she never shut the shop until eleven. On Saturday night. And it was after that and even her husband used to - if he want a haircut or shave or something, everybody went to the barbers shop at eleven o'clock. It was then they were opening. Yes. They could
n
't you see, they - the - the - the shops were closed - were closing at eleven, and then they'd be closing then eleven o'clock - the same time the public houses. And then it wasn't safe to be out on the road. I remember one night I had a fright of my life,
 
I went out and it was raining, and the roads were not like they are now. Muddy you know, very very muddy. And somebody something navy he was, he - I can remember I can see it now, and he had got drunk and made an awful row I suppose, and they were draggin
g
 him, he couldn't stand, and he couldn't walk, and two policemen were dragging him - through the street one catching - each arm, and dragging him on the street, as if he was a piece of wood. Oh I was frightened. Oh dear dear. That frightened me, I always 
was afraid of a drunken man, but that was - oh yes, yes, it was - and the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Rhondda{\*\xmlclose}
 then was at its best. And on a Sunday morning it was like - looking at funeral after funeral, of people going to chapel. The chapels were crowded. Yes. Oh it was a - it was wo
n - it was - the people, the stream - oh - all going to chapel - on Sunday morning. And I remember seeing the same thing in Merthyr going up to stay with my brother, in Merthyr, you know, just about the - oh younger than that, and Hope chapel, do you know
 
where Hope is in Merthyr. Well you used to see them coming down now, a stream of silk hats. Oh dear dear. Used to make you think then. And then Hope would be filled. Up and down. Young people. Chapels used to be wonderful then. Yes. But in the - in Tony P
andy it was the same. Big chapels there and they were full Because there were all - there was the rough and the smooth there you see. Because the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Rhondda{\*\xmlclose}
 was then at its best. That was the best time they saw. All the pits working. Yes, oh it was - there was money then you see, yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have a half day in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Let me see, I - I've got an idea we had Thursday. Half day, we had one afternoon. I have an idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have holiday with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh dear me no. I don't remem
ber whether I was playing, whether I was paying for - paying them or they were paying me. I was paying for my learning then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You didn't have a wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No. No, and I was the only little one there you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So you didn't have any wages at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No. I forget if I was paying something for - for my - tuition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was like an apprenticeship then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. It was, yes. If I'd been there another year I would - they'd have started paying me then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It had to be a three year course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. Yes. Two years course whatever but I - I went home then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Lovely. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did your employer treat you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - they were for the best. Never had a cross word with them in any way. No. Model used to call me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel about him who was your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I liked them. I liked them all. They were all very - they were all very respectable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel about the work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I liked it. I enjoyed it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did the job alter your attitude - what did you do after that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I went home then. I went home -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were sixteen when you went back home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I was about sixteen when I went back home, sixt
een to seventeen. And my sister was home then. And she was - my other sister was married of course and - Lizzie was on her own at home. So then I was home after on the farm. With them. And in chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have a paid job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Well - no
, not then. I - I was home then - until I was nineteen - on my own. When I was eighteen - I was made a teacher in the Sunday school, which was considered a great honour, because only the deacons were teaching then. And there was one - woman, one lady, Mrs
 George Lewellyn if you remember her, she was teaching, the babies. But I was made a teacher, a Sunday school teacher of boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You weren't paid for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. In the Sunday school. But I thought it was a great honour. Eighteen then. When I was twe
nty - I began to play the organ. And - started a Band of Hope that had never been there before. There'd never been a Band of Hope - in Groes, but I started that after I - started with the children in Sunday school, I started getting them together after, a
b
out eighteen, nineteen, that would be when I was twenty, I was - made an org - organist. A friend of mine used to - come down to Margam to give lessons, she used to go to the Gardeners and - to Mr Old and to the - to the coachmen's children and - and some
b
ody else. Mrs Elsie Morgan, she was after, and we were great friends, she used to come and stay in our house. And I - my father had - bought me a - an organ. Of course I was made - and - she used to come and - and - help me a little bit you know, but I - 
I
 had never learnt to play the organ. I learnt myself. I've learnt myself. I worked at it myself. And I used to go down before I had the organ I used to go down to the chapel, to - and that was the time - when they changed the chapel, and took the high sea
ts off, and made it all flat. The round chapel. And I used to go down to practice. Down to the chapel. To - to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were at home then at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I was at home. Yes. No, I was at home. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have to do farm work or were you just keeping the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh, help on the farm you see. Yes. But wait now, no, because before that - before that wait a minute now, I went to learn to sew. I went to learn to sew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was that when you came back from the Rhondda?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. I went to learn to sew. To Taibach. To Mrs Rhys. Olwyn Rysh's mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you get that, it wasn't a job again was it, you weren't paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were apprenticed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I was apprenticed there again you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No
, not then. No. Not then. I think I was paying her something. I forget now it wasn't much but I was paying her. And I was there for a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What actually did you have to do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well now she taught me how to - but I had always been - it's very
 strange you know, I used to make my own clothes. I'd always been - I quite forgot about that now, well of course I learnt a lot - when I was in the shop, you know, in the milliners. Because they used to make dressmaking, and I used to do things, and I us
e
d to help a little bit there. Well now when I came home, I was very busy with my fingers, I used to do things. Cuttings and - and fancy work and - oh and before that of course when I was a girl - in Twyn Yr Hydd, you know, where we - you know where Twyn Y
r
 Hydd is don't you, Elliston Knox there - he was the agent for Margam and - Mrs Knox, his sister, Miss Wade her name was, she came there from London, and - she - she volunteered to give the girls - of the church - the girls of - of Margam and the tenants,
 
to - give them lessons - handwork, such as drawn thread work and embroidery work. And - that kind of thing. But at the church - it was the church girls went. But somehow or other because of Miss Talbot you see - I was asked, the only chapel girl. Which br
ought a storm on my head again. Because I had been in the - in the - choir before, oh I forgot to tell you about the choir, that I'd been in the choir. Yes, I went to the church choir too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 To Margam Abbey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 To Margam Abbey. Now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you get by with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Now then - when I was in school of course as I tell you the - the - I used to take part in all these and I used to go - we used to have our concerts in - in the Castle, and there Miss Talbot took a great note - deal of notice of me 
then, it seems, but - and Mr Seaton the organist of course - and I had a very good alto voice I suppose I had a kind - a kind of voice he used to say, that I had a certain kind of voice. And they were short of altos in the choir. So I was asked to come an
d
 sing - sing alto, and they used to have the - the choir concert as they used to call it - this big do, it was - at the beginning of the year every year when all the Castle people would be home, and there was a choir concert and dance. And however I was a
s
ked to come to the choir. And I went of course. And I went down to Mr Seaton, and I sit on this - he had a bench. Where they used to put somebody else to play duets in I expect, these benches of long strips of wood you know. I used to sit with Mr Seaton, 
a
nd he used to teach me to sing. And he gave me voice training then. Taught me the way to sing. And I used to learn to - a lot - of him you know. And he was very - he was very stern and very strict, but he was a lovely man. However I got into the choir you
 see and I was singing alto in the choir. That didn't please the chapel people at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have to go on Sunday to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I would go to chapel as usual. I was a member in chapel of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was only for special concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Always special - special concerts you see. But they wasn't all willing. Some of them are jealous of course. It was the one big night - of the church was the choir concert, and dance. And - I had a ticket given me, and one for my sister. We had two tickets
. You could only go - they couldn't buy a ticket for any money, you only had them given you. So - I was - I used to go down to have practices with Mr Seaton and - learned them all of course and - I knew them in - no time. However, the week of the concert 
c
ame, my brother - Margan Jones was living with us then, a minister. And he was living at home then. He had bad health. So we - my sister and I were going to go to the concert, so I don't know, she had rigged me up in a - a frock, a little frock I had, and
 
she'd made a - a rose to put in my hair, a red velvet, and I had very fair fluffy hair then, I had a lot of hair I suppose. So - she dressed me. Then - so here he come. Then he had been out for his daily walk out the road and - and he said - what is all t
h
is preparation. Where are you going? Oh well of course I said I was going to the - to the concert. What concert? As if he didn't know anything about it you see but - I told him, we were going to the choir concert. He said, no, you are not going. Well - an
d
 he was the oracle of course, he was the authority in our house you see. He was a minister. Oh dear, dear, Lizzie and I looked at one another, well, well, well. Well the next day came, there was only two days now. I have told you. You are not going to tha
t
 concert. Well, why? You are not going, you a member in the chapel. Oh no. And there was a practice that night, I went to the practice with a very heavy heart I can tell you. However I came home bouncing and everything was ready for me and - and I'd had n
e
w little shoes, my sister bought me pumps they called them then, little - black - black - shiny shoes you know. I was it of course. And my hair done and everything. Well, he said, if you go to that concert I will break you out of Seit. Well now then - wel
l
 if he had said that we were going to the gallows it wouldn't have been worse, to be - to be struck off the list of the - chapel. Break you out of the Seit. Well - talking over it, my sister and I that night, oh - what shall we do? Well I couldn't - well 
a
ll right, and we said to him like this, well, we are going to the concert. We will go to the concert and we will go home, we will not stay for the dance. You are not to go. Well, we'll go home, we will not stay to the dance. Well that's how - we went. The
r
e was refreshments coming down from the castle, all the lovely things you could think of, after the concert of course. I was singing with the choir. And singing with somebody, forget now. Oh it was a great night. And I was plainly - plain - very plainly d
r
essed, well I had nobody - to - do me up, you know, like - the others were. But - however - I think I was singing with somebody - this alto solo. However this refreshments came. Oh we couldn't go and leave all these refreshments and the tables and - every
b
ody but - I was the only - we were the only chapel people there, Lizzie and I. And we didn't feel too - didn't feel at home, and yet I didn't mind, I'd been used to them by then you see been going to the practices. So there well now then - came twelve o'c
lock. And - they'd been dancing then oh and I enjoyed looking at the - it was the - that was the only place to see the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 clothes you see. The Miss Fletchers were - of course they were the last word to us, and I can see them now swishing round you know,
 long dresses with a - a frill like that you know, going round the room, in the orange room, you know where the orangery is don't you. That's where we used to have it. Well the - oh and enjoyed it. Came on, half past twelve. Oh well now - we thought we'd 
b
etter go home now. But we had - enjoyed it, we'd had about an hour of the dancing, after having - supper. Going home, now we were going - we went through the side door that goes - through the - goes beside the church - from the Orangery if you were coming
 
- out past - the churchyard, and then up to the little gate, that was our way. And we were going but we - we weren't - we were wondering whether somebody from one of the - one of the graves would come up to meet us and tell us we'd done wrong. We were goi
n
g with fear and trembling. Up we went. Didn't see anybody or anything of course, got into bed. Well - and my brother had gone to bed of course. He had a key. And my father hadn't said a word against me going you see. He was quite willing for me to go. But
 
of course my brother - we used to call him Billy for - William Margam as he was, Billy you see. However there was no Billy there whatever. And - not a word - the next day was Friday, and then Saturday. And now Sunday. And he had said that he was going to 
c
ross our names out. Going to bring us in before the - deacons. Sunday. Well - for - I didn't go to chapel Sunday morning, Lizzie - seldom went because - she had to make dinner and see to the milk and all the rest from the dairy you know. I didn't go to ch
apel. Watching my father and my brother coming home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Fear and trembling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. Oh when did it stop now? Afraid - of the verdict. He came home - not a word. Not a word was said, asked my father if - if the Elders had stayed behind. Yes, they'd stay
ed behind but - it was something else about the big meetings. Oh well. Went to Sunday school expecting to hear the worst. Went to chapel in the night expecting to hear the worst. Well now then to the prayer meeting Monday night. We'd be sure to hear somet
h
ing then. No, nothing. Well Society Wednesday night, well that wouldn't be - we were prepared for it. We never heard a word. I don't - he didn't say - but you see, he knew their attitude you see because - they were dead against these old church people and
 - remember one of them telling me, oh church people - patronizing lot. That's what used to happen, I'm surprised at you going there and - and they were dead on me you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was real animosity there between the church and chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - oh t
here was. There was. And yet - and - the church was a - as if they were a step above you see. Because of the Castle. Because of the Castle people. But - the Castle people were - made no difference between - church and chapel. If there was anybody ill, Mis
s Talbot and her lady's maid and the little basket - was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They didn't make a difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh no. She never - she never and - I remember one day - coming home from school, it had been prize giving, I had a prize for sewing and she used to giv
e prizes for sewing, and - doing little things - well, it was sewing mostly - from the - I forget what she used to give the lower ones, but I was now - in the - upper standard, I think it was a little - basket or something like that. But however she said,
 
I want the little - little Annie Jones, you have to stay here - you have to go up in the carriage, with Miss Talbot. Oh - well well. Butterflies. Butterflies wasn't in it. So of course into the carriage and she and her lady's maid and the coachmen. What w
as his name, I forget now. I knew him well too. However -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not Baker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. It was Mr - and his only son was killed in the war. And the only son of the gardener, Morgans. Yes, I remember that, the first world war. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Ogden{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Ogden{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} his name was. Yes, and
 - dear me, going into the carriage and sitting - with the lady's maid here and Miss Talbot in front of me there. And now she said, I want you to sing. Just as we turned up into the drive I want you to sing. I want you to sing a hymn, she said, I think it
 goes, oh hills of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Jerusalem{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. She wanted me to sing Oh Hills of Jerusalem. They sang it, she said, in my father's funeral, and I want you to sing it. Where was I going to find my voice. I don't remember how much of it I sang. But I remember that very well. 
Well that was talked of in school for months I think after that. Because I had gone - in the carriage with Miss Talbot, and the - the following - the week after - this was the last week, well now the - first week of course we used to have our annual tea u
p
 in the Castle. And - she came to me then. She was always very nice to me but - she thought a lot of my mother I suppose because - she was the last of the old Morgan family, and in my - my old home was one of the Granges, of Margam. And probably - and it 
w
as historic because - that's why she wanted my mother to stay there when she asked my father - to come there to live because - she didn't want it to go out of the old family. So there - and - that was my - my ride with Miss Tabltot. I never forgot it. Nev
e
r forgot those things. Those little things used to come around now, we were sitting down having - having our - and they used to make - everything themselves of course, everything was homemade in the Castle. And the jam and - all that, the little - sandwic
h
es and - all that sort of thing you know. I can see them now, little pies like that. And then for sweets - they used to tie them - into bags of flour. They used to have a bag of flour, and put sweets in it and tie it, together, and then they'd hang it up.
 
And then - just - just so that you could catch it with your mouth. And you had to - you had to jump to get it you see. Yes, and that's how you had your sweets. Used to jump and catch those, and of course the - the one that would catch them be covered in f
l
our. Oh used to have some fun about those sweets. But oh they were wonderful people to the children. That's what I can say about the landed gentry. They can say what they like, but we found in them - they made no difference in anyone. And the church and c
h
apel people used to go - to this tea, there was one difference. The Sunday school children that went to the church, and the roll of cloth, the boys enough to make a suit, and the girls - enough to make a coat and frock. And - the only colour that I can th
i
nk of - it was always grey. Although I did see fawn there once, but was mostly grey, and I got a new costume now just that colour. New coat and dress, it was made from you know, by a lady from - Aberafon, Mrs Taylor, very good dressmaker, and - the colour
 of my best suit now is just the colour of that grey, but they used to have a roll - of cloth to go home. But we chapel people - had a big tea cake. Huge one. Oh it was huge, like a dinner plate, and - and an orange. Now we had that to go home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So that was a big difference, what did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
We - oh we preferred it, we could eat that. Oh we preferred the bun, we could eat it. You couldn't eat the - the others, you see, the Cwm Brombil people now the - the miners children and those - 
well - they couldn't afford you see, and - and they relied on it every year. They had that every year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would it make some people go to church do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well some. Some of the English people would go, but - it was very funny you know, used to
 go to church on Sunday morning, used to come to me to Sunday school after. And to the Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They didn't have a Sunday school in church did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, they - no, Sunday school in the morning. And the children used to go in the morning. Th
at was - but then - several of them used to come to me after. Yes. So they'd have another tea with me of course and - and concerts and all the rest of it you see. And a trip down to the sea and all that sort of thing. Treated them, all of them. But - that
'
s how we - that's how - that was our church school. And it was lovely and I - think - and I remember the creed and remember - all I learnt there. All the English - hymns. I learnt them in school, and I knew them every word. And I know them now. I know the
m now. I do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 English would be the language in Groes school wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, English every word. There was no Welsh. And some of the se girls you know they used to - I remember one of them telling Bertha Seaton, Mr Seaton's daughter, go - don
't go and play with that girl, she's an old Welshie, about me. And - but she was made of - different stuff, this little girl, Bertha Seaton, do you remember Mr Seaton? Oh - Frank. He was lovely. Oh he was lovely, I - I loved them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It didn't make any difference to her that you were called a Welshie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not a bit. Not a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well of course I felt that size. But Betha would say, come along dear, never mind, don't listen to her. Don't listen to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They were mostly English in the school were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh - Scotch - oh, real Scotch she was. But she was a - a - rough type. A rough type. Oh yes. Of course he was the boss, her father was the - boss of the Estate you see. He was the master, poor thing. He - he had - notice
 to leave in two days. His house and his job and everything - after. After all that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh he done something you see, gone beyond his - yes. Mm, yes, oh yes. But I remember old Welshie, I can remem - I can see her now, old Welshi
e, as if I was something - but Bertha - Bertha Seaton, and that was - that girl - was a most beautiful violinist you could ever listen to. Oh they were all - they were all - everyone of them. Oh they were wonderful. And Olive, Olive had a wonderful voice.
 Olive and Bertha and Pattie. Oh Pattie was the - she was the harum-scarum of the lot you know. Pattie. And I used to go down to chapel and then I used to play in the chapel every night, there was something on you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You had to go to Taibach to do this dressmaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But I had to go to Taibach to - Courtland. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Courtland Place{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Now - in front of - in front of where St Theodores is now. They were building St Theodores then. Had they finished it then? Yes. Cwrt Ucha. And - and the Cowan's lived next d
oor. And the Cowans of course were related to me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you get that place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, no, they - she used to take - apprentices you see. Yes, she used to take apprentices.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What hours did you have to work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I used to go at nine 
in the morning. And then I'd finish - oh there was no - it all depended on the orders she had in. The work she had in you see. Yes. Well she used to - I - I learnt to cut out and - learnt a couple of things and - sometimes now we'd have a skirt - to start
, to start we'd have to make a petticoat or something, and underclothes we had to start with. Then when we'd come on to make a blouse we were - ready to take our wings then. Yes. Oh I used to like Mrs Rhys very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What time would you finish in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh in the - oh it was after tea. Yes, oh five or six you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you work on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - well, yes, on Saturday sometimes, but not always. I didn't always but I don't know whether the other gi
rls went in. But I didn't. If I'd go on Saturday morning - when it came on to the end you know, I'd go perhaps on Saturday morning. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The end of your apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The end, yes, of the apprenticeship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have a half day in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And you weren't paid anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you get on with the people you worked with there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh lovely. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did Mrs Rhys treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Very very nicely. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel about her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh I liked her very much. She buried her husband. Lewis Rhys's brother, do you remember her - do you remember Miss Hughes? Tall Miss Hughes. Well it was Miss Hughes' sister. And she had buried her husband. Lewis Rhys's brother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I liked it, I - I - I loved sewing. Yes, I liked it very much. And I was - I was eager to go and earn something you see. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you actually earn at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well yes. I - I went sewing then for about two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You did two years apprenticeship with Mrs Rhys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. Yes. No, I didn't, no. I only went for - I didn't do a year with Mrs Rhys. No, a - about a year. And then I - two years in the millinery, about a year there, and then I was sewing for two years then. I went out. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you have to do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well everything. Oh you'd be surprised. Had to do everything. But - childrens clothes, I made two wedding dresses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you work for yourself? You didn't work for anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh for myself. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you get out know about the jobs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I - well I used to do little things you know and - after I learnt with Mrs Rhys - then - she was telling people you see who to get you see. And I used to go to the farms mostly. Yes, I used to spe
nd weeks in the farms. Yes, I used to spend weeks in Brombil. And when I used to go to the farms you know I used to - especially friends of mine from - used to love to have me of course, but I used to go to an old lady, Auntie Anne the Cwm we used to call
 
her, and - she used to ask me, I don't think I ought to ask you on a Sunday, she said, but will you come to me tomorrow. I've got a week's work, have you promised anybody? Well - if I had promised I promised of course. I couldn't - so it was all right. We
ll come tomorrow morning. And do you know, every morning when I went there - she used to - when I went, oh before that of course - I'd forgotten this part, I'd been staying - as a companion to two old ladies. I'd forgotten then. Oh that was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was that before you went in to the dressmaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Before I went to learn to sew. Yes. I went to these two old ladies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In Groes. In Corner House in Groes, next to the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you sleep in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, I stayed in there. And I used to have one had six a week. I did. That was one and six mind you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have to work every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, every day, and do everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Any half day off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Washing and all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. And they used to - the
y used to keep the preabhers. Used to come Saturday night and go back Monday morning. Experience for any girl. It was. I went now then - after I had been my home and my sister - came home, and then my brother got married. And he - brought his wife there. 
W
ell now - these two old ladies were living in Groes. And they wanted somebody to come and look - be a companion with them you see, look after them and be a companion. Not so much - they didn't want to call me a servant at all. A companion they wanted to c
a
ll me. You know, they were on their high horse. So - I - however I went. I remember Mrs Lewis saying no I wish you'd come and look after my aunts. Because they'd love to have you. Very well. And I was still - I was the organist in the chapel and - had the
 
children and everything there you see, full - full trim then of course. So however I went to the old ladies. I was with them for two years, over two years. And - they us to keep the preacher. And the preacher used to come every Saturday night, from everyw
here. And they used to walk from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose}
 station, down to Groes, three miles. And - then they'd be preaching on Sunday. Well - and what we used to do I used to - make the dinner ready, on a Saturday, but - for us, you see, we had our dinner on Saturday,
 but on Sunday - the preacher went to Mr and Mrs John Lewis, to the chapel house. Up above the chapel there you know. He went there to dinner on tea. So then I didn't have to do that. What I had to do was get up and make breakfast for them, and supper. An
d breakfast Monday morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They stayed two nights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They stayed two nights. Oh that was every week. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You didn't have a resident minister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, we didn't - never had one. Every Sunday, yes. And then it was a hard day for me Sunda
y, I had to be up - early well then I had to be - in chapel to play by - ten. And then Sunday school at two. Band of Hope at five. And then chapel at six. And then there'd be singing school after until about nine. Then I'd - go and make supper for the pre
acher. And that was my Sunday you see. And when he was home - it was the same at home. When I was at home, down by ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So you didn't have any half day or holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was like being at home really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Only they paid you one and six a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 One and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But you still went to all your activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I did all the chapel - oh they were such chapel people. The chapel came first with them. Oh they would do anything, oh it didn't matter - as long - if I went and did my work in chapel. There you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you have to do actually in the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
In - with the old ladies? I did everything. I did all the cleaning. The washing. And - now they used to have another woman in to wash. No, wait a mi
nute - yes, that's right, one and six, but - they used to pay her one and six for washing. But now I was doing my own washing, she wouldn't wash for me. No, she said, she wasn't going to do my washing. And this went on for a few weeks after I went there s
h
e used to come to wash. And she was an awful slut, terrible. So - And this - and old Auntie she used to come - she used to watch me and she said one day, I like to see Annie wash. There is not a spot after her and her pinafore is always clean, she said. T
h
ey didn't know I was hearing this you see. Do you think you would wash for us? You will not turn Mrs Whaticall it aside? But look here, she is so dirty and Annie so clean. So however she asked - they asked me, if I'd do their washing. And I should have th
e one and six. And I had the one and six, I was having three shillings a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well nobody thought of much of wages then you see because - they used to - when I went to sew - a shilling a day I had after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were having your food with these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Because I was having my food. Of course I was having all my keep, everything here you see. I was having my food certainly, oh yes. One and six there you are. And my keep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would you do with the money you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well - first thing I used to do I used to put a little bit in the envelope for Sunday. I made sure of that always. It wasn't much but - and then I'd buy - buy my clothes you see. I
 used to make them myself, I used to buy my clothes. Stockings and shoes and things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you get on with the two old ladies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Lovely. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did they treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They treated me lovely, they treated me like a daughter. Oh yes, they were lovely to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh I was all right, unless I had very big things to wash now, a quilt or something like that. Yes. OH yes, I was all right. I was very happy with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The - work. Well, it was like doing any ordinary housework you see. Yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So it was after that you went to do the dressmaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And after that - well now they died, one of them died. That was an awful expe
rience. She had been ill - for a few weeks. And - and one night she was calling, she called me all the time and I got out of bed, and - I was sleeping in a little room in my own bed, and they were sleeping over in the over room, and then the other room wa
s
 the preacher's room. And - they slept in that there and she'd been calling, and she'd called me out of bed two or three times and I'd gone to see what - what she wanted. And - oh I was - I was worn out and I was ill at the time. I had anaemia. And - and 
I
 remember she had been - very restless that night. So I had gone in and gone back to bed now. So I got up now to go down to get breakfast. And when I was going down the stairs, I felt something very strange. I felt as if the house had gone - suddenly stra
n
ge. Suddenly - silent. There wasn't a sound. Because Aunt Eliza was sleeping - in one room, and Auntie Jean the other. And - here I felt very strange. I went down, went down to make - make breakfast. I used to take her breakfast first. And I was going up 
t
he - made the breakfast for her, cup of tea and a little tray and little roll. She liked to be so so you know. I was taking it up at the bottom of the stair, and then something - something struck me that there was a - an awful stillness upstairs. I went u
p
 to her room, and I said, And she was like that. Not a move. Well - I put it down, and I looked at her. Oh dear, dear, I realized you know, that she - that she was dead. Well now how to tell Auntie - next door. Because Auntie had a bad heart. How to tell 
h
er and be wise. Not to - I didn't know what to - so I went in, oh dear, I said. And the old lady looked at me. And she caught in my eye, then she came in and - and she looked at her. Annie, she is dead, she said. I was glad she took it that way you know. 
B
ut she lived after. She lived for about three years, she went with her - with her niece to - Port Tablot to live after. Tjey went from the little house then you see, and it was then I went to learn to sew. Yes. But - it was an awful experience. Awful. I w
as very - oh dear - I missed her very much, she was a - a dear old soul. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Then you went out sewing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
And then I went out. Yes. And oh I went to different people I can tell you. I got to know different people then. Dear. I used to go - int
o Brombil Farm for weeks you know. Old Mrs Marvick and I were great friends. Great friends. And one night - Mr Marvick was taken ill, the old gentleman was taken ill. And - Mr Marvick said to me, stay here Gwen to night, he said, because - I don't believe
 
my father is up to much, stay with Twen. Stay there and sleep you know. I didn't really understand what he - what he could see coming you see. So I stayed with Mrs Maddock that night to sleep with her, and indeed - not much sleep for either of us because 
-
 he died that night, old Mr Maddock, but - I don't know - I never want to experience, or hear anybody - having such a terrible time. As such a - such a hard time. Terrible. I've heard people saying about - hard death, but I'd never - I didn't go in, and -
 but - could hear him all through the house. And never forget that, it was an awful experience, for a young girl. And I was a young girl you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What actually would you have to do when you went out to these houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What actually would you have to do when you went out to these houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh whatever would be, mending a lot. I used to mend a lot and I didn't like that. Especially mend men's clothes and underclothing. Used to mend everything then. And sew buttons. Many times Mr
 Maddock would come in now. Miss Jones, I want a button on my trousers. Well Willie, what are you - what are you doing. Well you can you go and bend in the field without breaking your button, I used to have that very often, I used to - and mend things, bu
t
 I used to do lots of childrens clothes, and childrens hats, little girls hats I used to make. I'd make a dress and coat now, I'd make a hat to match. I remember making a suit for a little girl to go to a wedding, white silk. And this was a farmer's wife 
mind. She'd bought the silk in Neath, Neath market was the - big place then of course. Your mother would remember that. And - she'd bought the silk so I made - a frock, and - a coat, and I made a white silk hat, all rucked the silk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How much would you be paid for doing all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Shillinga day. Didn't matter what I did. And some places now - well then there's that house now, I'd go at nine o'clock in the morning, but carrying the machine was the heavy job. I used to carry the machine very often, an
d sometimes they'd come and meet me - very seldom they'd come and fetch it, and sometimes the boys would come and - you know, and sometimes they'd come and help me and send me on the way back you know. But - carrying the machine. It's no wonder I get pain
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were saying about that particular house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
There at nine in the morning. Well then I'd be working all the time after, sometimes - until nine in the night if I didn't finish what I was doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And you still had the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And I still 
had the same. But in most places of course my time was six o'clock, to finish, but if I hadn't finished the job or if she wanted me to go away or - something like that, I've seen me there until nine o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they give you extra then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. 
No extra. But I remember when I was - I remember having - now feathers - were sold at a shilling a pound then, and I was beginning to - get a bottom drawer ready, and I - of course I wasn't at home then to see to feathers myself, and she used to sell me t
wo pounds of feathers and - and then I - I'd be working for those. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 She'd give you the feathers would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I'd have to pay for the feathers, perhaps I wouldn't pay full price, but - I'd have to pay for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you make your own feather bed would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Made my own pillows you see, and cushions and anything like that you know. Oh yes, everybody did that then you see. They made their own.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You used to have a bottom drawer whether you were actually going to get married or no?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes, oh yes, yes, yes, yes. Yes, yes, oh yes. Yes. And - but I remember - and then I remember going to sew - to Kenfig Hill, I used to go a lot to Kenfig Hill because my sister lived there, my sister that was blind, Mrs Marshall you know. And I u
sed to - I remember going there - go - she had a - a lady asked her - she owned a public house there, the Prince of Wales I think it was. Well Mrs - think her name was Mrs Lewis, she was one of the kindest people I ever worked for. Though she kept a publi
c house. And her daughter was a nurse, and she'd been to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Greece{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, learning painting. It was a sight to see her paintings. She used to pain on glass. Yes. And she'd been to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Greece{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 to learn painting, and she - oh it was interesting. And - I forget what her nam
e was now. She was a nurse whatever, or a matron or something - in a hospital. Nurse I used to call her, Nurse Lewis. And she said, she asked me - what - when I came there, she said, now - one - twelve o'clock, one o'clock, yes, now you've got to take a r
e
st, she said. First day I was there. She says, you've got to take a rest now until two o'clock, she said. My goodness. Oh well, I thought, no shilling a day for me then. Didn't say anything. You will sit there and take a rest, she said. And then she would
 talk to me about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Greece{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and all the rest of it you know. When it came five o'clock you've got to take half an hour for tea, she said. And finish at half past six. And that was the kind of people I saw in a public house. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about these other places you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't - oh well, if - I ate my lunch and went back to my work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have to take your own lunch or did they provide it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, they had - had dinner with them you see. Oh yes. I had my - I had breakfast and - th
ere was breakfast ready in most places. When I got there, yes. Quilts I used to make. But quilt would take me - three or four days. Yes. It depended on the size of it you see, if it was a three yards long, and two and a half wide, that was the usual - bed
 size you see, double bed size. If they wanted it very big it would have to be three by three. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the frame, would you have to take the frame?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. I had my own - my frame was made for me. When I started sewing my brother in-law,
 he was a carpenter, Rhys Nicholas, the one that brought me up, he made me a frame. To - to quilt. And - three and - three yards long - well I can make any width I like you see, because it is - you can stretch it out, you can - the - the two ends - can ma
ke them as wide as you like. And I could make it three by three. I made many quilts, some heavy, some - light.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd take that with you when you went to these places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, yes, the - the frame would have to with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you often be asked to make quilts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
If there was a wedding anywhere, anybody getting married I made many. Upon girls getting married. I - there was a lady living next door to - living the other side of us, they used to go go to - to - Dyffryn, Evans, John Evans. And 
she was getting married and she wanted two quilts. Wanted a summer and a winter quilt. So I had to put - blankets in the winter one you see. And sheets in the summer one. Yes. And they were made of - sateen I used to like, floral sateen, or - plain sateen
.
 But sometimes - they would buy - a roll of cotton - perhaps on the market or something, and there was - lime in it. Like the calico used to be. And it used to cut your fingers. Oh it was a terrible thing for sewing. But - with sateen now the satin'd be -
 lovely for working. Or the fine flannelette or a fine flannel, anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It would take three or four days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It would take me three or four days to make it. Yes, would take me four days and and they wanted them done you see, oh, small, t
he stitches small stitches. I once got mine now, when it's cold in the winter John says well - where's mammy's quilt? He likes to have that, yes. Yes, I made many quilts, I made some beautiful ones too. And some would like a - a frill. The frill on the si
de of the quilt was very fashionable then. Yes. Each side, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have to have a room then to work when you went to these places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I usually did, but sometimes I - it - depended on the size of the house now, some houses I can remember
 - used to sew in the kitchen. Because they didn't have a - a fireplace or - if it would be in the winter now and - but - in the kitchen - mostly, by the window.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about when you were making a quilt because the frame takes up a lot of room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh - in another room then. Oh yes, in another room because you'd have to take a room you see. Yes. Yes. Oh yes. Dear, always had a quilt - in the house now that - the children - I always find it in the - in the middle room of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd always have a quilt on the go would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Probably I would then when I - when I was sewing I would usually have a quilt on the go. Yes. It was hard work, hard for the fingers.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The same they would pay you whatever you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No extra if you did a quilt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh - well of course the quilt seven and six I used to have for making a quilt. Yes, that was the price they used to pay for making a quilt but - they wouldn't get it for twenty-seven and six today. No they wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But would you have the shilling a day as well as the price of the quilt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well you see when I was making a quilt I'd be at home. But of course if I was making a quilt - in their house - a shilling a day I'd be having of course, as far as I could and they'd let me go on for ever if I go some of them. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well - about two years, but - after - after I got married - I used to make quilts for people after - used to do a bit of sewing after to help you know, used to sew - and I made all my own quilts of course before that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have another job then after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When you finished going out doing this dressmaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I didn't go after. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You went back to the farm then did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, I went back home then, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were there at home then were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, yes. Until I was married you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you do then at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - of course the house you see had to be - had to be seen to and - doing what - used to do
 a lot, I used to sew - I used to do all my - sister-in-law's sewing - for her. All the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And for the children. Used to do all the childrens work. Boys and the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They were living at home as well then were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They were living in the old home then you see yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You've done no other jobs have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no other, only sewing. And teaching music. Yes, I used to teach music when I was sewing. I used to teach music in - let me see 
how many pupils did I have when I was sewing, nine I think. I had three or four in Kenfig Hill. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What were you teaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh teaching the piano. Yes, teaching the piano. The daughter, Katie Brombill and Katie Cwm and - oh yes, I have - I thin
k there was - there was about nine pupils I had all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd be paid for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, seven and six for twelve lessons. Oh I was made then of course. It was a little bit extra you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go on doing that after you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No, not - I did a bit of sewing mind, but - but not the - oh I did too, I did some. I did a little after - I had two or three - after I was married and I remember a lady next door - used to come in - into our house to have lessons. And - oh yes, ye
s. Yes, I had two or three after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well I don't know, I probably - I would have liked to be a teacher you see. Yes. And everybody thought I was - when I - when I came to Grove Place - they 
all thought I'd been teaching, I'd be a teacher. Yes, well of course I'd been teaching in Groes so long you see. Yes. Yes. And had such a - big Band of Hope there, yes, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh dear no. Didn't know anything about that then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you feel there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Ther
e was, There was. They used to have more money, now this - that's what this has come in to you see here. They don't see that one man is better than the other, and that one man - should have - be paid more than another, but they don't realize - that it cos
t
s one man to come to his position. You see, now these boys down at - in the colleges, well, what does it cost their parents. I don't know what it costs them now, they are more grants now I suppose, but - I know what it cost us now to teach the children, t
o
 have them taught. Well now - when they take up a job then - they expect - more than somebody say - it isn't disrespectful, I am at all, because I'm a daughter of a - of a work - hard working man and I worked hard for a shilling a day myself. But still - 
I
 couldn't expect - the same as a - say a girl that had been in college and had cost her parents - like we had to cost Morgan and Margaret. You see, and then years - now Morgan was nine years - training to be a minister. Well now you can't expect a man - t
hat is being - well say sweeping the road, well - of course sweeping the road it - it's work the same, I'm not disparaging that at all but - he hasn't got to - work his brains - like - the boy that is - spent years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you feel there was a division of interest in those olden days between a craftsman and the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well - I don't know, they used to take it for granted I think. I don't think I - they took it for granted. Of course in Margam now - the - men that worked on the estate - I think they
 all had the same wage. I think they all had - I forget what they were now, I know my father used to work - on the moors to clean the ditches, so many hours, there were two or three men who knew how to do it. And my father was one, used to go - for two or
 
three hours in the morning, and that was all they could stand. In the mother ditch to clean it. Well, eighteen shillings he was having, for that you see, eighteen shillings a week. But it wasn't - it was only a few hours a day. Because no man could stand 
longer than that you see. But the - I think the average money in Margam - on the Estate was about that. Whatever they were doing. Because there were so many men - were in the woods and on the roads and everywhere you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 About eighteen shillings a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
About eighteen shillings a week I think they had. I don't think, they had - but of course - on the other hand again - their houses cost them a shilling a week rent. And they had their gardens, they could - well everything they needed, all vegetab
les fruits everything they can. Yes. And the - the - the farms were - was - was - were so much different then. From what they are now. Oh yes. Oh. They don't do it for the love of it now. I knew every - every - every chicken and every cow and - they all k
new their names, I used to give them names all of them. Cats and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I don't know, you got to know - different - the different people, different kinds of peop
le. Oh I - I think it was a good education to - the more people you knew the better - you were educated I think, that is if you had an eye to - to look for it Everybody didn't you see. No, I'd no - if there was a sharp child now, no matter how poor he was
 
- I'd know very well I could do something with that child. Some of them were poor, I remember - a little girl - she had to go to hospital. I think - she was about fourteen I think she was, had - had her breast off. Well her father and mother were so poor 
-
 although he was working underground, that is with - his his money was very very small, and they were a big family, and this little girl - didn't have - a nightdress to put on to go to the hospital. She had to go at - a day's notice, and I remember very w
e
ll - telling her mother, oh don't you bother. I'll make her a - I'll get her a nightdress I said. And as it happened it I had got a - material to make something in the house and - calico I think it was, and I remember - making her a nightdress overnight. 
A
nd taking it down to her in the morning before she went to the hospital. They were as poor as that you know. But that little girl had the sweetest voice. She was one of my little children in the Band of Hope. They were poor children. They were a family of
 
poor children but they'd wonderful voices. And - I remember the eldest boy, he had a wonderful voice too. Joe his name was. And they were such - nice children you know. They would do anything for me. They'd go anywhere. And I remember him sending home - h
e
 went - they were taken to the - first world war, there were three or four of them, these boys, used to be in the Band of Hope, and he wrote back a letter - to his mother and he said, I would have fallen many times - if it had not been for what Miss Jones
 
taught me in the Band of Hope. Well I thought that was worth all the years of - he said, I would have fallen many times, he said, if it was not for the - what I learnt from Mss Jones in the Band of Hope. I was - and they were - when they used to come home
 you know they used to come to see us. In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose}. Yes, you see. And then -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 After you left school did you continue to live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, yes, I continued to live at home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You did go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Rhondda{\*\xmlclose} to live with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. With my sister you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 For two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, for two years, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you come home at all then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I used to come home periodically. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your father at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. No. Always the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. Just the same. I was the little one all the time. Yes. Yes, there was such a difference in our ages you see. And I - I was so young, I used to feel - oh I don't know, som
etimes I used to feel a bit of a lone bird you know. Because I was the - you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were like an only child weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, yes, in a way you see - In a way. But - not with my father only. No. And he used to tell me about my mother and all 
that sort of thing you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Only to oh - well to chapel, and Sunday school, oh yes. The chapel was - built around us and I was always in everything, until I became eighteen as I tell you and then 
I took - a childrens - Sunday school class, and then began to play the organ, and there you are. I was always in chapel. Yes. I had to go down to meet the children there. I couldn't have - it was up in Grove Street then. Because Grove Street was full anyw
ay.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How many evenings would you spend a week in chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well now in chapel in Groes it was like this. Sunday of course all day. Monday night there was prayer meeting. Tuesday night there was Band of Hope. Wednesday night there was Seit. Thursday
 night there was a scolga. Singing school. And then Friday night there would - almost always be a Bible class. Perhaps on Saturday night there'd be a rehearsal or - something or other somewhere. And that's how my - that was my life, yes. Always. Always. W
ith things of the church. And that's how the children were brought up too. Yes. But now it's only one - service a week now and there's no Band of Hope you can't get children to - come to Band of Hope now you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. We were all Liberals in - in Margam. Everybody was a Liberal. That's all I knew about politics - was Liberals. Mr Talbot of course was a Liberal you see. Yes, he was the father of the House of Commons then. Yes. Yes. Yes, yes. Oh yes, they were a
ll Liberals. Everybody was a Liberal in Margam, yes. Oh dear yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So you continued to spend your spare time in the same way really didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. And - but - there's one little thing, I don't know whether you can call it political or no. 
There was a - a letter sent to the chapel - from the different churches around there, they wanted to build - to build a public house, in - somewhere in Groes or Margam, and now of course the rule of had been in Margam there was no public house to be. Beca
u
se there used to be a little - in one of the little houses by the church - there used to be a small public house, just a little - country one you know, where the farmers used to go sometimes, and I suppose one night - Lady Charlotte Talbot - was going hom
e
 from church, and she had seen somebody coming out of this little public house the worse - for beer - the worse for a drink, a little bit unsteady, not - not - very bad I suppose, but - she said there was no public house, it was to be closed and there was
 
no public house to be in Margam. And it has remained so to this day. But however now - this is what I was coming to. The - this - this paper came and wanted - to - build a public house in Margam. And then - the - there was a leaflet sent all round to the 
c
hurches, and it came to Groes. To - to ask them of course you had to get - the people to - give in to it you see, to be - willing. So - however - another lady and myself, Mrs Hicks - she and I were appointed to go round every house and every farm in Marga
m
 - to put their names to this sheet. What do they call it now, the - a kind of a form it was you see, against the - having a public house - in Margam. Talk about walking. I walked for days. Walked to every house, and every farm, and fair play to them - I 
d
on't think - any one refused. In one of the farms, but you had miles and miles between them. Well now - we got through to Brombil first then on to Gross, then - the other side, Cwm, Tonmawr, Grigo. Right up to Penybryn, and then we had to come down and th
rough {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Water Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, down Water Street Margam you know, and we didn't go - have to go to Pyle. But we went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address
}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Water Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And the Pyle in was there you see, but there was not - it - I suppose it had - the - the rule had been made in Margam there was no pub
lic house to be between Pyle in and the Summerset Taibach, there was no public house to be. But of course the Twelve Knights has come since then. But the Twelve Knights is the other side of the river you see. It's in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose} side. But there isn't o
ne in - and it was - it's down on the statute book. Yes. And I was one of the two that went - all around Margam, to every house to ask them to sign this form. Children, I had the children from - and we turned the Band of Hope into a - into a revival choir
 and - yes. Yes, oh wonderful time. It was - 1904 and 1905. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
But - well of course the revival started you see in - in - Luchar, Sir Evan Roberts of course, and - then I got to know somehow or other, I got to know his sister an
d got to know him and his - brother. And - they came - of course they were going all through and when they came to - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose}
 I met them then. And it was a - I got interested with them, and then - that's how I started, but we had - of course they came t
o - to Groes do you see, we had wonderful - some wonderful times with them, and some people - that were not members - in the chapel - and didn't have much to do with - with religion, Taibach and Groes then - but - changed the place altogether. Yes, change
d
 the place altogether. Well now then, in the beginning of 1905 - of course I got into the swim and - got going in Groes, oh we had wonderful - wonderful services, well we were there until midnight very often, and out to the road and sing away after, it wa
s wonderful, it was a wonderful time. But the beginning of 1905 I think it was - that I went with - with - Mr Dan Roberts and Miss Mary Davies Gorseinon, and myself, that we went up to - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}North Wales{\*\xmlclose}
 to Llanidois, went to some chapels there. A wonderful time there. I forget all names of places all of them now. Oh yes, North Wales, yes. Oh yes, we were up in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}North Wales{\*\xmlclose}
, we saw - some wonderful services there, wonderful. And do you know we - I remember going - we had been to - we had been visiting Angus, this 
little chapel, the Moriel chapel that afternoon, and we were going back now to Llandilois to - China Street, have you been to Llandilois? There's a big - yes, yes, there's a big - it's a big chapel, two big doors going into it, a big chapel. And we were c
o
ming back now this night we had been to - other places before that you know. And we - came back and when we came back to the chapel we couldn't get anywhere near the place. Because of the people. Couldn't get near the road. Oh it was full, so then we had 
to go around the back, and we only had room to go in - to the pulpit, there was only room for us in the pulpit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you actually have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I used to sing and - recite and - chapters and - I sang a lot then. It was then I did - and tha
t was what - they wanted me to do when I was on the - television you know. They wanted to hear - what I'd been singing then. Yes. Yes, I used to sing a lot then. But - I remembered that night, that was a - a wonderful night that. We went in and we - of co
u
rse we had to go straight up to the pulpit. When I looked down it was full of - ministers you know, the ministers were looking. Well maybe - and it was my turn to start the meeting. And - I can see them now, I can see - I can see one of them now. And I st
a
rted - by reciting a - Fifty-third chapter of Isaiah. You know the chapter do you? Yes, that's right. And - and - and when I was saying that there - this man was looking up at me you know. I can see his eyes now looking. And do you know I nearly stopped. 
H
e looked you know, he looked it. It was a won - it was a wonderful sensation. Yes, wonderful. And - and when he went in - and sat down in the pulpit now just before the start, I noticed two young men coming up on the gallery there, that every seat was ful
l
 you see, and they came down and they could only sit on the step, and they sat down on the step, two boys now, they - one - one of them be something like your boy now Andy. Something like that. And they came and they sat down on the steps. And they were l
o
oking round and - I don't know whether - they were chapel boys or - seemed to me afterwards that they were because - there was great rejoicing and they stayed behind whatever. And - I remember oh - well forget now as I say - that was what I sang that nigh
t
, and there was a - a man sitting over at the far end over there. An elderly man. When we were all - all people singing now, this man got up over in the corner. Well - you never heard anything like it. Remember it very well. And I was watching these boys 
y
ou know. And then when it came on to the end one of - they got up, and they went up to the top of the gallery as if they were going to go out. And then they stopped, and they came back again. And they were going on sing - I forget what they were singing. 
A
ll those you know, all those thing - things they sang then. And Mr Roberts, he had been speaking and - Mary, she had been speaking and - the three of us were doing our work you know, and one shouting here, another one shouting there. But however I was wat
c
hing these boys you know, a funny thing, I was watching. I was glued to them because I knew - there was something there. So - they got up again, and went up to the top, and made as if to go - down the stairs now. And - tell they were singing, Gtell Mother
 
I'll be There, you know, used to sing a lot of that then. They came back again. And now they were testing the meeting. To see if there was anyone staying behind and - and new members of course, and these two boys came and sat down. Oh, he fainted. They mu
s
t have been well known. I think they were because the - some of these deacons came to the chapel house where we were staying - that night - and they were still singing at half past twelve. But these boys, I - I'll never forget that. And I was watching the
m. Oh as if my - well, I knew the boys were struggling you know. There was a struggle there. And - there they sat. They sat down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long did you do that for, go round like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I - I didn't do it very long, of course they did it 1904 and 1
905, but I didn't go very - very - much no. No, about a couple of weeks perhaps, because I came home you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did you go altogether?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well mostly North Wales and then to - to Gorseinon and Carmarthen, oh we had wonderful times in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Carmarthen{\*\xmlclose} too, wonderful. Wonderful times in Carmerthen, wonderful people from - people from underground you know that had been - the miners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you plan the service before you'd start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No. We didn't know who was going to take part in the serv
ice. No, everybody - to take part in the service you see. Everybody that - one would pray here and another would - sing there. Oh yes, oh it was wonderful. Oh dear, it was wonderful time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What was it like really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They used to come from work and 
then they used to - they used to have their food and - and - on to chapel then. And they'd be there until mid - midnight. I remember in Taibach - I'd been up in my sister's - Mrs Nicholas, and she had been to - to Neath and Evan Robersts himself was there
 
that day. And she came home and I was waiting for her to come home. I was - I wanted to go down to chapel to Margam. And she looked strange and she said she had never - in her life - seen anything like it, as the people in that chapel that day, they were 
a
ll shouting. It was - it was a wonderful meeting, but - what I remember - of course I didn't know that it had come now to Groes and - and Dyffryn, somebody from Dyffryn had been there - by this time. And when I was going down past the - where you turn dow
n
, on the bridge, to go down to Dyffryn chapel - there was a crowd of men from Dyffryn, singing and praying. And oh, well, dear, dear, dear, and I was going down to Groes then of course I - wanted to be down in time to - play the - dear, somebody had been 
there from Groes. So you know, it spread that way you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you think it was emotionalism a lot of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. Not for a minute. No, you see - as they were saying then, that it was a visitation from the Holy Spirit, that the country had gone into s
uch a state. And something was bound to come you see. No, I don't for - oh no, I don't believe that. Might have some - might have I don't know, emotion but - what - what made you sure was - the changed lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You saw changed lives did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I 
did. I saw a man - a man I think he lived in Taibach. And he was a terrible man, he was nasty to his wife. And he used to drink - terribly. Well of course when he was drinking he know what he was doing. But I saw that man - coming down to Gores, I heard h
i
m - I - I heard him myself on his knees. I never never saw such a change - in my life, you could hear him shouting. He was shouting to the road. And - but the change that was in that man's life you had to see to believe it then. Whereas his - his wife use
d to say - that she was terrified of seeing him coming home from work in the night, and the children were terrified of him. As I heard many saying. I heard them saying it on the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Carmarthen{\*\xmlclose}
. They were afraid to see them coming in, and then they used to come 
home, and - wash and change and go to chapel. Now what was that, it wasn't emotion in it was it? You couldn't call that emotion. You know, it was - it would be wicked to say that was emotion you see. Oh it was, and I remember - one night in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Carmarthen{\*\xmlclose} - in
 the place called Penygroes, and there was a man there - he was a horse - doing something with the horses, and underground, and I suppose he was the terror round the place. Everyone was afraid of him. And he had a - a book - per hand, can see him now, and
 
there he was, oh it was a - well, it - it was unbelievable to hear him, and her, he was - he was - praying that night and he was saying - everyone used to be afraid of him, and everyone used to be afraid of this - because he was a terror I suppose, no man
 
would fight with him or anything you know. Everyone was afraid of him, but now Lord he said, the devil is afraid of me. Do you see? Well no that wasn't emotionalism you see. It wasn't emotion, no. Oh wonderful, wonderful. Very good. Yes, wonderful. Oh yes
,
 I knew - I heard many - many saying - that their lives - and especially the women, when you heard the women saying - that it was a pleasure to see daddy coming home. Whereas the children - used to fly from him. You know, there's - that was not emotionali
sm you see. Perhaps some would have made a - I don't know, I - I can't say because - it's too terrible a thing to think of. It's too - it's - it's too terrible to thing to play with, you can't play with that you see. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did it feel like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 W
ell - I was in the middle of it. Yes. Yes. Well you see in a way I'd always - I'd always - thought that way. I'd always thought - it wasn't - it wasn't strange to me, I had always - I - it wasn't strange to me. But - remember I learnt a a lot. Oh yes. I l
e
arnt a lot. I saw how big I was, and how small I was. Oh yes, it would make you you know. I remember - one night - in Groes, the first night they came to Groes. And - now this - he will smile at this - the - the - talk came now that Mr Evan Roberts was co
ming to Groes. So now - I thought oh and that there was going to be a lot of people there and all the rest of it, and there was an old keeper living not far from us. Old Henry. And - he said to his wife - put my black clothes by the fire, he said. 
\lquote Cos he h
adn't thed them on since his wedding day. Put my black clothes by the fire to air, he said. I'm going to hear that man. But - the revivalist. Very well, the clothes were put by the fire. But however - the day before the meeting, the message came that Even
 Roberts - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5388354\charrsid11040510 him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
self couldn't come. That he was sending his brother instead. So - it was his brother, but I remember that, that the night came, and I was getting ready to go to chapel and father saying - you'd better go early, because I was playing the organ 
and I thought there'd be a - a crowd there to sing you know. I was going to play the organ of course. My duty. And off I went, I was there before time. There about half past six instead of seven. And the place was full. When I got there. And - dear me, no
b
ody giving out a hymn. Everybody singing as he wanted. Thought to myself, oh - and I was sitting over by the organ on my own you know and looking at - and coming and coming and coming the people, father came down, of course we had the farm and he had to l
o
ok after the stock, he couldn't come and leave everything you know, there was only - only we both there that night I remember very well. And I couldn't see any chance of any - that I was wanted for the - by the organ, but I - I sat where I was, quietly. U
ntil it came on now ten o'clock. Here's a bustle by the door. Three or four young men come in. Evan Merchant was one of them. Young Evan Merchant. And some boys that went from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
Bethany{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - as missionaries after that, I forget - Clement I think - I forget their name now. And in they came. And oh - of course there was the jubilation, and then - one of them said - they had come from 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Bethany{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And - there were - navies working on the road, they were making the roads in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Port Talbot{\*\xmlclose}
 then. And three of - three of them I think they said, yes, it was three, had seen lights in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Bethany{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, and could hear the singing, and had come in. And stood by the door. And they were singing - somebody singing - there's power in the blood, won - wonderful blood of the lamb, something like t
hat, and then another one stuck up, tell mother I'll be there. And they went in. And on to the big seat. And this biggest man of them all - went down on his knees. And began to - they began to shout and people began to - shout and - well - and singing. An
d
 their - they started to pray, and they said - God, he says, you know what I am, he said, and you know that I don't know the way to pray, he said, I haven't prayed since my old mother taught me, he said, and here's my prayer oh Lord, he said, Gentle Jesus
,
 meek and mill, look upon a little child. Pity my simplicity, he said, suffer me to come to thee, and then they began to sing, tell mother I'll be there. Oh there was an awful place there I suppose, and these boys came from that you see, down to Groes. Th
e
y set the place on fire. And half past twelve when we came out. And father had gone home, thinking I'd be following now you see, coming up. Somebody else would be coming as far as the drive and then I - well - half past twelve came. I looked at the clock,
 
it was half past twelve. Well now the people are beginning to go now of course. Oh - well - indescribable. You can't describe it, and these boys, they were great. Remember Evan Merchant, oh dear. Yes, and then - I remember that very well. That was the fir
s
t time - we'd - a revival meeting came to Groes. First time. And I remember when I was going up the road - I could hear the trees singing, I could hear - singing all the time in my - and I could hear the trees - I could swear that every leaf was singing -
 
in the trees you know, going up on my own up through the middle of the wood, and telling father what I got in, well well now bach he said. Because it was late you see. And - he thought perhaps I - I'd be - be afraid, but I never was afraid of the wood, I 
n
ever met anybody. And - I said to him, but the trees were all singing, I said. And he said, to me, it wasn't the trees were singing, he said, it was your heart was singing. But I could swear - I can hear it now, I could swear those tall trees - were singi
ng, all - voices in them you know. I'll - always remember that. Yes. That was my first taste of the revival. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long did it go on for then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It went on - more or less for two years, 1904 and 1905, and it spread and then some of our mis
sionaries - took it to - to India, to the Casha Hills and - it went to - went to England too to some places. But it swept all through {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And yet - there were a few people - now as you said now about emotionalism, a few people dared dispute you see. And
 a few ministers disputed. Yes. You see the people were - clamouring, going into those - to those churches, where this was going on you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It wasn't in every church was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not in every church. No. Not in every church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was it only in the non-conformist or was it in the church as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember that it was in the Anglican church at all. I don't remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Evan Roberts was a Presbyterian wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, yes,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did it go to every chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh mostly - it
 was in - but as I - as I say now - every one - it depended a lot I think - on the ministers. I think it did. If they didn't agree with it you know, they didn't agree with some things. But - but the - well this getting up and shouting and singing and - of
 
course the - the service had to be - conducted - the usual way, they couldn't see you see that - oh no. But it made a difference. Oh yes, of course someone back to the old life and - they did have - once they - it cooled down gradually. But - it left its 
m
ark. Oh yes, it left its mark. Undoubtedly. Yes, and it was only - if it only save a - a thousand souls it was worth it wasn't it. If it was only one, one family. Because the families now - that I was telling you about, but now - the - the mother wasn't a
f
raid you see, the father coming home, the children, running to meet him. It was a great - it was a great thing you know. Oh yes. And those boys going out - to the war and the - they had that you see. Mm. No, the first would - yes. Yes-. Oh yes, yes. Yes. 
O
h yes, the - it was a wonderful time. Wonderful. I shall never forget it. And it made you feel what you were. It made you feel small. Made me feel small. It made me feel that - that my - I called myself a Christian. But - I ask myself now if I'm a Christi
a
n. I'm wondering now if I - if I - if I've got the - the right you see, Christianity means - giving up - I don't know. We won't know this side. Oh no. We shall know when we - when we go hence I expect but - oh no. Oh yes, trying and we are having strength
.
 We will have strength. We believe that otherwise we wouldn't be here. We wouldn't be able to stand very often did we, if we didn't believe them that's all - the Saviour asks us to do is believe. And I am with you always, that was my last hymn at the Goli
ad, I don't know many people have been telling me about that, that they seem to have had comfort from it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way, when you were older and left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about all this writing of poetry you've done and hymns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When did you manage to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well - oh yes, I did a lot of - of hymn writing before - before - well I tell you my sister went to America and I was only my own. But I'd always been that way, since I was a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You mentioned that you were writing verses when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
When I was a child. Yes, yes, I was writing, that was right, when I was a child I was writing verses you know, such verses as they were, I wouldn't show them to a
nybody of course. Well now - and as for composing music, I've always done it. It was a part of me, and composing music on anything. It was in me, well it - no, I couldn't help it, so then - but - when my sister went to America - I was very lonely, I was i
n the house - of course, farmers - they're out from six in the morning until six in the night, and up there in the farm on my own you know, and I was always composing. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Your sister Lizzie was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 She married did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 She m
arried. And went to America, yes, yes. But - the - I used to compose a lot of hymns then. And then of course the revival came, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Before that you were composing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I used to compose before the revival. And then - about - I think it was abou
t two years - I had learnt a lot of the New Testament, and a lot of Psalms, before that, but - but the time - when the revival came - I made up my mind that I was going to learn the - learn John, I wanted to learn the - the gospel of St John, because I lo
v
ed John, wanted to learn the gospel well I thought to myself, well all right then, if I'm going to learn John - why don't I start in Matthew. So I started in Matthew. I learnt that Matthew and recited it Sunday after Sunday. Recited the chapters you know 
i
n Sunday school, Sunday after Sunday. Matthew. Mark after. Luke. John. And then on to Acts, Romans. Oh I loved the Romans because I had learnt some of the - of the Romans you see, and I'd learnt some - of - John and Luke when I was very young. Romans. Dea
r, onto Hebrews. Colosians, Thessolonia, I went through the lot. \lquote 
Til I came to Philemon. And there's only two chapters in that. And I was taken ill then, I went very ill, I was in bed for a long time then. And I didn't learn Philemon somehow or other. So I
 had got - and I'd gone on - to the - to the Revelation, I'd learnt a lot of that, most of it. About four or five chapters left perhaps, but Philemon - and I remember when I went to have a medal, the - Gee Medal you know - I was - of course they'd had my 
history then, and they knew that I hadn't learnt Philemon and they asked me what had Philemon done to me. The minister asked me what had Philemon done to me then. I expect I shall hear that you have learnt Philemon before long, he said. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The Medal Gee is given for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Long service in the Sunday school. Yes. And I had been seventy-two years a teacher you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But it was at this period that you were really learning the New Testament off by heart then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, well now then yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You didn't do so much after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I didn't learn - didn't learn much after, I was teaching the children then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So you in your spare that's what you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, I was always - I always had them. And I'd learn a chapter 
in an hour then. Yes, that was a wonderful holiday. What I saw in Germany then - and of course it was these - and we used - these young men used to come up - from the college up to the - Englanders house as they used to call it, to our - because we were E
n
glish and the boys you know were there. And - one of them I - I was a little bit afraid of him, I - didn't like him very well. And he used to wear a straw hat and - I can see him now. And he said to me one night, we have been preparing twelve years for wa
r with England, he said. And we can afford to - prepare another twelve years. We probably shall, he said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That was in 1903 was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. I've come from there. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you come to go there, to Germany, a holiday was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - went 
for a holiday with nanna you see. To her - to - my - my friend from Cwmavon, Miss Thomas. And she was going to her Uncle - Molly, Mr Evan Molly. Do you know any of the Molly's in town here? Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He had a job out there did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He was the managin
g a tin works there. And I - a cousin of his - which was his name - Jenkins, no. He and his cousin, they were managing this big tin works, and under the Rio Tinto they were you see. The works had been opened out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When did you go actually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And - we went - they were living in Ruselstein. We went by boat to - to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Hook of Holland
{\*\xmlclose}, and then we took a train up after, up to Ruselstein and Noybid, where the Prince of Bid lived. And we used to see them coming down in a carriage you know. Rush out
, but you know when we used to go to a place - all the people used to come out of the houses - as if they were coming out to see a circus. To see us. But they were bitter. They were bitter to the English, because of the Boer War, that had been - hadn't be
e
n very long before that, but they were bitter to the English, and sometimes now - if - if they'd been in - say they'd go and see - some people go on a visit now and go to see pictures or something like that, and do you know they'd hound them out. And the 
t
wo boys, two boys they had, and they went out with their bicycles one day out to see the country, and do you know they had to go - go for their lives and leave their bicycles and all. They were that - in - well the feeling was there then you see. And that
 young man telling me - we've prepared twelve years for war with Englanders, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 he used to say. It was. It was. And it wasn't very safe, I used to go out - to go out on your own. Oh and we used to - and they didn't understand, we had names of every - e
very busman, every - well they had - yes, they did have buses of course there then, and we had names, one of them was George Llewellyn, he was the one that was always on our bus. Oh dear, we used to have some but - there was a - and in the hotels, oh dear
, it was a wonderful - wonderful experience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Six weeks. And we saw - six churches. We wanted to see all the churches you know. And the Mr Morley of course all Welsh in the house where we were you see, and - we used to go 
to see the sights that were in - and then - all Roman Catholics you see. All Roman Catholics there. Although we went to Protestant church. And we went to a Moravian church. Where the Moravian nuns were. Long black gowns and - little white caps with pink b
o
ws and - used to march into church. And do you know there - if you coughed - the Pastor would stop. You couldn't - shouldn't make a sound there Oh they could teach us a lot. Yes, they could. And - and I remember - I - I wanted to know, the first time we w
e
nt into church and - the daughter, Nan, she said, deary me, and I said look at that there, the Prince and Princess of Vieder in their box up there you know. And I said to Nanna, oh dear, look at those people. She said, whatever you do, she said, we'll hav
e to go out if they see us peek. You shouldn't - you shouldn't speak. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you writing any of the hymns then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, I had - oh - I started writing hymns when I was very very young. But - when I was about nineteen - twenty - twenty began to
 write hymns, you know, the books are here now but I've never - never published them, but I used to make all the work for the children of the Band of Hope, and for their concerts, except when the - when the the - revival came you know of course we had the
 
- that book then you see, the revival song book then you see. But I used to make all - and make all their plays, all their dramas. I knew exactly who could do what. And every part was - I've got some of them here now, but I never published them and - many
 people have asked me, because I think I've made about - twenty-four plays in all. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were busy during your spare time here then weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I was never never idle. Never, I used to take }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5388354\charrsid11040510 my}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  - I used to learn my chapters and take my - testament up to the fields with me and - learn you know. Yes. Anywhere where I could have quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You used to compose hymns then before you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Oh yes. I used to compose hymns before the time of the revival. I composed many - many hym
ns then, yes. Oh yes, I composed many hymns. Time of the year. Of the revival. Many. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 At this time after you'd left school and you were at home, did you go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Only to chapel. Nowhere else. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - i
f my - if father would be going I would be going with him or - if he wasn't able to, being on a farm you know there was always - specially in the summer now. I used to go - well I was always playing and then I always went. To chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Because you were the organist I suppose you had to be there every service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I - yes, I was always there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you make any new friends, boys or girls, at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - well I don't know, there was no - not many new people coming to Margam. Beca
use it was - I don't remember many, only as many as I'd make if I'd go to Cwmavan, up to - Nanna you know and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You mentioned this friend in Cwmavan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, yes. Oh yes, used to - get to know people. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 She was your special friend was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. Well she was then my special friend, then. And then in the time of the revival came - May - Evan Roberts' sister was my special friend, and remained - you see, I must show you her - picture with her -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you bring your friends home to your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I - bring anybody that would - it was a long way for anybody to come but - they used to come you know, yes. Oh yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The special friends you had, there was this friend from Cwmavon and then May Roberts, where would you go with 
them? You mentioned this one holiday you had in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Germany{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. Yes. Well - the only places we did go it was - it was some church service or - or a - concert or gymanfa or - something like that, it was always - a religious service, I used to go with Na
nna sometimes - when she used to go to have her music lessons. I used to go with her sometimes but - to Swansea, but - very - very seldom yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your father meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - yes, yes. Oh yes, anyone that came there with me was always welcome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, well he knew - he knew where I went, where I was going. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Sell - it wasn't very safe to be very late up there because it was - it was very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What age were you when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Twenty-nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long had you known your husband?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well since - dear since - I don't know. Since I was a girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well in chapel you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh he was in - he was from Margam too, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you save up money before getting married or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. I didn't. Not much chance of saving then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your parents help you to set up a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, my father did you see. Of course I had no mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5388354\charrsid11040510  we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5388354\charrsid11040510 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh dear, I don't know, I don't remember. Well I don't know, there were no form then you see, there were no formal engagements then at that time. I don't remember one of our - our ch
ildren being engaged, I don't remember it. Didn't - didn't think of those things then you see, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Could you describe the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - usual wedding in the Margam church. That's where all our family - were married you see. My mother was married there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In the Church, not in Groes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh there was no - oh no - they didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Your mother's uncles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Had the both uncles, they were clerks with Mr Knight the old - the old - cannon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Can you remember the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - just in - an ordinary wedding. Don't - remember very much about it now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh dear yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I forget how many were in my sister's now, I forget how many they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 We went down to Carmarthen, to a friend of mine - one of my - friends during the - during the - revival. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did you live after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I was home for a little bit and then I came here after. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How many years do you think you were at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. Well I don't remember, between there and going down to Cwmbrombil, I don't remember much now, I think - might be in - we came here - we've been here - sixty-one years I think. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So 1911 you came then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. Sixty - it was roughly - we - we've been here roughly sixty to sixty-one. We've been here sixty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How old was your husband when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He was thirty-four I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What was your husband's job when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh he was doing the same, he was a blacksmith. Always been a blacksmith. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he have any other jobs before or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No. Oh no, not as I remember, I - I remember him a boy in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
PlaceName}}Margam{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Gardens{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, in the Castle. In the Castle gardens. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But as soon as he had an opening in the tinworks he went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He went there, Mr David you see, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You didn't work after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, only I - gave music lessons after. Children used to come here, chil
dren used to come here you know to - yes, I used to give music lessons before that and gave music lessons after.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 From the house here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mm. Yes. And I think I've been giving music lessons ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did your husband feel about you doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh he was all right. Yes. Oh yes, he - helped me to be - we've been - one in everything. We have never quarrelled. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How do you think your husband felt about his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well, he was all - of course he was brought up in it and he
 was - he understood his work you see and - understood the works and grew up with it I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh he liked it I think, oh I never heard him say - anything different. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Before I was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I've - yes, indeed it was - I've got five beauties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Can you remember when they were born, those that were born before the end of 1918? It was only Iswa was born after 1918 was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, well now there's Morgan and Margaret and - Olwen and Gwyn. And Iswen. They're the five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You haven't any idea when they were born roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - yes, wait a minute. Oh I don't, I - as - as I told you I - I do get - 1912, 1913, 1915, 1917.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. And - and 1918 I think Idwen was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were the children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. They were all born at home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you know what to expect in childbirth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did I know what to expect? I don't know indeed. Does anybody? Had to prepare at home. OH yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you really know w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5388354\charrsid11040510 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 at to expect do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, well I don't know, no. Oh well we knew that we had to expect to go through a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You knew that before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. And - oh yes. I know when Morgan was born I thought I was dying. I know -
 I remember when - when Gwyn was born, oh I had a terrible time then, I remember very well. I had an awful time. And the morning that Gwyn was born daddy was going - to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cardiff
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} to be attested to be taken to the war. And he went that morning and he came back and he had passed class A, and I didn't know what day he'd be called away. And I had three little ones besides him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - I was very ill and I had - then I had a gathered breast and I - I remember Doctor Davies - telling me, I
 would always suffer from it, and I always have. Always this side. And then - a month before Idwen was born - the four children were taken to hospital - with diphtheria and scarlet. And I can see me now lying on a couch in there Listening to the horses ho
oves going up the road, I didn't know whether they'd come back or no because Gwyn was unconscious, and he was two years old that day. So you can think now what it cost me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was a horse and cart arrangement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was, that big van. Yes, to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Top{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Hospital{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And the four children. Oh - and Gwyn was unconscious you see, he was unconscious for days, they didn't think he'd come from there. The matron came here every day to see me, and I remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And you couldn't go and visit them because you were expecting Eidwen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No, I couldn't. And I - and I remember the nurse carrying - Morgan was the last - to be carried out, and when he was going through the passage here and I was standing there, mummy, oh don't cry will you? Well - oh I'll never forget th
at. I'll never forget that, it's always stands out.. Terrible. And the - the - sound of the horses hooves used to make me sick after that, then in a month the baby was born. Matron was coming nearly every day to see me and Doctor Davies was coming, and he
 
was going up - to see me, and their father went up - almost every night while they were there, and I didn't see them. I didn't see them at all. But in a month the baby was born. And the matron went into the war and she said - your mummy's had a present. O
h
. What do you think - would you - what kind of present do you think your - oh a baby I suppose said Morgan. Well now then - but I hope, he said, that it isn't a girl, I hope it's a boy, we've got enough girls. Olwen and Margaret. It's a little girl. Oh al
l
 right then, he said. As long as mummy's there didn't matter. Well there of course she kept them there after till the baby was a month old. I didn't see them for eight weeks. And when they came home, of course the baby was in - I used to make my own baske
t
 and - and ribbons and frills and - the muslins and all the rest of it, I had my own little - little - cradle always, oh I was very fussy with baby I can tell you. She was more like a doll than a baby. And - and Margaret came in, she was so matter of fact
 you know. Oh dear, who flattened her nose? Because she had a tiny little nose you know, Eidwen. Oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did the others say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - of course Olwen couldn't get over the baby you see. They loved the baby, yes. But Gwyn of course was the 
baby. And Gwyn - had shut himself up in the cupboard one day, gone into the cupboard to eat sugar, and we couldn't find him and he'd shut himself up in the cupboard. Oh he was a - and it was there he began to talk. Yes. And there he was weened. Because he
 
had the bottle, he had been such a delicate baby and I had such a terrible time. And I hadn't really got over it you see. So there, they came home, and the following Wednesday night - well of course I had to teach them a verse - a new verse, they'd forgot
t
en their verses then, I had to teach them a new verse to go to Seit on Wednesday night, following Wednesday night. And - the one that - Olwen learnt was - that was her verse, and they all had their verses and went to - went to Seit on Wednesday night afte
r
 they came home. And they were sitting down having - dinner the next day and - and Morgan said to me - mummy, I'm sure God has something to do for our - our Gwyn, he said, because you see he nearly died in the hospital. I'm sure God's got something for hi
m to do. And our Gwyn, when we tell Gwyn that now, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Morgan must have been a thinking child then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh he was. He was. YES. Yes, the minister always thought he would have been a - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any medical help when you were having the children? What about with Morgan and Margaret, would you have any medical help?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. I don't remember if I had to send for the doctor. At all. Although when - when Gwyn was born Doctor - Doctor Davis wasn't willing - that the - midwife didn't send for
 - for him. Because he said I - I - that could have been fatal, he said. And he wasn't willing I said - well I thought it was the - it was the midwife's work to send for the doctor you see, of course I was quite - didn't know much about it then but - yes,
 yes, yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your husband help?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mm? Well no, keep him out of the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He didn't help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, it's very strange - for they were - the men were - at that time were not supposed to be were they? They don't mind now do they. B
ut it was quite enough, I'd rather be on my own and get through with it - on my own. Oh yes. As - that's one fault they tell me about me, I'm too independent. But there you are, no you can't help your nature can you. What\rquote 
s to be borne by myself has got to be borne by myself and there you are. I don't want to give anybody any trouble in any way. I've always been - funny like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember how soon you were out of bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I couldn't - it was usually about ten or eleven days. Yes, I'd be ab
out because the - the children was - well now when I had that gathered breast I - I got up too soon then I think and went about because - the little ones you see, the - to be seen to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember how long you would have stayed in bed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well, I'd be - oh I'll - be getting up after tea you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You don't remember how many days you'd actually stay in bed without getting up at all
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - usually it would be about ten, yes, but now the time of the war you see, it was well ever
ything was - although everybody was very kind, there was an old lady living here - old Mrs Storey, Annie Storey's mother, and I remember her coming in to see me and bringing her ration of sugar for me. She said I needed it more than she did. And giving me
 her ration of sugar. It was an awful time, time of the war, butter was so scarce and - sugar, the things that you really needed. Yes. They were very scarce then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you manage while you were in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - oh well you see my - my mothe
r-in-law used to come up for a week or so. And she'd stay here for the first week. And then - she'd go well of course daddy would be - would be with the children and - once I had a girl here too. When - when Margaret was born I think that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would she be a nurse or just a girl to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh a girl to help in the house this was, yes. She was here once. But I - I never used to have - I used to have somebody to help to do the washing. Yes. Yes, someone to do the washing, I'd manage then
, and that meant something you see, the little ones and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would it be a relative or would it be somebody you'd pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Probably it would be a relative would do the washing, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever have a nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Nurse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Midwife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, she was the nurse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 For how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well, her time would be ten days you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That was only the midwife would help you with the delivery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would she do anything for the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well, used to come and wash them every day you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feed your first baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Let me see. Oh I - I think - I fed Morgan and Margaret myself. And started on olwen. But - had to give it up. I had to give up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But the first baby was Morgan, and you fed him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you enjoy feeding the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well I - I - I didn't mind the babies, I - oh no. You felt that they were your own somehow, you felt - you felt nearer somehow the baby - and you fed the baby yourself, but I wasn't strong enough. Mm. Mm. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you use then instead?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well - I used to have milk from Margam you see from the farm. Yes, from the farm next to my home. Kept the same - kept the milk every day, from the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any difficulties in feeding?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Only Eiddwen, and you didn't feed her at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. No. No, and I had to get of course Gwyn then when I had the gathered breast, I started - then - he couldn't take cows milk, so I started - and the min - the mi
nister's wife came here, Mr Rhys - Mrs Rhys and she said, why don't you try Glaxo? Because he couldn't - well I thought of course - we thought that we were going to lose Gwyn. And - I started on Glaxo. And indeed it made a marked difference, and Glaxo he 
h
ad, and Glaxo Eiddwen had. Good people now my mother-in-law was very keen on keeping the children on the breast you see. Very keen. And now - and - but then Doctor Davies came here and he asked me - if I had a - been feeding the baby myself. I said, yes, 
w
ell I told you not to he said, he was very cross. You must - you must - you mustn't listen to every old wives tale, he said. They think they know, he said, but they don't know everything. So then I stopped then, but oh nearly lost Gwyn. Nearly. He was a v
e
ry delicate baby. And Morgan is a very delicate child. Very delicate. Morgan was delicate until he - well - even when he went to Trevecca college, used to bring him home sometimes. Yes. And he couldn't - and when he was in Aberystwyth - he was sitting his
 exams, his final exams you know, well - he had - and in one exam, the Hebrew exam I think it was, they had to take him out, they couldn't - couldn't go - and yet he won a scholarship to Oxford. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 With Morgan did you have any difficulties in feeding him when he was a baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, not much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 If you needed advice about things then who did you ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well of course my sister was alive then you see down Penycae, my sister, yes. She was there then. And she was - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 If the baby was a sleep would you wake it for a feed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - oh I don't think I would. I'd let \lquote em sleep if they'd sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 If they cried before the normal time would you feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well there you are, you\rquote d have to - stop it to cry of course. Yes.
 Oh yes. You had to use your judgement, every child wasn't the same. Whereas one child would be like this the other one would be the other way. You had to study them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you do if the baby didn't seem hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well of course had to - had to seek medical advice then. Yes. If he was off his food.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long did you let it go on feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I don't know - they'd know when they'd had enough I suppose. I don't remember exactly now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you remember when you first gave it solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well, they used to - they didn't have solid food until they were about a year old then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go on feeding them until they were a year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Usually they'd be wee - be weened then you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How would you mean them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I'd take them off gradually and - and give them solid food. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They'd be about a year old probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, or nine, ten months, eleven, that way. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So it would be gradual would it, not sudden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was sudden with Gwyn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, I had to. Poor little chap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He hadn't been weened before you went to hospital?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, but he was - of course he was on - on the bottle you see, hadn't been weened off his bot - he hadn't been weened because he 
was so delicate you see. And he went off bottle and all. Up to the hospital. Oh dear -, they were thrilled to have a baby there. But the baby was - he was three days unconscious. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When you did wean the baby, did the baby mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - they wer
en't willing at first you see. Of course - because of course if they could - if they could take enough solid food well - the - the kind of solid food we'd give them you know - different food you see, Cow and - no, I didn't give them Cow and Gate, I gave t
hem Glaxo. It was very good for them. I don't hear anything about Glaxo now. And I've never been worried with any stomach troubles. No. No indigestion or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you think at the time that it did harm to a baby to let it cry or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I - I couldn't stand the baby crying. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you think it did any harm to the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes. Yes. I didn't - I didn't - some would leave the babies cry - dear I remember the babies round here now, they'd be left out in the pram, and they'd be crying oh dear, I couldn't stand it. No, I could never stand them crying. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would you do if they were crying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Pick them up. That's the - same - the same with Mirran. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you punish the baby when it was naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well no, not a baby. Very little punishing I did. Very - if I'd give them a smack it's I would be worried, not them. I'd be crying if they go to bed if I'd given them a smack in the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 For what would you give them a smack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well if they'd been 
naughty of course. Well I don't know, don't remember - very much. They wouldn't do much and they wouldn't get a very big smack, but it used to hurt me more than it used to hurt them. Very little. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How much did your husband have to do with your children when they were babies under one year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well of course there was not much he could do then you see and - and he was always working, so then - oh no, I used to - see to them myself. Nurse them of course sometimes, oh yes, he loved the babies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did he feed them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, not much. \lquote Til they came on, were able to - eat something you know and perhaps - give them the bottle, oh yes, it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he give them the bottle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he bath them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, no. No, I always bathed them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Change their nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. I used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Play with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, he'd play with them. Carry them on his back around the house and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he get them to sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes, he'd get them to sleep too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he attend to them in the night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Sometimes. Yes. All depended - what time he'd come home from work, if he was very very tired or - it depended of course if they were ill well there you are we were both - we were both on call then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he take them out without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - yes, sometimes in the day. If he'd happen to be home you see but very little time he had. Very little. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I wonder how you managed the housekeeping in those years before 1919. Did you know what your husband earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How much of that would he give to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well he put it all - he give it all. It was all put down. And I used to do a little bit of - bit of sewing perhaps and make an occasional quilt or - or if I did - one or tw
o children music lessons and it would all help. But I used to do all their sewing. I used to do all the washing. Everything in the house. Did all the sewing that - every - no, I didn't knit very much but - only what I'd knit all little suits you know, but
 - I did all the sewing, the boys and the girls. Their dresses, their coats, their hats. Remember when Margaret went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cardiff{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - University - she said to me, mummy - can I have a coat from the shop now? It was the first coat from the shop father. I used to
 make all their clothes - And people used to tell me that they looked like fairies, I used to make their bonnets and all you know. It was - hard work but it was worth while. And - teach them, all I could. In every way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you discuss with your husband how the money would be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well we knew exactly what it - where everything went you see, oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How many rooms were there in the house at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Tanygroes Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} here now isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, this is the one yes. Yes. Three up. And three down. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were there any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. But - somebody came here and - a niece of Mr Mainwaring's came, she was married and - and the - and they didn't have the - or they couldn't get the house or something, they were here for a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh wait a bit, no. Not that was in - no, that was in 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was it during the war or after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. It was - let me see now, it was after Eiddwen was born. Yes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 This period we are talking about there was only you and Mr Mainwaring and the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes, and the children. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Couldn't afford it then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh it was done at home, every - always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You mentioned earlier that you made the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And mended of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they be new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I used to make everything for them. And then they used to come down one to the other you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When would they have new clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well usually now of course - they had their clothes for the winter and their clothes for the summer and - used to have new clothes - for the summer of course, and they used to co
me down from one to the other, I remember Eiddwen asking me one day mummy, when shall I have a frock of my own? Instead of one after our Olwen. Yes, she - well it was new shoes, because they got their shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They'd have bought new shoes_?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Well they'd have new shoes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That they wouldn't have hand downs of shoes would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would Mr Mainwring help you with jobs in the house, with cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't know about
 cooking but - helped the cleaning of course what he could do, but he was very handy in that, we used to do all our own painting and papering. Everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That was a help wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I papered these rooms many times. And - we want to do our green
 house now. I want you to see the flowers there. And - and I remember doing the wall, colouring the wall, I was telling daddy yesterday morning - we were talking about having the painter here. I can't - I can't see myself now, I said, up on top of the lad
der doing that wall. And he used to do all the painting. He does the painting outside now. Yes. Yes. We've always done it. Until the last few years of course, we've had to - get the papering done. Oh I can't now. I can't now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would Mr Mainwaring do any repairs that were needed to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well if there's any repairs that he could do you see because - he was a blacksmith used to do many little things, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well we'd - we have improved of course.
 We made a study of the little room you see, for the children to have - well my brother came here to live with me, he was a minister, so he had a study of that, he made a study of that, I think it's the only one in the street that's closed in. And it's a 
- a very cosy room of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mr Mainwaring did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, he didn't, it was a - my nephew did that. Penycae.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was quite a big job wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. Oh yes. And made all the shelves you see, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the fires, who would make the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well he'd light the fire in the morning. Before he'd go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he wash up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well not so much then, he washes up now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Got him well trained now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the washing in those days, you must have had an awful lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. The - washing every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he help with the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, he couldn't wash then, help with the washing, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he help with the children at all, dress them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, all he could, yes. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he bath them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I - not so much bathing them. He would help you see. Help through and through whatever it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he read aloud to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, sometimes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he tell them stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, well -
 if he'd be - reading stories you see, he'd - tell them and - used to do more of that with Sue and Jane, the grandchildren. Yes. There you are, yes, used to read line upon line and all this you know. Oh, used to love to granpa read.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would your husband take the children out without you when they were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. Take them down to Margam to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would he look after the children when you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well yes, otherwise I wouldn't have been able to do what I did in the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You were telling me you went on straight away more or less didn't you after the children were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You continued with your work did you all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes, well I - I had to take over the Band of Hope - in about four years
. Margaret, Morgan was five years, there you are. Morgan was - Morgan was five and Margaret was four - when I took over the Band of Hope and I used to have the children here - I couldn't go down there except one night a week you see, vestry full of childr
en, on - Tuesday nights, but I used to do - most of their work was done here. In this house. Yes. \lquote Cos that room wasn't closed in then. It was in there and it was the organ I had you see, and I used to do all the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You had the organ here in the house, you could do all the practicing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Always have, yes, always. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did you find the time to compose and write the plays and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well there you are. I - I was late going to bed and early getting up. YES. And composing has alwa
ys come natural to me. It was the time to write it out. Write everybody's part you see. Used to write all their parts out and I used to make the dreams and things. Everybody's part was written out of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mr Mainwaring then had to look after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes. Yes, he used to take - charge of the baby or the girls, but the big girls that would be would look after the baby for me, while I was teaching the others. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did the children have any regular household tasks to help you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well of course when they came older enough, they - they had to wash up and - and - and do the dusting and something like you see. Each one has his little job. And clean the knives and forks and - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What time would the children go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well, between six and seven somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they be put to bed by themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well no, I was always taking them to bed and it was then they were learning their their psalms and - and verses and - always go to bed and - about half an hour I s
pent with them. Teaching them. The psalms and so on, oh yes. Just before they go to - go to sleep you see, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you teach them something every night or would it be just ready for the Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - it was a regular thing. Yes. They were
 used to it and they were used to saying grace before every meal. And Gwyn used to say - thank God for my good food please may I leave the table, and by the time Gwyn was saying table he'd be under the table and out you see. Not much time about it. But th
e
y always - always said grace. And they say the same now. And - when we were all together now - Margaret and Morgan and - we say the same now. And on Sunday night when we have family prayers - they say the same - same prayers that they used to say when the
y
 were children. When we are with them. Oh - Eiddwen looks forward to getting us there. For family prayers. And Morgan the same, oh yes. How we were brought up, that's how I brought them up very - you know, very happy, they knew they had to do it but they 
never - never questioned - no, they never questioned about going to Sunday school and chapel. Never, they knew the - it was expected of them and there you are Part of their lives. And - they're glad today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did the children share a bedroom or bed at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well they had to you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember how it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes, well now then - it one - of course one would be - the baby would be with us you see. And then - then we'd have two beds in the - we'd have a bed in the other room and a bed in the - other room. And now we've made a bathroom of the back room you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You had Morgan and Gwyn together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And Morgan and Gwyn would be together and Olwen and - and Margaret, yes, yes, and the baby with us. Yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What room did you use for bathing in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I bathed them - kitchen in front of the fire. Big bath in front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When would they have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Saturday night. Oh they had - there was two on Saturday night, all the clothes would be ready - hangi
ng on the line. By the fire, ready for Sunday morning. All their clean underclothes and - socks and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where were meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where were meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh in the kitchen. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well it all depended if we had a preacher staying here or - anybody coming here, we saw the preacher often - very often on Sunday. We used to - go in the middle room then you see. Bigger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did you cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh out of - of
 course I had a back kitchen as well you see. We made a back kitchen - ourselves after we came here. And then that was used as a kitchen then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What cooking equipment did you have, a gas cooker then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not then. We didn't have gas then. We had the - we had the - grate, the - coal fires then you see. Coal fires, both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When would breakfast be eaten then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh about eight to half past. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What members of the family were present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well they would all be there then. Daddy would come home by half past eight to have breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He'd be gone out earlier would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. He would be gone out by seven, six or seven you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you get up with him or would he get himself off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I'd be - he'd get up and - some - well, 
it all depended, bring me a cup of tea if I wasn't up to the mark. But he'd be coming home at - by half past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He wouldn't have breakfast before he went out would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, not at the beginning, no. No. Used to come home by half past eight. A
nd then I'd have the children - all having breakfast and - and getting ready for school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mr Mainwaring would just have a cup of tea or something would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Before he went out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you have usually to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - tea, and porridge they used to have you know and toast or whatever it would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have anything different on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I don't think so - I don't think they would have anything - different, or perhaps they'd have an egg sometimes you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I made a dinner every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would everybody be present then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, yes. Unless daddy would have to - work, and then one of the children would have to take his - dinner d
own to him, and in that case, I'd make dinner in the evening. If he was coming home to dinner I'd make dinner dinnertime, but for years for years I made dinner in the evening. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was that when the children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, well when they were small and when they were growing up you see they used to take his - dinner him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would you have lunch time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well, we'd have cold meat or whatever would be going you see, or - make something for them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd make the main meal in the evening would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The main - dinner would be in the evening then. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would you usually have to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - what meal do you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 For dinner, oh the - the dinner. Oh well, meat of course
, fresh meat, soup, vegetables pudding. Rice pudding or - bread and butter pudding or - fruit, I saw plenty of fruit from - from the garden from Margam. And I used to make a plenty of jam, and - then I used to - to store fruit myself you see. Gooseberries
 
and blackcurrants and - always had plenty of fruit, I used to store it. I used to bottle them you see. But - sometimes I'd make sixty pounds of jam perhaps from the garden yes, so I didn't have then - I didn't have to buy well now - we used to raise all -
 all our potatoes and vegetables - in Margam. In the garden there, and the garden here of course used to - plenty of vegetables and fruit always. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you ever buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Very seldom. In the winter perhaps but - while there would be - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have different meals on certain days? Like Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well of course it was a - it was a better joint on Sundays. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd have it midday then would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh midday then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you ever have it in the evening on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. No. Oh no, not in the evening, always midday then. Yes, because daddy would be working - every Sunday - for twenty-five years he worked every Sunday morning. And then used to come to Sunday school. Used to shave - wash and change - din
ner be ready, and he'd - come with me and the children to Sunday school. Then if a - one of them was very small I - stay in with them on Sunday night. And they used to play chapel in the house. That was Sunday night. And Morgan was always preaching on top
 of the chair. And Margaret was sitting on the stool and playing the piano on the chair. I used to play - I used to play the violin with them. Because we were in the kitchen then you see. And it was too cold to be in the front room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you make bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, I used to make all - I used to make everything then. Make bred, cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Everything, and pickles. Anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - elderberry wine, and ginger wine I used to make a lot of - in the winter you see. And elderberry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Only the ginger -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Diodfaen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh the diodfaen, well of course that was then because we used to - go to Margam and - and gather the - whatever we'd want you see, all the leaves I'd want in - nettles and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you make it of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I used - yes, blackcurrant leaves - and - nettles. And dandelions. And - and of course I put ginger in it always. But - the blackcurrant leaves used to find - and the dandelion. And - elder. All those leaves we used to fin
d then, and nettles I used to find very good too. Boil them all down. Oh yes, I used to make ginger - diodfaen every week. Yes. Well - you couldn't go and buy then you see the - big family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you make any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I used to 
make all the medicine when they'd have a cold I used to mix - honey - and vinegar, and - butter, and sugar of course but - honey mostly, and what else, I used to put something else. Glycerine. And vinegar. Well I used to mix that. And put it by the fire, 
and blackcurrant after I used to give them a lot of that. And elder. Elderberry, used to gather them you see. Everything we could gather. Yes, I used to make all those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you bottle vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I didn't bottle vegetables. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have any tinned vegetables or tinned fruit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not then. Not then. Never knew what it was then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. But I remember having - dried peaches. The time of the war. I remember they came on the market. I used
 to - buy dried peaches. I think that was about the only thing - \lquote 
cos we had plenty of apples you see and - used to buy oranges Christmas time of course. And pears, but - otherwise - we didn't used to buy much of anything that way. Nothing I could make myself. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was there any livestock kept for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well we didn't - we did keep fowls here for a while. Chickens. But of course we were having them from Margam you see. We were having the chickens from - because grandma used to - she used to have a lot of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would look after them when you had them here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 We didn't - oh I - well - we were never from here - I think Morgan was eighteen before we ever went on a - on a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who looked after the hens when you had them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh it was I was looking after them. Oh I was looking after them, three or four of them that's all. Yes. Only they were a help too for eggs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - we used to have meat three or four times - in some from 
or other. But - we used to have a pig you see, up in - in grandma's, we had a pig and then - we used to - have that pig and salt it and then we - we'd have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You didn't actually keep it here, there was a pig for you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was a pig there you see. And - then we used to have - perhaps I'd bring half of it here to be salted you see and - perhaps I'd -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That would be Mr Mainwaring's mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. Yes. Because we used to buy the pig and - leave it there and - and if there was any re
fuse here it was taken up there. But there was plenty of stuff from the garden there you see. To give to the pig.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I don't remember ever buying tinned meat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have any extra meat from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 To catch hares and - pheasants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They wouldn't allow you, but they'd allow you to get rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes. Every farmer could - have as many rabbits as he could catch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have them often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Oh no, I was getting tired of - I used to get tired of chickens when I was home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about when you were here in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Tanygroes Street
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} with the children young, would you have rabbit then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 On occasion had one. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But it wouldn't be poaching really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh dear, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You wouldn't have any hares or pheasants would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever go short so that your husband and the children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - sometimes I'm afraid. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did Mr Mainwaring need to have larger helpings of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not much, he has never been a - a very big eater. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were the children allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - not - not al - no, they didn't make it a habit of talking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Could they choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Or did they have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well there you are, if it was put there - for them and they ate it and there was no - I knew exactly what suited them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you serve the food then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well there you are - out it - on each plate of course. Yes. Oh every one had enough, they all had enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What was your attitude if some of the food was left uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well there we are, if they couldn't eat it they co
uldn't - I never quarrelled with them - about their food. I knew exactly what each one liked. And how much. And I put for them. What they could - I knew - one could eat more than the other, the other - the other one would eat very little, I knew exactly w
hat put on their - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Would the children have to wait until things on the table were offered to them or could they ask, for the salt or the pepper? Could they ask for them to be passed to them or would they have to wait until they were offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well, I don't know. Don't remember much about that. Probably they would ask - if they wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, if they wanted it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Could they hold their knife and fork in a certain way, did they have to or did they have to sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well, they had to sit straight of course - by the table, but I don't remember - much about their - knife and fork, they used to grow in those things you see. You didn't have to tell them, preach to them. They grew in them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were they allowed to bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, not then, not with - not with the meals. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When did members of the family leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well when they were all finished you see. But - as I 
was telling you - Gwyn would say please may I leave the table, oh they would ask of course, thank God for my good food. Please my I leave the table? Then they would - have to go of course. But Gwyn was out. Oh dear, dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did all the family present for the meal sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they have the same places round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You can't remember how you sat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 We had a - I remember we had a seat, that they were - renewing Penycae chapel then. And they were sel
ling the seats. And we bought the seat. Enough to hold four, and we put it in front of the window, where the table is now. The table is now, in front of the window. And then there'd be four of them sitting there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The four of them sat there in a pew really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where would you sit then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And we'd be - dad usually at one end you see and I'd be at the other end and the baby with a high chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where would the baby be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. She'd be in a high chair with me you see at the other side. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about when the children were too young to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - oh dear -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I would feed them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When would they join in the family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - they'd sit on the hig
h chair when they'd come to sit in the high chair you see. Of course when they were babies I had to - to nurse them certainly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When your children were young did you feel there was a right way and a wrong way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well
 - I don't know, we tried to bring them up the right way. Tried to - to be - and to study one another, and especially to speak the truth. That was a big thing with us, always - maintain that. Never could stand - you know, you knew where you were you see. 
And I never had any trouble. Never.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you and your husband have the same ideas about bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - oh no, I think we were pretty well the same. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you talk about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't - no, I don't think so. Bu
t there you are, they did - well they knew they had to do - they knew what to do you see. Of course if - they were naughty sometimes like every child, there never was a child that wasn't naughty. No. They had to be reprimanded sometimes. But - very little
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh I don't know, no. No. No, I never did like to take - our affairs outside the house. Never. I was friendly with everybody in - up and down the street. But I never us
ed to go to their houses and they never used to come here, unless - if there was something the matter, and I could do something, as I did many times, they came to fetch me or something like that, but - I never made it a habit. Never. And I never had a cro
s
s word with anyone. All the years we were here, and the other day last Saturday we were in - Annie's golden wedding here. Annie Storey was saying - and - they were the first to come here, and we were - we were the only ones that are here now. And her moth
er - was - was here when we came here. We're the only ones left in Tanygroes Street. And talked about her. And we were saying now, how wonderful it was that we could say - that we had been here over sixty years, and never had a cross word. Yes. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Your mother wasn't alive when your children were small, what about your mother-in-law, she was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 She was alive you see. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh she used to come nearly every week. And we used to go up there, of course da
ddy used to go up you see to - see to the garden and those things, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ask her advice on bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well no, I don't remember that I did. We had to - mark out our own paths then. Things were getting different then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you and she have the same ideas on how to bring up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I don't know, perhaps we didn't always. No. We've been brought - well you see I had been brought up - differently and - not exactly, but we never had a cross word. Never fee
l out - on anything. No. I've always - left well alone. She had her way, I let her have her way. And it was the wisest plan. I was younger, she was older. And she had lost her husband and brought up a family, and I knew that she knew - what I didn't know.
 And then I - I gave her - her way, and I never disputed anything. If she wanted to say something - well I let her say and I didn't dispute at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would she give you any advice on bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well if she - sometimes she'd say some
thing, I wouldn't say anything, perhaps I wouldn't agree but I wouldn't - disagree, I wouldn't say anything. It was better to keep the peace. You see. Yes. I've always been a peacemaker somehow. Always loved peace. I can't stand cross words you know, I'm 
an awful coward. I'm a terrible coward. Oh dear yes I am, always been a coward that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Could you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do dor your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well I don't know. I wish I could have - well I did my best to educate th
em in every way. But I wish I could have given them more mind. But otherwise I don't think we could have - I don't think we could have done better, we did all we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you want them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh they used to do that. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well there you are, truthful. Truthful and - but I didn't mind, as long as I knew exactly what worried them. If any - there was any worry but - they used to - oh yes. Yes, it was - everyt
hing was open, we were - we were just one family, and they're the same now. Never - never a cross word.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the safety of the children in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Used to go out to the play with the children. Oh yes. Yes, used to go out to play with t
hem - with some children, but - I used to prefer them bringing their friends and playing her in the back - where I could see them, and they used to make a tent out there and - that's why - we did - we had the greenhouse mostly, how I - they used to play s
c
hool there, oh the children were place there, never saw such a - such a racket as there was. Oh yes, they used to bring the children in. And Olwen used to have a hospital, she used to make a - a tent of sheets and all the rest of it, out the back. Yes, th
ey brought the children in here. I preferred them bringing them in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When the children were young did you and Mr Mainwaring both ever manage to leave them so that you could go out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember. Well the only once or twice we would go there w
ould be - to some funerezl or - something like that you know. Otherwise we never went to - or perhaps to some - some certain meeting perhaps we'd go. But otherwise to any - amusement or anything like that, never. No, we never went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How would you manage then, would somebody come in to look after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well it probably - oh my sister or sometone'd be here you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 A relative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. I never leave them with a stranger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about older children when the children got older, would you leave the older ones in charge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well, but the older children perhaps would - would be able to do it if we went to - a meeting somewhere in our - chapels, something like that. Otherwise that was the only thing we used to do. Only places we used to go. We never went anywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you leave the children in the house and have somebody to look in occasionally at them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Or would you have someone listening from elsewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you leave them in with nobody responsible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, no. Oh no. No, I don't remember ever doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, they never did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I think the most important thing was to - well live good lives, live - Christ - well acc - according to the - Christian way, we had tried to bring them - tried to teach them. That's the most important thing in life is to be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you tell them they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't remember much about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were there any other children you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, they didn't used to go with
 - anyone. Well I don't know - to me a child is a child. They are not all the same way, if - if they hadn't been brought up the same way as my children well I couldn't help that. But - you couldn't - teach a child to look down at any child. A child is a c
hild.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 So you wouldn't stop them from playing with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 If the children did something you disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well it all depended on - how much did it merit or if it merited a - a smack or a - or be reprimanded of course and shown the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would punish them, you or Mr Mainwaring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well, I don't know, I had very little punishment they had. Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you both punish them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well - very very few times I used to give them a smack sometimes. Very few smacks they had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember any particular occasion when you punished them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No, I don't remember - I remember once - punishing Morgan - for going for a walk down the docks after chapel on Sunday morning, instead of coming home. Went with another boy. I remember giving him a couple of smacks then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did he think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well the idea, you see, they had so few - that the idea of being punished - hurt more than the - then the punishment itself. The idea.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you 
say that your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from both parents, or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - oh I don't know, no, I think that - it was the way they saw life, you see, as it was. Yes. It was here. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You did a little work after you were married but it was always at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Oh no, I never went out, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Some people think that children should be with the mother all the time, others think that it is not necessary and it 
does them good to be with other people quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you think at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I don't - definitely not. I think the child should be with - the mother should be with the child. Until the child is old enough to - to know - what is right and what is wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 About how old would you think that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I don't know, it all - some children are - are children when they are twelve, others are grown up. There's such a - such a difference in them. And they begin to go out y
ou know to - school or go away to school or - makes a difference then, they have to stand on their own feet, well - if they've been brought up properly they know they - know then what is expected of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When your children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes. They'd have a birthday whatever. And they'd bring all the - all the - form in with them if they should. They'd bring all the children in school. I remember we didn't have any teaspoons to go round once when Olwen
 was about three - oh, yes, they all - oh dear, dear, they had picked out their friends to come to the birthday party. The - the children in the - in the class - will be - they'd be telling 01 - Olwen or whichever it would be - we're coming to the party. 
Not waiting to be asked Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would the children have presents on their birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, they'd have a present you see, a little present we could afford of course, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they have anything different to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh they'd have 
a birthday tea and a birthday cake and - yes. Always a birthday cake. I used to have to make - six birthday cakes you see in the year. I never bothered about myself of course. I used to make six and - yes. Dear dear.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Can you remember anything you did with your husband and the children on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well Christmas Day was mostly spent in chapel. Christmas Day was mostly spent in chapel. Childrens concert and all the rest of it, or I'd be preparing. They'd be down putting a stage, daddy used t
o go down, and Morgan, to put up the stage in the afternoon. Chapel in the morning and then they'd be down there. We'd have dinner. And then they - and the Christmas tree, we always had a Christmas tree. Oh yes. Always had a Christmas tree. And then they'
d be preparing for the - there'd be a concert in the night in Groes Place. Fore years and years and years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I had the organ when I was twenty one, it's here now. In the study now. And a violin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would play in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well of course Olwen had learnt to play the vi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5388354\charrsid11040510 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  children learnt to play the organ. Well that's where they learnt to play was on the organ you see. We had a piano after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Up to 1918 it would be just you would be the player?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, I'd be playing the organ and the violin then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did any of you sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh the children were, yes, the children were all singing. Children were good - Margaret was especially good singer, she won a gold medal for singing. Yes. Yes. Yes. About fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever make music together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh we were always singing. Yes, and any friends come here now, especially boys - and girls come, boys coming with Morgan, oh dear they were here \lquote til twelve o'clock on Sunday night singing. Always singing here, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You had the children here practicing too didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And oh - dear dear, choirs of children in here. Yes indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever play any games with the children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, they always had games, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you play with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well if I could. Snakes and ladders or whatever it would be. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would Mr Mainwaring join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Or would he play different games with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well, play with the children you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were there books, newspapers, magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh yes. Well there were books, the childrens books you see, that was the present Christmas time was - the Girls Own Paper and the Boys Own Paper, and - and all those you know and - babies books and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Newspapers, did you take a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Used to have - he's always had the Western Mail. At that time it was the South Wales Daily News. After that it was the Western Mail. And I remember he used to have John Bull once. And th
e children used to have childrens - newspaper. Remember the childrens newspaper? And the girls own paper. Boys own paper. Oh they used to have those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you have any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well those were the only magazines we had you see. I wouldn't bot
her because - very little time I had for reading or - most of my time would go for writing for something or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did you get the books and newspapers and the magazines from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh in a shop up here you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you belong to a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I used to get an occasional - well I tell you I used to - go up - well, every week, two or three times a week sometimes, I used to go round the different churches speaking the Sisterhood you know, and if there was anything I wanted - special p
erhaps I'd have a book from the library and see what somebody else had to say on the subject you see. But - that was the only -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you read aloud to each other or to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. There wasn't much time for that. Daddy used to read and - - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were the children taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh they were taken to see their relations of course, wherever we'd go the children would go of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who would take them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I would take them, oh yes, and daddy would take them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were they taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh when well I had to take them shopping of course to buy something for them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did the children ever go out with just their father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I expect they did go down to Ma
rgam you see down to grandma's. Used to go then. Their turn. Morgan used to go with him. To the garden you know and - and Margaret, they used to pick fruit. Now this time of the year you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you do on Bank Holidays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well we used to take them down to the beach. And - or we would go up to Margam, it would be either of those, up to my old home - or to - Mr Mainwaring's home, or perhaps we'd go down the beach. But on - Bank Holiday now, Easter - the bluebells would be ou
t
 - in the woods, and I used to take them up to the bluebell patch, up by the old monastery you know, my favourite little spot, used to have a picnic up there. That was - into the middle of the bluebells, used to roll in the middle of the bluebells you kno
w
. Those were the things that our children had, they were all nature, it was all. And of course I had always been - I had sat so many hours up by the old monastery you know, and I knew every tree and every - I knew ever branch that was there, everything, e
very rock that was there you see. I used to wander around. I was a terrible wanderer when I was a child. Always wandering around the woods. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever go away for a holiday before the end of the first world war when you had the children young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I think we went down to Carmarthenshire - once. Once or twice, we went down there to my cousins. To the farm where I used to stay you know. And we went to - we went to Island House, Lacher, to May's home. But May was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}Africa{\*\xmlclose} and a missionary then. A
nd she was about coming home. I - we went there - May had come home I remember, and the river used to come up to the banks you know, just outside the house. And I remember, oh the children of course, the river there, and Margaret going and - into the rive
r of course. And now the problem was because - we didn't have any small - socks to put on her, and May bringing a pair of her - her stockings now, I don't know whether she brought them from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Africa{\*\xmlclose}
 for one of the children. But do you think Margaret would put them on? No. She wouldn't. Oh she wouldn't. I remember that very well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you go every year for a holiday regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No, we went - used to go up to my home or - the children perhaps would go but - we never made it a - the first time 
we went for a holiday together was - down to Marcross, and Morgan was eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That's a long time after 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes. And now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go at all when the children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go away during the war at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. We didn't go anywhere is the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go away with the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Before Morgan was about ten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No, we didn't. I don't remember going - I don't remember going as a family, only down to - Carmarthen you know, used to go to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Carmarthen{\*\xmlclose}. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 To stay with a cousin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How long would you go for then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh a week or a fortnight you see, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why did you go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I'd been used to going there you see, yes. When I was young, and I - used to go down there every year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd all go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And they let you take all the children and - and Mr Mainwaring would take us down and he'd come and fetch us back. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He wouldn't stay with you down there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What would you do down there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well on the farm you see, the children. Children were delighted of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you spend Saturday in those days? When you had the children very small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well the children were home of course fr
om school and - prepare for Sunday - on Saturday, be doing everything - ready for Sunday. And do the shopping and - clean and you know that was the old - everybody did that then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well chapel Sunday you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you manage when you had the children small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
I used to take them. I used to take them all, take the baby. Get up early on Sunday morning. And as I tell you everything was ready Saturday night, for them to put on. All their clean clothes. Then I'd dress the
 baby first, I'd roll him up and put him on the - on the table while I was dressing the others. It would be him or her or whenever it - whichever it would be, roll up the baby, I used to take them all on Sunday morning. I remember there was a man up there
,
 living up here, I don't remember his name, but I can see the man now, and he was supposed to be a man that didn't believe much - in religion. He had no room for religion. And - so I had been told and I thought it was an awful thing. But how - I was comin
g
 up from chapel on a Sunday morning, I was carrying the baby in a shawl, and I had - I think I had three little ones, I think Gwyn was the baby then, yes. I know I was carrying the baby and had the little ones with me whichever, and this man used to sell 
m
ilk. And he stopped the - the - the dray with the horse, just by me, and he said, a sight like this, he said, does a man's eyes good. I thought it was such a strange thing to say And - from him. And I was pondering, I was wondering. And indeed - oh in a l
o
ng while after that - I was told that that man had died in - in a service in chapel. Yes. It seemed now as if - the sight of the children - of a family going to church on a Sunday morning. And that's what he said, a sight like this, he said, does a man's 
eyes good. A funny thing to say wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you or the children put on different clothes on Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Different clothes? Oh yes. There was always best clothes then. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you think it wrong to work or enjoy yourself on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I'm afraid we did. My father wouldn't allow the boys to whistle to the dogs. He wouldn't allow them to shout to the horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about you when you had your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And I was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You didn't think it didn't matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - 
no, we never did any sewing, I - I don't now. Any sewing, we shouldn't use the scissors at all. And I am the same now, I don't like to see any - anything done on a Sunday now. But - very - as little as possible of - work done on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you allow your children to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, not on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Denomination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh the Presbyterian. Welsh Presbyterian.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How often would you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well, when we could, I'd go thr
ee times. Of course when I had the baby I couldn't go in the night. I used to go twice then. And three or four times in the week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your husband attend too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. We belonged to the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did the chapel run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No, I did you see, I did, I ran a - Band of Hope, temperance, and temperance examinations. And they used to sit - and we won the silver cup for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}South Wales{\*\xmlclose}
 three times, from the - yes. Yes, and our children won many prizes. Many.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What activities did the temperance club have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well we had - concerts you see and then they had - conferences and - we had teas. And - and then there used to be the - temperance queen. And - what did we - well, all 
sorts of activities and then we used to have the - prize givings, that was a very big affair. Very - yes, prizes, for the best, for the - for the ones that had passed the exams you know and - and then we'd have some people down - from head - quarters - to
 speak, oh yes, you - and marching of course with our banners and - and the blue ribbons. You belong to that - the temperance - the temperance children marching, sing temperance boys and girls are we. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Round the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes, I remember that very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would that be once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes, there would be a - a conference and certain people would come down to speak and - and we would go - to these - big does after, I remember going to the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5388354\charrsid11040510 Brangwyn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  Hall. There was a very big do there of the temperance. All the churches round. Oh yes, it was - very - and our children in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Groes Place{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} well they did - they did wonderful work with temperance. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you belong to any other clubs organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well only the Sunday sch
ool exams again you see. They used to pass those. I tell you I - used to take me all the year between the - between all the exams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about womens activities in the chapel, were there any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, the - the missionaries you see, missionary meetings, the Sisterhood and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go to those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Oh yes. Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You mentioned that the children went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did they go to any adult services at the chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They went to them all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you take them in the week nights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, they used to go - with their new verses - every Wednesday night, yes. Well - our minister used to look for it you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You mentioned earlier that you had family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When would you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well always on Sunday night. Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were your children taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who taught them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well, we taught them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Both of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not just you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, both of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Not very much, I didn't. No. Well you see - in Margam everybody was a Liberal. And we never thought of anything else but Liberal you see so I didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about when you moved up here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I didn't bother with politics at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What were your views then when you came up here?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't know - I - my views were the same as they'd be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember voting, there was a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. I expect I did. Who did we vote for, I don't remember now. Oh I expect it would be Lloyd George or somebody - somebody like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It would be Liberal. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why do you think your views were Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't know, well that's how we'd been taught you see, that was - that's all we'd been -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about Mr Mainwaring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh he was the same of course. But because Mr David was, he was working for Mr David you see. D.R. David and they were Liberals
, Liberals, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you think your husband felt under any pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Because Mr David was a Liberal do you think he felt obliged to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't think so. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever work for one of the parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 At an election,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Mr Mainwaring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When you and Mr Mainwaring were not doing your work how did you spend your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't know whether - I don't remember any time that I wasn't working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Such a hive of activity in the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And here you were composing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Oh yes, always composing. YES. Always work in the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you still writing poetry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. And writing dramas for the children you see and - teaching them. Yes. I was always full of work. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever go out together in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not unless we were going to a meeting or taking the children or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When did your husband get home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well it all depended. His work - time was at half past five. But many a time - he'd send up for his tea and he'd be working \lquote 
til ten. Many a time. And then I remember about - if something happened in the works, somebody would come knocking at the door, half past two perhaps in the morning or three. Such and such a thing h
as happened in the work, he'd have to go. Out of bed. I didn't mind it except that the children were ill, and then I didn't like him to be going and leaving me. No. But many a time I heard - heard the knock at the door, at the window. Many many times. He 
had to go. And I say - some of the men that are making all this fuss today, ought to be living then. And making a living then. Bringing up a family. It would be very much easier to talk to them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You see a big difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - and I - of course I say everybody - should have what is due. But - sometimes I think they've gone a bit far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How many evenings a week would you say Mr Mainwaring spent at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh he'd never go anywhere. No. No, he'd never go out. Never a club or any - there was nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Institutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Nor you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Boot clubs, sick club, funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, nothing, no. No clubs at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Raccobites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh he was in the Rechabites, but he never used to go anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He'd just pay in would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did either of you take part in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806212\charrsid11040510 any sport}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Nothing. Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did either of you bet on anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806212\charrsid11040510 dear me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No, very - oh very seldom I went to a theatre. I think I can put it on my - on my - one hand. I went to see the King of Kings. I went to see the Ten - we went to see the Ten Commandments in London, when we were up in London. Ten Commandments, now }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806212\charrsid11040510 what else}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
 did we see? We saw something else too. The Boy - the Man Born to be King. And what else did we - we did see How Green is my Valley once. In Cardiff.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You can remember the ones you've been to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There you are. I remember - I remember the King of Kings. And the Ten Commandments. Dear dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go to any concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well if there'd be a concert in the chapel you see or - any concerts around well - when we could go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They used to have operas here didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, but I - no. I could never go there because I couldn't go and leave the children then. No, I didn't go to the operas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You never went to the opera?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No I don't remember. What did I see once? I did see one. In - school. The county school. What was it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 A school play that would be would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Name one of those operas that they used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Desert Song?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That was it. That was the only one. Yes. Desert Song.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you go to the music hall at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Never went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806212\charrsid11040510 Cinemas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well that's the only ones that we saw.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Hobbies? My dear child. My life was one hobby. Oh dear, dear, dear dear. It was all a hobby I think. Oh dear dear. Oh indeed. Yes, it w
as.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That was your life really wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. Had a busy busy life. There was no - I used to ask myself sometimes you know if I'd hear somebody saying now - there was somebody lazy I wanted to know what lazy was. It would do me good to be lazy s
ometimes. Oh dear, dear. Yes, but it was my life you see, that was my life. Always been like - always my mind was always on the go. And even now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When did you find time to write, to write the poetry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - and that's why I haven't - many people have told me you know - that I should have published them. But I never tried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But a lot of them have been published?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh in the Goliad. Yes, yes, there's about forty hymns. Yes, and there was a minister telling me - well telling Morgan too, and Mo
rgan wants me to - gather them together you see and - and have a hymn book made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were you able to write them when you had the children small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Oh yes, well I'd have - have a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806212\charrsid11040510 minute}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  to myself you see. Yes. It's always been a - been a part of me you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You couldn't help doing it really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
No. No. No, well somebody declaring me - well you must be clever, no I wasn't, I was born like that. It was born in me, it was in me. Of course I could have - I could have thrown it to one sid
e and gone and enjoyed myself, but - that was my enjoyment. And nothing I enjoy more now than to - puzzle out a hymn. Because by now - you see - this new - this new way, the new wording of writing hymns has come. It's different. But then I like to keep to
 the Bible - to the Bible language you see, the - the old way yes, yes. The old Welsh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You're still composing them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. I've got one on hand now. - Yes. Yes, oh yes, it's a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you keep any pets at that time or collect anything or do gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh dear, yes. Oh I've done loads of garden - well I used to keep - I have kept this garden going really until now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about when you had the children small, would you do any gardening then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, and dad used to do most then. Oh yes, used to do most of the garden, but I've always seen to the flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The pot flowers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. And the flowers in the garden too. Yes, always seen to the flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you go out to enjoy yourself, by yourself, without your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - oh no indeed I - I never went out, but remember going out alone to enjoy myself, well I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have any other interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. Except the - except the - the different meetings I used to go - speak to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No other interests really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, I used to go to speak to these meetings of course. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd go round to Sisterhoods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not when the children were small would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, I would go round. I've done it for years. After the children - whe
n the children were in school I used to do it then. Yes well of course - come home from there and then back to Band of Hope after the children. And then after they go to bed I'd begin to do - do other little things you know, sewing or - whatever would hav
e to be done. Mending. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did anyone outside the home help you to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh no. No. I had a little girl here once or twice. To help me a little bit when I wasn't very well then. Girl from Penycae, she was a very nice girl too. But she went to work - the time that the - the war came there was more - there was money to be had.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You mean the last war now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 But this period up to 1918 you didn't have anybody to help you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No, no. No. I couldn't aff
ord it. Well you see - a man's money was only - about - my - I remember my first pay was - one pound seventeen and six a week, first pay. Well the lasted for a - a few years, only daddy used to work - a good bit of overtime and that used to bring in two t
o
 three pounds - a week. Well that wasn't much pay for three or four children was it. But we had to go very warily you see. Yes. Remember now on a - Saturday night I'd want to put - get some - watch now that I had something small to put in the envelope. Bu
t I wanted the envelope to be - something however small it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That was your contribution to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 My contribution to the chapel. Always used to watch that. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you manage if you were ill in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well now that was a pr
oblem you see, well daddy of course had to - do then and - my sister would come. But very little, very little I would be in bed. I'd have to be very ill to be in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did either of you have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I had my sister living by you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 She was in Penycae?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In Penycae and - and his mother was living in Margam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Margam was about two miles away wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. Oh that's three miles from here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And how far was your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh - quarter -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Quarter of a mile is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How much did you see of the relatives then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes, I used to see her every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And your husband's relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 And he used to see his mother every week. She used to come up here. She'd come up here mostly every Friday. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you go down there to Margam as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, we used to go down. Well he used to take the children down you see, \lquote 
cos I couldn't always go because of the - the babies but - push the pram with the two children and it was no joke. And especially after Cwmbrombil. Oh dear, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever manage it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well, yes, yes, used to go very often. Very often. And when I'd be going up to my own home after up there, I used
 to leave the pram down in Cwmbrombil. And go up through the wood, carry the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you go to your old home very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh as often as I could you see, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 That would be about a mile further wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. And that would be up through the woods you see. Terrible climb.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You wouldn't go there very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Not very often with the babies. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have friends then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh friends? Oh yes, I had friends - I had friends, plenty of friends everywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where did you see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well of course there was no much time to - after that it wasn't the same as when I was - not married you see. Well there was no time to think of anyone but your own then. No, when you had little children. You had yo
ur duties then. Pleasures - to go one side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about your friend in Cwmafan and your special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well of course - oh we were always friends to the end, and May after down in - and they used to come here sometimes you know. Yes. Yes, and Dan Roberts, oh yes, they used to come here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did your husband share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Or would he have his own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. We always had the same friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you see them very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well we used to see them often see but of course - when we had the family well we were tied in. Our first duty was here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were the friends ever offered into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Invited here? Oh well well when they used to come - if they'd come down - anywhere near the place -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How often would they come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well I don't know, we - we had lots of - we had friends, ministers friends and they used to come you know and they used to come and stay with us and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When you had the children small though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh they used to come and see you, yes, they didn't mind, it was done, the preachers used to come and stay, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You'd keep the preacher on a Saturday night would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, yes, yes. Yes. Oh yes. Not all the time but - if there were any friends, they'd come here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806212\charrsid11040510 a meal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  of course the same as ourselves, whatever would be perhaps see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would you say that the friends invited in were your friends or your husband's or shared friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh we were the same. Oh we never had anything - we always had everything in common.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Would friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I expect they would, I don't remember much about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 When the children were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Probably they would if they were - anywhere near or if -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about neighbours, would they come in casually without an invitation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, no, no I was friendly with everybody, but - I never went - never made it a practice - to go into one another's houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, what did you do when you got together with friends or neighbours?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh we never - we never - we never went to - to anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Supposing your friend called now from Cwmafon what would you do here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. Yes. Well there we are, we'd talk and that was all. That was all, that was all was expected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 No. No. Daddy had bought this house before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In this district where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I don't know, I don't know whether there was anybody important here. They were all important then I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 This was just being built then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There's all the street, they're all the same you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the district of Port Talbot then, who do you think were the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh I don't know, the most important people in Port Talbot I remember - were the doctors and the ministers. They were consider
ed important then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Why do you think they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I don't know, we always did, we were always taught - to consider them important when we were children. We always curtsied to the minister and to the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about when you moved here and you had your own children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well they were taught to consider them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You still thought they were the most important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes. Yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you come into contact with them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh yes, everybody that was - here you see all did. Oh yes. Came into contact with them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the shopkeepers then in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, yes, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I - don't know, we - we were all right with the shopkeepers as well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the clergy in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
And the clergy, well then - to me of course I had always been used to the clergy you see, always been. And I was very - very friendly with the clergy here now and Margam - well - everybody in Margam church were ju
st like ourselves you know, and here again in the same. I've always been - friendly with them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the teachers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I was all right with all the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Who do you think they mixed with, the associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well they associated with themselves. Mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
The farmers were one - there was something wrong in one farm the - all farmers would be there. They were wonderful. All together I remember now - my father couldn't go - somebody ha
d died, some - a funeral, and if nobody could go because being in the middle of the harvest, oh I had to go to represent the family. Somebody had to go to represent the family. Oh yes, there was - quite a clan, farmers. And I don't know - I think teachers
 were the same. I always got on well with them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about employers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You mentioned D.R. David?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, well D.R. David and - of course I didn't know Mr Byers but I remember them of course, we were friendly wit
h the Davids, always had been, and as far as I knew, all the family, the girls and all, I was very friendly with them, very - of course I can't say anything - further than that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about other employers in the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 I didn't know about th
e others, no. Oh Johnnie Davis and - Evan Davis and those you know, well there again - they were an old Margam family. Because we were all - friendly you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 They owned one of the other tin works didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes, yes. Yes. And we were all friendly, all of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Now there was a - a little bit of - distinction. They tried to be different but I don't know whether they were. I never saw any difference. And I was always friendly with all the church people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What made you think there was a distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There was a little - especially in the schools. In schools you would find it. We found it in Groes school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about when you moved up here to Port Talbot, to Ta
nygroes Street, what sort of people would you say went to the church in this district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well there was - oh quite a number of people go to church around here, but - to me - they wee all the same, I didn't mind. I never felt any different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What about the people going to chapel, what sort of people would you say went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well - just like myself, but - not - very few people went to the Welsh chapel around here, until they built Calvaria. I remember them building C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806212\charrsid11040510 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 lvaria. Used to be a pool of water down there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It was a Baptist chapel as well wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Yes. It was real Baptist chapel, they had the water underneath them ready. Oh well, yes, I remember then there was a - a very good congregation and very good a people b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5388354\charrsid11040510 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 ing there. Yes I remember that very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, I don't think there was, I think they were all the same here. Everybody tried to do their best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you think any one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Oh well, I don't know, there may be a little bit of the element - in some - some people but - especially people that came here now from a long way off a
nd had - been rather well to do, perhaps they think that - I knew just one or two - families, but they were very soon put to - know - that they were no bigger than - we were all the same here. Yes, oh a little bit of that, but it - that's died out long ag
o.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Were some families thought of as rough and some as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well I don't know about - I don't now about anybody that was rough around here. Didn't see much of that, there wasn't much of that here. Not in this locality. But I suppose it was
 - in the poorer parts of the town perhaps you - you would find it, down, lower down. In Aberafon, down the - sandfields really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 The other side of the river really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Down that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 You wouldn't have any contact there would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no, no. No, we wouldn't come into contact with them much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 There may have been but - I - never came into contact with anyone like - that. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you have a struggle to make ends meet at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well yes. I did have a struggle sometimes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Well I had to go through and - and - and I wanted to be - I didn't want to owe anybody any - an ha'epenny that's my big thing, 
didn't want to owe anybody a penny. I'm afraid I've been a little bit sutbborn in that way. Yes. May have been - proud but I don't know, I - can't help it, you can't help what's in you can you. Can't help your nature can you. No. No, no. But there you are
. Struggle sometimes. Oh yes. Couldn't get what I wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How did you feel about that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 
Well there you are, I went without myself. I went without for the children to have it. I didn't mind that at all. Never worried, no. I never worried about
 going without myself. Never. If only the children were all right. And they've more than paid me today. Yes. Comes back doesn't it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 What difference did it make when your husband was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh well it did make a difference. Mad
e a big difference. I remember the time when - all the slump was here in Port Talbot. It was the - I don't remember what was - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5388354\charrsid11040510 whe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 ther it was the time of the war or - and my husband was out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 In the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806212\charrsid11040510 thirties}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510  I expect wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes. Yes. 
I remember that very well. And - he had to go down to get the dole of course, and I've been over in town, I hadn't seen - the queue for the dole before that. And I was coming home. Been over - over in town, and I saw my husband in the queue. Going for the
 
dole. That was the first time. I came home and broke my heart. Oh dear dear dear. I'll never forget that. It was a - terrible feeling. I could see him in the middle and - I was thinking to myself oh he was too good to be there. Yes. Yes. But he wasn't ver
y long, some were years you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 How often was Mr Mainwaring out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 About - about once or twice. Yes. But it was once he was out for a while then. When that - slump was. I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 He remained in the same firm didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 It's just that the work was stopped altogether wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Stopped altogether. No work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13252668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Did you ever have to get help from the Guardians, the parish or a charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11029534 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14097869\charrsid11040510 Oh no. No. No.
\par }}